[{"Name":"Hugh Gao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFlJmYlj82sx6sLKOje56IkZUG693ZnITvHtJUekoopvQlVKt9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came here for dinner in my first year at UBC almost everyday, because it‚Äôs probably the best dining hall out of the three. The food was very consistent. My recommendations: butter chicken from Square Kitchen, fried rice from Custom Kitchen, and the occasional dim sum on weekends. There used to be serious health safety issues with bugs being found in the food, so be careful of that","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMRDeLLpeWOB1zL0Lr950WO3mPYyfYGnkq9_BTJ&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Alexander Hunt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKntg94WsHup3cVgJBk3yO0jaRf4K-ndL2T0xGy94s_gBQtie8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Orchid Common is one of the first year residence dining halls at UBC. Being built in 2016/2017, OC's dinning hall has a main seating area and another room for additional guests.

The atmosphere is really spacious and the architecture allows for great  natural sunlight. The seating there can sit 200-300 people. At regular meal time, 8am -9am, 11am to 12pm, 6pm to 7pm, expect there to be lots of people.

The food there is okay and there is variety there every day. The portion is small (all-you can eat, but you get pre-allocated portions) so you can get multiple kinds of food. Sometimes, the food is too saulty or the tasting is off. The dinning hall is open from 7am to 10pm every day, but the food may not be plentiful or have great variety when you come to eat outside of regular meal hours.

The pricing is cheapest around breakfast at around $12. Lunch is $16 and dinner is at $20. The food is all you can eat. If you have a UBC meal plan, then you can go to OC as many times as you want and are unlimited in entries. If you have residence meal plan, then the cost would not matter to you. You are not charged per entry, but charged for the entire meal plan as a whole.

For food options there, you can expect salad bar, yogurt ball, vegetarian options for food, stir-fry grill, and burger grill. There are fresh fruits like apple, bananas, oranges and plum. There is tea, coffee and juice available. Their Philly cheesesteak sandwich and burgers is good.

To know the menu of OC, you can download an app to see their menus. Their lunch and dinner menus are the same.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0aPX-vNdBTU_jqkiXOSgJRpgqyUEHS9HhAyML&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2023-9-13"},{"Name":"yoyo huang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHfL3bnaoL_4LM9Q6GkGocV7c7Sko1louBNBsuDc0OrdaDTJLa=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The food here is very unstable, sometimes good, sometimes bad. Once was way too salty, it tastes like it got drowned in salt and it even stings my tongue. Not goodüëé","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Saskia Asyari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOw-vGRppaZWH-87l0DTjRp6cH2-cGmCr2why8D5leomPAj1GywA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here for lunch and this is probably the best value of $15 you will ever spend in Vancouver for an all-you-can-eat eatery option. They have salad bars, bakery section, beverage bars, and fruit baskets. Great selection of menus from western, Asian, Indian, and vegetarian foods. The menu varies everyday though, you can check on their website. They serve halal food options foods such as peri-peri chicken and kung pao chicken noodles. They grew some of their own veggies and fruits. When you‚Äôre leaving, you‚Äôll be allowed to either take home a fruit or pastry and one beverage with your own mug/bottle. Will definitely be back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCaEKVOt1CdDyAyFi_ZBkw_TWa3ENkeMQ1oyuf&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2023-3-15"},{"Name":"dabossdud","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8qzSvvMAD5ffHxPidijA4FBHoh1MqBeLVTwN70J852UBbgpO7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"To be honest if it wasn't for the newer building, it would be pretty bad. The food is comparable to totem park, except they don't have pizza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkwULCaVFlfP0ezbHsbSwlugj6abTd-iAvQ9jg&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2024-2-17"},{"Name":"Monique L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9o0N3sSdNhQoJRm_UTMB_81UV1EwCg55ZvQAZUsA1N6LBkXzD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Best place to go for food by far on campus. The brunch is my go to at Open Kitchen and I'm never disappointed. Eggs Benny, super fresh breakfast sandwiches, buffet style yoghurt parfait, salad bars, dim sum, and so many selections! Something for every kind of eater (ie Vegan, Gluten free, paleo, carnivore). Definitely beats going to Vanier's or Totem cafeteria.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgNdCb4Sio0BJe6HhHYusx5okeS7mU7FNGVQRY&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2017-3-16"},{"Name":"Lizzie S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5qIG1VmBASZQRSYXsIMifm6rtLhZA6xcKTGDs0bvXyJT2pXkmsA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this student restaurant. Very fresh food. Good place for breakfast.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOU2m_RFTQNNcxwo_5q7KsyjSchNVQOGZMxhP5B&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2024-2-12"},{"Name":"Tala Vera","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJcvcL500DcEodS8A6CxW3NgQRJf6q0SX7Xd4hIbm5xb8dUiA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"UBC students in line for dinner at one of the school‚Äôs cafeterias were greeted by an unwelcome guest this week.
Video circulating online shows a dark-coloured rat on top of the grill station at Open Kitchen, a cafeteria in the Orchard Commons residence on UBC‚Äôs Vancouver campus.
ADVERTISEMENT

First-year student Isabel Curiston was in line for dinner around 7:30 p.m. Tuesday when she saw the rodent standing next to the food.

‚ÄúI look up and I see this rat coming out of the cracks where they keep fruits and vegetables, and just standing there,‚Äù she said.
RELATED STORIES
UBC delays return to most in-person classes again, citing Omicron concerns
UBC obtains 1st edition of Shakespeare's First Folio, promises 'unprecedented' public access
UBC researchers look at 'gel' biomaterials to help treat spinal cord injuries
The rat caught the attention of many students in the cafeteria. Curiston pulled out her phone and recorded the encounter, which ended when a kitchen worker grabbed the rat with a pair of tongs. The critter fell to the floor, and the worker carried on with his duties.
Dinner service continued, but UBC told CTV News the grill station was immediately closed down and sanitized, and all the food was thrown out.
‚Äú(We) are working actively with our pest control partner to address the situation," said Colin Moore, director of UBC Food Services, in a statement to CTV News. "All employees have been informed and reminded about proper sanitation measures as necessary,‚Äù
UBC also confirmed Vancouver Coastal Health has since inspected the cafeteria, finding no evidence of rodent infestation and saying it‚Äôs content with the school‚Äôs sanitation and pest control measures.
Students living in several residences at UBC pay for a meal plan, which gives them credit to buy meals at school cafeterias and restaurants. Curiston wants UBC to consider giving students some form of a reimbursement or meal voucher, saying despite health inspectors signing off on the cafeteria‚Äôs cleanliness, the image of a rat in the kitchen will keep her from dining there for some time.
‚ÄúI refuse to go back until I know for a fact they‚Äôve dealt with the rat problem,‚Äù she said. ‚ÄúIf they set out traps, I‚Äôd feel more safe eating there.‚Äù‚Äã","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNdu1L40XRvbU__oyjBuTwVZOpwceqlwIHYwesg&fid=0x0:0xd0113f8377d90e0c"],"When":"2022-1-20"}]

[{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved my experience at the Gallery. Ordered burgers with salads and my friends also ordered some chicken wraps and fries. Everything was pretty tasty and well seasoned. Beers were fantastic. Prices a little bit on the high side, especially for a restaurant inside campus, but it‚Äôs definitely worth trying.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOs1KGPNL5W9iWl4zIgcxQSrnJ2fRONlu24N4UE&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Anthony Le","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIC22IEsZIbsu-lUm5EyMjgm7JYJbJkRjU13-W8XkZYXAuixkB6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pretty good place for a nice meal for ubc students. There wasn‚Äôt necessarily any service, but nonetheless the food was pretty good. Definitely would go here for a drink it I was a ubc student","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9K99fN-Zftq2MUemombIFm2bz26P8kglKa8XA&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Randal Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-rLwNvZI_YNkKUeSaM-3PNFSDfyyf9aevvVnQDsEtEwj3jDdP=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The dining room is spacious and has lots of natural light making it a good spot for lunch. During lunchtime there was no loud music playing so I could have a conversation with a friend. You order food and drinks at the bar, but I got both pretty quickly. I had a red sangria which seemed reasonably good. I had a citrus and beet salad which was also good but not very filling if you're expecting it to be a meal. The service from the staff serving the food and clearing the table seemed reasonably good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I like this place. I wouldn't go here as a night out, but at the right times, it's a chill hang. The atmosphere varies wildly depending on the day. On some nights it's louder and is in line with what you'd expect a university bar to be like, and sometimes it's very relaxed, and you can even find some people using it as a study spot (not something I would consider or really recommend, but you do you as long as it's not busy and no one needs the table). Sometimes it's somewhere in between or a weird mix of both. It's not always predictable, but I've found that to hit the quieter days that I prefer, early evening during exam season at school is best, and summer in general are chiller than the main academic year.
The food is good, often surprisingly good. The menu items are well thought-out and tasty, and nicely presented. It's not a veg-centric establishment but there's lots of choice for vegans! Off the current menu, I've had the Power Punch Salad, the Vegan Pulled Jackfruit, the Vegan Burger, Vegan Chick'n Caesar Wrap, and the Tempeh Teriyaki. I wasn't particularly impressed by the Caesar wrap - it wasn't awful, I just didn't feel like it was worth $19.5, but everything else was a delight. I'm glad their vegan burger is a (seemingly) housemade, minimally processed black bean patty instead of beyond meat or similar! I usually won't order a salad as my meal, but the Power Punch is substantial! The side salad that comes with the sandwich orders is actually pretty nice too.
They make good cocktails and have a long list of local draft beers on tap which I haven't really had a chance to dip into, but I got the "Green Bird" for fun on St. Patrick's Day, which is just a version of their house "T-Bird" lager that's been coloured green (maybe naturally, judging by the grassy notes I got from it, but I don't know for sure). It was actually a good lager though!
Sometimes the staff is nice enough, sometimes I get the vibe that they're too cool to be serving me or something, but because the only interactions you have with them are when you order and pay at the bar and when they bring your food out, an unenthusiastic bartender doesn't ruin the whole experience. Because of this service style, you can expect to be in and out of here faster than you would at a full table service restaurant, but it's not fast food, so dishes still take as much time to prep as they would at a "regular" sit-down place. It's also pricier than typical counter service food, but very reasonably priced compared to off-campus restaurants that serve food of this quality, and there's no obligation to tip 20%. To me, the service model, fair prices, and high quality are a combination of the best elements of counter service and full service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQwEdJ88aXsSlarpRs-9jcRwBTBo0B-hIa3KfE&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2021-4-19"},{"Name":"Steve Morgan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmgrmzSyB3CC_qWamR3pXmaZna6-RxfqDluiFzTGNrypDReGc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very large service area. Games. Foosball table. Big patio. Not the least bit crowded for lunch in summertime. They have a limited menu but it has decent variety. Quality of the food is good for a university joint. Beer list contains a good number of local, craft beers. Kids can dine here but no kids menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPovaBoxIJBbbrqqo0D1-7ZOWCRu2vS1WYswiw&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2019-7-10"},{"Name":"N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIY4v8Faubu_Z2iYv4KPw3dI0PsoX4C2vKMs2dyC6KeQw7f0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Almost no service (walk up to bar to order) and any service you do get is most often unfriendly. Like the type of attitude you would think takes more effort than being nice. They are not making a case for autogratuities in general because I think this is one of the reasons this place gets away with such unpleasant staff. The other reasons include that there just isn't that much choice on campus and the food is basic but decent here. The view is nice if you're out on the patio. And there's a lot of space. It's very sad that the sit-down nice restaurant didn't make it because that's exactly what the area needs. They just didn't promote it and since this is the top floor, no one discovers this space by walking by. The service at the Gallery when it was in the old sub was never this sad. Have pride in whatever you do. Just making people happy and not disappointed is a reward in itself. Or fake it. Whatever. Just don't make people more down than when they came in.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jade","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyJzoLeWrDhvC2NhSPJXZCJklxu-S39z3hI0-Hrrv9m9AA5ZkKQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is my first review below 5 stars.
They automatically charge a tip without telling their customers (I didn't notice any signage). This makes their prices misleading. Also, since I wasn't with a group and I ordered at the register auto-grat does not seem reasonable. I will happily change my review and return as a customer when they are more forthcoming about their prices.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Haleh Magnus","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZGl2rvHWlqbzuuFKZ9pHQfQXwlTmRHH4ep4A1K4mjlsDM4dQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went there for a light food, beer and to listen to good #jazzmusic from amazing musician of UBC Jazz Club. The space was bright , spacious. I found it busy and big line up. The Jazz performance are on Wednesday 6pm to 9pm by UBC Jazz Club.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPIUZZN56p20ZRBTeW6npihhigzi31LzbVDTis&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2022-9-22"}]

[{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best places at UBC to hang out! Lovely staff and wonderful vibe. Tried the grilled chicken ramen and it was generously filled, almost couldn‚Äôt finish the whole meal. Other friends of mine ordered burgers and they said they were fantastic. Prices aren‚Äôt cheap, so it‚Äôs a place to go for a celebration once in a while.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCAcUJj4YsDoBohcTlkfqkVoKoS5nD30m0xhBk&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"M J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKuOygw8Aep3D50DIY1TUyT5-BADbHqefvUMdU3qf0JomdEvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great selection of food and craft beer, good place to hang out for a few drinks. The small nachos was enough for us to share between 4-5 people, loved the roast beef sandwich too. Deep fried Mac and cheese was nicely cooked and the tomato sauce helps with the heaviness of the Mac and cheese. Ordered the IPA and loved it - crisp and had a nice aroma. The service was fast and attentive although it was busy at the time of visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXcjzjGRoyy6vduMIRbCuk6WLqez6jCJo-pmrv&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Dylan Magierek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0kVFJpnKEbseG6UEIeqqL4lraFc9x941pplBP3I-C35nxYYtP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was a nice sojourn from a long day of driving and walking around the UBC campus moving my son into the dorms.  The food was very good: especially the fries, chicken sandwich, side salad and burgers.  The French Dip was just pretty good.  I wouldn‚Äôt recommend it.  It didn‚Äôt have enough meat to balance out the kinda hard roll it came on.  Lots of beer choices and I enjoyed the Pilsner.  Expensive for a brewery/sorta pub!  But good service and atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9A45j3pzrU9X5vPV34VvyOZ59GJCSIADcF_aQ&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Anthony Le","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIC22IEsZIbsu-lUm5EyMjgm7JYJbJkRjU13-W8XkZYXAuixkB6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice place for a sit-down, fancy-ish meal. The drinks were pretty good, and the food is delicious; definitely a nice place for a formal meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOE7MmrhhKXG2H5sjxLe8eW9H0WqnR-Tuz2xtla&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Vanessa Becker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjP-M2atXZC7s46eJ4wd5XC-RHr2pn3fRoPwoLQqghdxSrQBA9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Browns is a nice pub type spot. We got seated quickly for lunch and our server was friendly and attentive. Drinks and food came out at decent times.
My sister has celiacs disease and had heard Browns has gluten free options. They were able to make modifications on a meal and she enjoyed it, Blackened chicken Caesar with no croutons.
I got a cheeseburger with Caesar salad.
There‚Äôs a ramp and accessible entrance and chairs can be moved to fit wheelchairs.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgyStbHqW6IqBgmoutJLEDmIuxPuu1FMQBsNe6&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-5-19"},{"Name":"Maria N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvvSp5rMnSOuZlWMjCChnc3kIAvhaXhf7fzSVxvOmtGCdirlnS=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty food and quick service. There were barely any customers when we came in on Saturday afternoon.
We got a chicken burger with a side of fries and a salad with a chicken breast (came a bit late.) Both tasted good.
Very decent place to grab a bite around UBC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMh6lhWfsmLChgTOHHA4RM65-xzqYFv7EYhpgf5&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Biggie Sandhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJJXTSWG9GRBzr7s-0VIl70S37U8PyPayiekKKBiKbK7ygPFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had our work Christmas Dinner here. Great workers great food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMIthBnLk1en1HwdUUDWZ3GIt9z3pNtalz6zAt&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"Zibiah Sandhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIV7J0QaWpaOWLAzK9jqKBW9H-FOCY6ViMt-aqG3Okqi6IgVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am following up from my previous review that I had left a few weeks ago. Despite having a negative experience, the staff at Browns Crafthouse went above and beyond to make sure that my friends and I had a good experience to make up for what had initially happened. The manager Matt reached out and was very kind and generous, and offered to make the experience better for us. They accommodated drinks and many appetizers for our large group, and were super sweet the entire time. I cannot remember our servers name, but she was a tall caucasian woman. She provided excellent service and took my friend's gluten allergy very seriously. It was some of the best customer experiences I had. Matt himself had come out and greeted us, apologized for the previous experience, and made sure we had a great time. They went above and beyond to make sure that we had a good experience, and it was really appreciated!","Images":null,"When":""}]

Ambience was comfortable and staff were attentive.  Will definitely go back again if I'm ever in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPH91GTRSzk1oTMM9p1IO53xs2WIKdEM3AxtjvG&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Stephanie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBV5KRG75WlxmWo1wuDhWSQhlZCOao4V2_9kFkOn0OqRNe45TP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We came on a Saturday during happy hour. The restaurant was pretty empty. I love how it's laid out and the number of tables they have.

Our server was knowledgeable and friendly. Happy hour wildlight drinks get $2 off

Inverted dude - was a coffee based drink. I didn't really like it. I wouldn't get it again

Negroni - strong and delicious

Mussels and fries (16) - plentiful and well seasoned. Loved the sauce. The French fries were crispy and addictive. Would recommend

Chicken wings 10 pieces (12) - pretty standard. Crispy on the outside. On the sweeter side.

Overall would come back to try their other items. Prices during happy hour are a steal","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDxXa1iPMIaDUb3dYUzqDVP3M8rux0dOeqzQqE&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"Crabby Ermine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7ghzWacgyIAQrG2Lk7qt0s7V3r_adVAnu6EbLXS1Ck1zLBRgjvA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"10/10 experience. Great service. Great atmosphere. Great food.  Parking is free underground and register with check in. Loved all the dishes we had today.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaJa3xW-fN0TaVwqmoUrrmVKfqPIH5GB-Ezcgu&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Ray Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3wj8Ne3ngI4eg9ouEU6zPmvERlQuudbckz4ma4Vg6pfYrsWM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful service in a nicely appointed dining room with a fun and trendy atmosphere. The location is particularly convenient for parents who are looking for more upscale dining options while visiting their kids studying at the nearby university.  The seafood chowder, seafood linguine, and duck breast were particularly good. We went on ‚ÄúWine Wed‚Äù where select bottles were 50% off offering good value. Portions were just adequate but not what you would consider large, but that just means you get to leave room to try their yummy desserts (I particularly liked the Stawberry Fraisier, and the Basque Cheesecake with red wine reduction).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4tLmOOTAsLJvn5WtbD1OyzUmHRy-gI1MFkAD8&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"Riley Taylor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ-9EcAoNHnhEH_CEFhkVuk3VNbTy11CmDBZ6MWN5FAekK6Cw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"TOP TIER. Premium EVERYTHING.

Quite literally one of the best dining experiences that we have ever had. From the second we walked in, we were approached by GM Margot who made us feel the warmth and excitement to host us for supper. Victor, our bartender didn‚Äôt miss a beat with suggestions and promptness of beverage top ups! Food‚Ä¶. Don‚Äôt get me started!!! I‚Äôm salivating a day later writing this review thinking about how beautifully curated each dish was designed. Chef Chow is a total artist and a master of his craft. A few musts include the Tuna Tartar, Oyster Motoyaki, Beet and Burrata salad, duck, the scallops OMG, sable fish‚Ä¶ DOUBLE OMG and an array of desserts that the pastry team had skillfully curated to reflect British Columbia‚Äôs nature and environment.

From the bottom of our hearts- HUGE thanks to the entire team for the special hospitality and delicacies. You all truly outdid yourselves.

Thank you!!
Riley and Anna","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8Z8XjNkHyhAvJM342-p_KpqBWYsIkY1rwLmYe&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWuLCrwKa9NLpGvoI7KXeamb10EWAoAmRoPxgdu96hyYHG6mtPkhg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came the other day as a solo diner for lunch. Had the smoked sable fish chowder and the harvest green salad. The chowder was the best I've ever had. Very nice atmosphere. My server Mel was also welcoming, attentive, and came across as a genuinely very lovely person.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfJygC171kXxCcNsSJo3-wLP0SQ2Uyt1Mnw7Sc&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-9-26"},{"Name":"Alex Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIuPG0P_xvSAHjLq3lehdcGbMVx_kB14iyd4zXzj-7VOUEMAw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First and foremost, a huge thank you to our server Naomi for making our evening at Wildlight truly special. She was an absolute joy, incredibly sweet, and very attentive and informative throughout our meal.

We split the pescatarian board and mushroom gnocchi, had the strawberry frasier for dessert, and finished with the complimentary shortbread.

Everything was absolutely wonderful.

The pescatarian board showcased a fantastic mix of seafood and pickled vegetables and was a true pleasure to explore.

The mushroom gnocchi was the epitome of comfort food with some great textures.

The strawberry frasier was incredibly refreshing and had the best ripe strawberry flavor in several forms.

The shortbread was a lovely surprise and sweet treat to end the meal before we left!

My partner and I each had two cocktails (Awesome Blossom and Pacific Vesper in the picture) and were thoroughly tempted to try more! Each cocktail was delicious, well balanced, and complimentary to the food.

Wildlight was a lovely experience from start to finish. Both my partner and I would strongly recommend an evening here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORrSSDOzpPYS1WvgEYc9nnBneuVG28DZxfzgy3&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Mary Proulx","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEhEtou551etajvQPOzB4dygQrXePqTCHvPLlyMk3uMrquxnRA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love gnocchi - the mixed mushroom stroganoff gnocchi here is the most fresh and flavourful ever. Half price bottle of wine Wednesday a wonderful surprise. Dessert is beautiful and enough to share. A fabulous lunch with friends; food, location and space and great service - thanks to Brandon","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTKSTnTBH98HWxtMSpyf0Dq2J26QKkVW-G2ebL&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-10-23"}]

Anyway a good place to eat around UBC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMy-NvXHubthP6fKrTnGkTCghY0IwIsMJY4MAOw&fid=0x0:0x52216304f25772e2"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Isabelle Cho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLBjZAJ5N5Vf61U8bAV-vmsfvv8q6XPugQT2Yj1QY3XiGZmEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time trying mazesoba and it was pretty good. I liked how you were able to choose the size you wanted. Noodle were also pretty bouncy as well. Service was okay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlxg2CDnEkBwjyqyzM_su7S9HTHVfGJ7FrsSA5&fid=0x0:0x52216304f25772e2"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Ryan Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJg51dkTiELfwGSC3YeGg0Cqc2FbwTcp56uR5oMbjvMxs9-kgt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Surprisingly the best gyoza I've had in Vancouver. Compares really well to gyoza in Japan, really appreciate the corn starch slurry layer. Could be a bit more juicy, but overall very good for the price in Vancouver.
Great mentaiko mazesoba, really good chashu.
Good service in general, nothing crazy.
Milk tea was a bit sweet","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAm-IE0G313_iWr4Sw78bxgmaTQ2nP38DwoN77&fid=0x0:0x52216304f25772e2"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"Jason Foo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIviPWCwBZ9CELxlfzmvetOnkGvkTCIJGcCV87BO6JMjSbVFg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Friendly and hardworking staff. Both the ramen and the mazesoba were good. The pork was slightly less fatty and harder than the usual ramen, but otherwise nice flavours.

Servings are also a little small, up sized it and realised it looked more like normal serving. Probably better to serve more to cater to the student population.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxr74lRM_hjEQIzAYwZSCD6IvxA1XlUaqvyE-A&fid=0x0:0x52216304f25772e2"],"When":"2023-8-9"},{"Name":"Rico C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJSPs7IwE2pPBNxNqoF9AWcF7glNi-GV2crXAnc0vJ62CxPEebCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good portions though soup ramen could use some more soup. Unfortunately long wait for the meals","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_T6Wc6hTlg0cwo0eqvzElG5H3kM7Jj3wEU06S&fid=0x0:0x52216304f25772e2"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Sung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLeVcYj3-ZDXlwZ2o-FctUomqPCQwtliej9CUEI0ZuG2Zpbcg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The mazesoba was very disappointing. Considering it is campus food it is okay. Especially the type of noodle that absorbs all the moisture which make overall dish so dry. I got salmon it was very dry and hard to swallow. Most of my friends got Zenbu which was better with meat oil but still it is very dry‚Ä¶ I think undon noodle must be much better with tautly texture. And couple of other friends got ramen but they had way less soup which was hard to consider as ramen.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXMfseh0r3-pO1t9km1YWuZvXue_njWC60ZHm_&fid=0x0:0x52216304f25772e2"],"When":"2024-3-8"},{"Name":"Miyuki Food","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIefbmBJIFd8vluRG1CtvO_cHUxsRdwtm3bVobO6E-icLpG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Noodles were tasty! I got the mentaiko cream mazesoba and it was very tasty! The chilli powder was super good!! You can get any size for same price but it's the same amount of noodles and toppings (it's just more soup). The waiter was quite nice and brought rice at the end to finish the cream sauce. My friend says the original ramen was average.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHjn9o9NH4BtH9gzNPuscVipBcJepA6cMCIPU&fid=0x0:0x52216304f25772e2"],"When":"2023-11-21"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Reliable for simple and satisfying homestyle Korean food. Nothing blows me away but everything is good and flavourful. The meals all include lots of vegetables which I appreciate, and things aren't overly oily.
There's no atmosphere to speak of and I think they probably have more takeout than dine-in customers, but having done both, dine-in is the way to go, because the food comes out super fresh. The people who work there are nice and hardworking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXR2zL3EAW7SvQOTWGiznVuK83Eyw_nBeqY_6G&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2024-2-25"},{"Name":"Yuchang Zhan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJCu1wqeMUBpitsBVSAyQ29MPKUdyLQ__YQ2QBJ3AHY3DJY3g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went several times and recommended to all my friends. The owners are truly caring about the customers and always have THE BEST service ever. Once I mentioned I was cold, and later the owner offered me warm miso soup for free. This really made my entire evening.

Soups are always served warm with large portion. The pork bone is absolutely my to-go dish. So flavourful with so so much meat!

Never disappointed with their inari, I have tried beef, spicy salmon, shrimp, spam, tuna, kimchi, seaweed, some were even gifted by the owner. All the toppings are so delicious and flavourful, it‚Äôs hard for me to pick one favourite to be honest! The seasoning of rice makes everything even another level.

Foods are so authentic. My Korean friends said the dishes really brought them back to Korea. If you love Korean foods like me, you should definitely try it out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNM3_rcDUbPQB4N10byn-i2gBKLWgdvTB41RrFy&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2022-3-10"},{"Name":"Sasha Sadiora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqMB9CioB05yUeMJrchJN57cOo1BuZF_w3T8u4DS8Px3X91XTp=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The lady was very nice but the fact I paid a EXTRA $3.50 for cheese and got a KRAFT SINGLES slice is CRAZY","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLwLofol73ghxQyaPInWLd2gYRGqz6pWOzjLKe&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Niloufar Sharif","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3A88lqgzyr_DZVby4DylCumivfYhcpesHqnFk78Ei2iZVsggWWg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a student, this place is so comforting and the food tastes authentic and homemade. The owners here are AMAZING, so caring, and kindhearted! They gifted us three free inaris to try as well as miso soup! Now the food. The portions are so generous and they will not cheap out on quality or amount of protein despite the affordable prices.
We got the gamja-tang and galbitang. The galbitang has a very clean broth and you can taste the fresh ingredients. Gamja-tang was packed with flavors and spices and soooo much pork!

Cant wait to go back and try all of their other dishes üòã","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMNkVy2Nj_O8RT1_bytgunpwMTz22R8HjUrX_Hu&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2022-3-6"},{"Name":"Ahnaf Muqset Haque","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9JdQZtXBMvD618JDWqRmaMkXk-I2NhqdPuW2NLQFP33Qn87KikQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The only reason for my four star is their  customer service is heart warming. Really welcoming and good service. However, if you are actually looking for really really good Korean food then this probably isn't the place. It's okay as I would describe it but definitely not the best. Also, quantity is not adequate. However, trying to improve quantity first would be resonable step towards improvement!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPATOMJVNA_QXKyqiMpX11OXghmAXYiZDhRB6OR&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2019-4-19"},{"Name":"Anne W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVq8l7IxqCBT6CUTt6a8ydNheNQQYDJZKBxOYNsNiNzdtSpTCtW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The quality of the food here is excellent! I got the Jjajang Beef Udon today and it's now one of my favourite meals on campus. The sauce is delicious, as is the side of pickled daikon. The sauce is generous, so I might be able to get a side of rice and stretch it to two lunches (helpful with the high cost of living these days!).

Staff are lovely and helpful people. The outdoor seats on a good weather day are in the sun, so it's a great spot to enjoy your lunch. So glad this place is here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2GSZ-Y2SmizoNXA-E9OpCto2VOEvGfTSaozkJ&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2023-3-21"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I ordered Inari, it‚Äôs ok. The meat or topping to rice proportion was a bit off. There‚Äôs more rice than topping. I ordered 3 but it‚Äôs not enough, and it came out to be around 14$ so I‚Äôll say just order a regular meal instead of this as it‚Äôs not that filling. The service was pretty good tho and the atmosphere was nice and cozy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOanBKptQ-R_H5eiyx4s67HHQU7ukggwSAkZ7tv&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2023-10-2"},{"Name":"cbl Google","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKseLK4QE-uFmbW8_hEmTOkS9RGzjwTJs3q9tyPwtQSc-dy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Korean foods and such an awesome owner! Definitely a gem in the village area. Tried a few of their new inaris and was not disappointed. The spicy salmon and bulgigi are highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMixXDyBd0gN0Cf58omWSw-4LIfMRQAXe33CFI&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2021-10-11"}]

This is good. One of the LARGEST wraps I‚Äôve ever had, must have weighed several pounds. The quality and balance of meat and vegetables is perfect. I will eat these all the time. I ordered a mix wrap, chicken, beef and lamb and all three are cooked perfect and not dry.
The counter service was so nice and accommodating. Upstairs was clean and a generally great place for lunch!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPm2KQDyO2c1CL0fzUMucqmbPUMgqg47YuRE_9v&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"FARZAM ameri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUC2df7lOXeiqMsnPi2htms2568VuOUkmExj9MZ8kkh6j2hvhus=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered Loghmeh kebab, and I have to say optimistically under 40% of that kebab contains actual Meat. The food was tasteless and It was just waste of money. I STRONGLY suggest you not to go there.
Staff was really polite and friendly though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoCVXxYvNnPrU6RCsUdI-VTH87WanqMj-btLQ2&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Extremely delicious and huge portion size (tho the size might vary some days, I have put the two pics for comparison). First time I went, the portion size was quite small for the price but the second time I went, they gave me a huge portion which lasted for 2 meals in total. I love the Vaziri meal that they have!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPih8L_Q2wK2QfkznE7CiefGaptLdidvJ3Bpds5&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-4-16"},{"Name":"Mariena Bui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6Nw1jeBXne8haJacgZytBHrMEqU2gmOMAF3l5QWK0CwO3rXPJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the saffron chicken with zeresht rice and I was satisfied with how the food taste and how filling it was, that I even had leftovers. My husband ordered khoreshte ghayme and he said that this place made this dish very well. For dessert we got sholeh shard and I love how it this place didn‚Äôt make this dessert to sweet! Next time I‚Äôm in UBC I will probably go to this place again ‚ò∫Ô∏è","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCCrILJyF2kem_vb-iTitmN7-tSH1WfxWLBmab&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-2-29"},{"Name":"Negin Rahimi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4DUUoCWRf2VeIHKqwIhVGBDp6aPH06WL8KyLGIL_eC6FWBXb5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I recently visited the UBC branch of this restaurant near closing time. Unfortunately, the two jooje kabab (chicken) dishes we ordered were not warm. When I asked for a replacement and for them to be warmed up, they simply reheated the same plate, which did not resolve the issue and took a long time. The taste of the food was also disappointing, and the chicken was not cooked well. We ended up requesting a refund, but since it was late at night (around 11 pm), we couldn't find another place to eat. I have had a great experience at their other branch, but I cannot recommend this particular branch due to the poor service and quality that fell short of my expectations for Sahel Restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7yKfp8eM4dYI6zdmfXa1F0jAkoq40k9-j-8vc&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-5-23"},{"Name":"Miyuki Food","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIefbmBJIFd8vluRG1CtvO_cHUxsRdwtm3bVobO6E-icLpG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So good!! I got the lamb and beef donair and the meat and everything was tasty, and the service was great. There is also a nice upstairs area with seating and a tv","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFpW22RVhCzjq0t8O64yMaiiDBQ5d2EBHb_Nw&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-4-9"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"New branch of Sahel at UBC featuring donair and Persian food. The ordering counter is downstairs with a seating area upstairs. It wasn't particularly clean: some tables had crumbs and there was trash on the floor under some tables, which weirdly is carpeted. The furniture, however, is in good condition and comfortable.
FIRST VISIT: I had a felafel plate and a rice pudding. The food was average quality. The sauces they use are a little different than the typical sauces: the white sauce was thicker and tangier and the red sauce had a hint of heat but mostly tasted like a zestier and thinner version of ketchup (this is maybe not the most appealing way of describing it - it was good, like a cross between hot sauce and ketchup). I liked the different flavours and the rice was actually pretty good, but I was indifferent about the felafel and hummus. The felafels were like the puck-shaped ones you can buy at the grocery store. The rice pudding had a nice flavour but was almost gelatinous in consistency, which I can't decide how I feel about.
Second visit: I wanted to see if the more distinctly Persian dishes would be better, so I tried the eggplant stew, the one veg stew on the menu. The ‚Äúbroth‚Äù that the eggplant and tomato were stewed in was straight oil, which I did not like. Again the rice was great, but they give so much with the stew that I didn‚Äôt know what to do with it all.
The prices ($17 for the plate and stew w/ rice, $5 for the rice pudding) are fair for the amount of food you get, which is pretty generous. I finished the whole felafel plate but was very hungry, so if you have a smaller appetite you will have leftovers. Two people could easily split a rice pudding.
The staff seems very nice, but I just can‚Äôt see myself coming back for the food. I‚Äôd get the felafel again if it was the ONLY place to get felafel in town, but it is very much not.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNY72ngJ2ZaAwXFb3jb_xOhzFGMNLItp0KiPLjO&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-1-12"},{"Name":"Abdullah K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaOLs3U1NGAh-EH96OS0WG3dhkXXnjYtovUMs7UYINOdg16mA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my go-to place to eat on and around campus! With the limited halal options at UBC, this is a lifesaver. Good food, phenomenal portions, and fresh! If I had to suggest one thing on the menu, it would be the soltani meal. The steak is really well cooked and tender. I‚Äôm so happy Sahel opened at UBC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9Y519rm1k_jiyVqRKLtV2JmvAIaOwnipoGyUb&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2023-12-8"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Carlson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfSH3Mvx6Gquzf2h2Yz13MuXUcH81ASX8ObjzRJu92XMv3J9M3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really enjoy the decor and atmosphere of the place! The prices are not bad for a place in UBC and they have great specials on different days of the week. You can even get a can of hard iced tea for $3 on Wednesdays! The food was pretty good as well and service was quick. Definitely a cool hangout spots for students","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyTwuCZccSL-7X42Ctxdh6oCHq4iBc2RWWDEgi&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-9-17"},{"Name":"Anson Leung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLpRG7sV65M0Vk9fJln2fqg-G8cTgdbnIHe6i_26HAHg5rk2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This was the second time coming here for the all you can eat pasta.  Unfortunately, the policies have changed and a beverage and gratuity is added, very fair, since I was told that some didn't tip, so the policy changed from this week. From this visit, the sauce amount has decreased, and the pasta has gone from al dente to harder, basically raw pasta.

The first plate of pasta was almost perfectly al dente but still slightly under what I preferred, and was still a treat to enjoy.  After the first plate, I had asked if the pasta could be made softer for the next.  They said that it would not be possible since the pasta is par-cooked.  However, for the next 2 plates, the pasta got harder and harder until I tasted flour and I decided to cut into one.  Well, it was raw inside (photo included).  At this point after 2.5 plates of hard pasta, I didn't feel like asking for it to be remade since they told me before that it wasn't possible.

Overall, the food experience was marginally unacceptable after the first plate. The service was good and the sports bar atmosphere was excellent.   I recommend the rigatoni alla vodka sauce for the all access pasta since it tastes the best, pesto the second.

After the complaint, I was told there had been a miscommunication that the pasta couldn't be cooked longer, and the drink cost was taken off as a result.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMb5h3FMgcqIKIxfIJ4PYZyyEEGjALlZXy1MfK1&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Simon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWq3mMD7x0QRiQPROCB5BEqtJbykKAfvm5IFcPhyVt8QiitDIxq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I got introduced to this place by a foodie influencer  (Howie) and got to enjoy a lot of their food. This visit, however, was solo and only just on a Monday evening so it wasn't very busy inside. There is  outdoor patio seating which is was my preference.

I ordered the Steak Sandwich which came with EXCELLENTLY crisp fries and a small dipping sauce. If you ask for any kind of hot sauce, they will charge you $1.50 - SO BE CAREFUL! The Steak  Sandwich was *absolutely* delicious! The taste from the AAA medium-rare flat iron Steak with the  goat cheese and bbq sauce had such a really nice, umami flavour and mouth feel. It was just so delicious!

I also ordered a Nashville Chicken Sando. No pictures taken as the first bite literally made me devour it on the spot! Will definitely come back again to take a photo.

Overall, I had a great experience at Sports  Ilustrated Clubhouse. Nothing to say about their  interior or service.

Definitely recommend although I will say most items in the menu is quite expensive for the value. About 10-20% more expensive than what I consider reasonable price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZ_l_-O0YA_6zwiOUN1AOIRb233AEnDOfUPpUz&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Nai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIReum1hobq8yy8xS95oLeLTMWqUAVsUqS3FQjvLQXW9PrM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I‚Äôve been here twice during the day-time and the service was great both times, I came with two friends during the evening yesterday as it was their first time and we thought it would be a fun place to come to in our own neighbourhood; however, the service last night was not it! We left feeling uncomfortable. The server made it seem like we were a bother, she gave two of us the wrong bills granted we should have double checked but we couldn‚Äôt because we felt rushed‚Ä¶ the Attempt of a pleasant interaction was only when we were paying our bills and we left feeling really bad at that service! Mind you, we left at around 8pm and the restaurant was not busy. She wasn‚Äôt welcoming at all from the start. We were still all smiles though. For my friends that came there for the first time, I don‚Äôt think they appreciated last nights service. It kinda sucks cause I was happy that they could finally come there. It takes one little experience like that to throw you off! I appreciate the server the times I‚Äôve been there during the day though, she was great! Food is good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lou CB","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiUtEy3y60GPfgpVV5JSZrfFEBJi2Q16v4jzANAcFWH_TE0GBffw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We had the BLT sandwich which came with fries and a salad, and the sizzling brownie. The BLT was well seasoned with quality bacon, generous amounts of tomato and shredded lettuce and the fries were tasty and crispy. The brownie was served with a scoop of vanilla ice cream. Good solid food in a bright clean space ‚Äî ambience very different from when it was a pub, and some will miss the vibe! Still, will be back to try other items on the menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNh087caXrJbS0HKIa3aQ2-peVfgUHsyIosCQ2v&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2023-12-9"},{"Name":"Mahsa Haghjoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRSnT0Wip7Pbg6Z8m0cglGHkWd61YfkTkUIlG6b0IkPWIUcJi2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"If you are in the village you might wanna check out this place. Food was delicious, plenty of seats and you can even sit outside. Food was good","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5VsJRScu6NCdsyshKWhhH-ZIiDoIN1Y9DqH8-&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-9-26"},{"Name":"Elaine S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXw0NZVlw-DYhg6yu3CwCqawu2sEc8yv_yDRJNRZHiHpXsjuXCx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A couple of days ago I met with my BFF for a much-needed catch up. We started off at the UBC Botanical Gardens and then she suggested Sports Illustrated Clubhouse for lunch.

It was a quiet afternoon which made the atmosphere perfect for us for a wonderful visit, and the food was great. The best part was the incredible service by Emi! She was such a lovely person, so friendly, and she took such great care of us!

My friend and I shared the truffle fries (they were sooo good!) and house salad. And Emi recommended the perfect beer - my new favourite - Main Street Brewing Hula Hula Tropical Sour!

Thank you Emi - you made the visit with my bestie so special!! We will be back! XX","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkqcVOmUrER6YSL3yQW180GcblcqGtJukGWVDB&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Eugene Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvb9M5oHuuuLu9F3QxDe3Xu-5rsVsCB6BayNIPfvQOtlwnoIIv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a great place to watch a game. They have a massive screen above the bar flanked by smaller ones next to it, then more around the corner. There are also several TVs throughout other areas so there are almost no bad tables

The food was pretty good for the most part. Other than the guacamole being a bit bland and not as creamy as I‚Äôd expect (maybe they did a chunky style on purpose?), we enjoyed everything else. My Nashville Chicken Sando was awesome (normally I don‚Äôt think much of coleslaw in a sandwich but it really worked with this one). The brussel sprouts with bacon was awesome as well. My friends enjoyed their burgers and Caesar salads while their regular fries were extra crispy and tasty (it‚Äôs got some seasoning on it and isn‚Äôt just plain salted).

The drinks menu was pretty big and there are a lot of beer options.

The server was friendly and attentive despite a packed house for the Canucks/Kings game.

We‚Äôll definitely be back for more games and meals.

Sorry for the sad food photo; we were focusing on the game too much. üòÉ","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPmEGUSnxAI5BuksllsLzdLs3sDJ4ayGy7dA9vP&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-3-1"}]

While the spring rolls were a tad oily, they were still enjoyable. However, the highlight was definitely the potato BBQ stick - it was spicy and utterly amazing! Overall, it was a fantastic dining experience that I would highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matthew Nichiporuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMUo7vJRTLjS5Vph1J5OjCQjPWsKGPlNJaI4FKpAmzwqfqZMPt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Definitely one of the best places to eat on campus. My only comment is I wish the spicy options were spicier. Friendly service, good value, and the fries are fantastic.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAsRUwM1kr5fYWMaPSOwtGOGh-_MAyOOzjDYfokhHY8k5IaUlm=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food is generally tasty here but I ordered delivery that was not delivered properly (never received the order) and when Ubereats (which was fulfilling the order) told me the restaurant was responsible for a refund, I informed them of this and they disagreed and refused to refund the order. If you want to throw away money at food that does not arrive and get zero customer service then order here\n\nEDIT: they did follow up and resolve it the next few days. It ended up being a fair resolution, but it was difficult in the moment because of uber. So good experience overall from the restaurant itself","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went there for the grad students meeting and absolutely loved it! The place was packed with vibrant people which gave such an energetic atmosphere. Staff was very friendly and contributed to the experience. The beers were great and the burger I had was good enough ‚Äì not very large but also not expensive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDgBUdvc8jRuHppQfgKjuHI0zVR3S0Q2HrSskp&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Aileen Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtnbeuRSCrTtTivdNIO4OHLKHO_ilmZOOqqMZVCM5535PBeWYx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had our wedding at Koerner's Pub two weekends ago and we are beyond happy with the venue and how everything turned out! Caroline did such a great job with communication throughout the whole process and making whatever we wanted to do a reality. When we first booked, they said they're very flexible and can customize our wedding however we liked, and they really meant it! We added a signature cocktail a couple of months before the wedding and they made it happen with no hesitation. We are just blown away by how accommodating they are. We wanted a cozy, intimate, laid back wedding with the ceremony on the open patio and a cocktail style reception with canapes, platters and food stations and they more than delivered on that. The outdoor space is just beautiful surrounded by the tall trees, the atmosphere inside was absolutely perfect and the food was delicious! Our guests raved about everything! I could not recommend Koerner's Pub enough!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSpoODXsooMuueBjFMVUbAncCRWmoP1B6ORPuo&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2023-11-7"},{"Name":"Jerry J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9DQ7B_TRq3u3bo5NkgYrIEp3oIpu1Uv2owPApsfpA107EzZBD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Don‚Äôt come here for the food. They ‚Äúonly do two things, tacos and burgers, but hey do those well‚Äù according to the staff on duty - LOL ü´†

The burger patty was as thin and crispy (smashed burger) as the one tiny stripe of bacon that you get for an additional $2.50 - for me, the smashed thing is mainly a cost saving measure. No lettuce or fresh tomato, just the mushy bun and greasy undercooked fries, all served on a plastic tray (no plate) to give it the perfect canteen finish.

The person at the counter did not want to be here (bad day for them it seems). Deco and atmosphere is ok, nice garden/patio. Beer and water good.

In summary, the place called Freshii at Wesbrook and this pub battle for the bottom of the list of eating out on campus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMV5sDHilMGHK49b7Ep2ceOcuYUZ4P5cInKnkPf&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Nat D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVq59Bz_Kc8jFzJNz9bEb180ByB9AU4nY2IRQXQnfI8npN0Tz_3=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Koerner‚Äôs pub is my go to for the BEST vegan tacos in the city! ü§§üåÆ As a tasty side dish, be sure to order their yummy fries smothered in vegan mushroom gravy - truly heavenly! üòã The prices and portions are very fair as well. The staff is always super warm and welcoming, and I greatly enjoy the pub ambience as well as the large patio surrounded by the lush greenery and mature trees. On a side note, be sure to check in advance to see if the pub is open as sometimes they host special events and will close for the day. This place is truly a hidden gem!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPV3UKCC0-8HY8nb3tMBs5r1g2Yp3mZ1z7ifA-D&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2022-8-2"},{"Name":"Jess A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQcaZCQGrB5OVS66pu43CkqxqUxwzuyGP2ki5075OI4cgNK_DdiA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had our wedding ceremony and reception at Koerner's this past weekend. It was one of the best nights of our lives, in no small part to the staff at Keorner's. Ana, the venue coordinator, is on top of everything and was an invaluable resource. She responded quickly to all our communications, and went the extra mile to fulfill every request, including accomodating allergies and liasing with vendors to get the site setup just how we wanted.

The venue looked stunning - more beautiful that we could have imagined. It is an idyllic setting. It looking like our own little forest oasis! We had a night ceremony and it felt right out of a Midsummer Night's Dream.

The food was exceptional. I wish the chef had a restaurant we could eat at all the time! Our guests were comfortable and happy the whole night. The staff were attentive and fun. The beers they had on tap were awesome - even my favourite, Four Winds saison! We really can't say enough good things.

It was fun getting to know the venue - we visited a few times in the leadup, and hung out eating burgers and tacos. The vibe is great. We will be back as customers and look forward to attending one of their drag nights someday soon!

Big recommend and lots of love for this place!! <3","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsoFuH2exuiAgDyAF2BAIjMYZg0qGUDYavAiXb&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2022-8-29"},{"Name":"Nanook Bearkiller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJGd-lKZGiw3s1Cstm96X_oNJSIZl-bTkcRWm3S82g26MG6YQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Really poor service.
Went there at 12:30 pm. I had to wait for one full hour only to receive my burger. And then had to devour it without really tasting the damn food because my class was starting. This team is not good enough to be on campus. They're severely short staffed with inexperienced undergraduate students serving tables of 6 people. But with absolutely no competition around, they survive on monopoly.
I don't think I want to go there ever again. I try to change my friends' minds too if they suggest this place for any sort of gathering.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jason wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAr7OPM3u3i7bBkh0r7Q9kS7_8Gu_88Crv223BgydShD66TQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very good taco‚Äôs but the the menu is very limited.. Very crowded on the weekends.. very hip hang out for the UBC students..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMK9pm6ZuPgIIUqe-PBzrXbwWZ2KyumEdlGl06e&fid=0x0:0x7bf6312548e5f7ba"],"When":"2024-3-16"},{"Name":"Daniella Stewart","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJvrtZ9JggwDL2AwQ_WItI2VaTglWpBeElIlHroHM6ga-UoOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"**Beautiful Wedding Venue***
We recently had our wedding at Koerner's Pub and we are so happy with that decision. The location is beautiful, Loafe catering was delicious, and Marcela and her team were great.
Having our wedding at Koerner's made for an easy day with no extra travel for ourselves or our guests between the ceremony and the reception. It felt intimate in the garden ceremony with a beautiful backdrop for photos. The tables already at Koerner's provided a simple and elegant feel that didn't require a ton of decorations which made for easy planning. Multiple guests came up to share how delicious the food was (we definitely recommend the flank steak with chimichurri).
Would highly recommend considering Koerner's for your wedding!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Selina Zhou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdh_K07G_35WE1XQolPePKtbRPCS7etPd4GO37eQJrOR8PInDd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Mercante is a great place to visit, and I urge you to, especially for their pizzas. However, as great as it tastes, it is clear that over the two years I have been going there, the amount of arugula they have been adding has decreased drastically.

Maybe it is just shrinkflation, or maybe nobody likes arugula, but regardless, that is disappointing nonetheless.

Stick to the pizzas with pesto or tomato sauce, they are absolutely amazing, the ones without are quite bland.

The crust is some of the best you‚Äôll ever taste, or maybe all my years of never trying pizza this fresh ruined my tastebuds.

If I were to recommend a particular pizza, it‚Äôd definitely be the pesto pollo! It‚Äôs simple, pesto with chicken and mushrooms but it is a joy to eat.

The pizza is quite fast, cooked in around 10 minutes, and there are plenty of seating as well.

I tried the pasta once when it first came out‚Ä¶ and it was basically just reheated in a shoddy take-out container. Incredibly disappointing compared to the pizzas.

The mini caprese salad has the best sauce I‚Äôve ever eaten, so even if the price is a bit steep, worth it imo.

Anyways, please visit! And enjoy some of the pizza pictures I‚Äôve taken over the years.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8dRluJ1Y1QIiw864urKWtZC0j-aWF2bSdF9bd&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"B W (Battery)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2VcTxYkMGGx4jwVvZYc_zLzH45KC5E2wcm69COre1h2Q43jQG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The pricing for the pizzas increase further and further BUT the quality and portion size of each pizza decreases. The flavour of the pizza is decent (not justifiable for the price). Compared to in 2021 the toppings added have been less and less (You can see in the photos below, One with less arugula is recently taken)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOEaFBwrMdmz38q6u4vdNNgNito6eNO4ARACcrh&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"charles bai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVivIWOvTOamsgiucoqI5EKukhiOsZqTk7nog1iV-Y1Xav6PIczow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pizzas were ok. The dough is most as chewy as I‚Äôd like. The underside was a bit too charred for my liking. But other than that, it tastes like you would expect an Italian pizza to taste.

But what is that $7 for such a small slice of tiramisu‚Ä¶","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyDKLlV2mlf_ToQxfsaQiVcIBUIa9jTyxTTki9&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-7-9"},{"Name":"JuChul Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBl2ZXIT6h1ADZaXOEj0qdwPy-q7Gry2PxCal1RfLk4LIaRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow, a hidden treasure inside UBC~
The coffee was a bit disappointing, but the pizza was the best. Since it's not a coffee shop, it would be perfect to just have it with coke^^","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLPEGB-CaG0qEI3Tio6TacurZsxD_EtFBBO-5W&fid=0x0:0x2199ac3872d942ea"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Ryan Tsang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVH174LmUPGzeC52GF3Com64V8GOYDH3Xrkt6Q91uXjQsUYZcmm4g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"If you look at the menu someone else posted here, you can see that they have increased the price per pizza by $4 over 8 months. Edit: went back to try the prosciutto, it‚Äôs a good, honest pizza on its own.
