user_reviews: [{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Honestly one of the best and cheapest cafes there is on campus! They have a very cute vibe, cozy study space, and fantastic food for a very low price! The hot entree I got is only $5, and I can't recommend it enough especially if you are a UBC student :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNM6nTAjzjR6e5-f13vSwueAd7J6ng09sRByk2z\u0026fid=0x0:0xb2d4584a9ad4bef2"],"When":"2023-10-25"},{"Name":"Ben Rogers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtnzRv60cviP_9OuJIIU1qkuhSbqn-p2y4KUjHqNkJZr9VFSQD8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great options, fresh food, friendly and quick service. Keep in mind, the cafe is in the basement of the building, you can access it though the stairwell or by going around behind the McMillan Building (as it is on the basement level). Finally, if you get a granola bar, be sure to grab a Granola Bar Stamp Card (photo uploaded to review) from the order table, as you get a free bar after every 10 purchases.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTLMibsAACJHPWDtDAy2Vn3P9WiPxQ63rGECuy\u0026fid=0x0:0xb2d4584a9ad4bef2"],"When":"2018-2-7"},{"Name":"Andrew Scoles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLgy4xcaXZ2GwFerX4jMQpq_ZTZyUdz1A0Sd6J-ggT_uEJIkw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Such a kind cafe promoting food security in society. It‚Äôs their last day for the term but, given the prices and plant focus, would highly recommend to everyone! Only $6 for a filling and nutritious lunch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOblUStcEWiS7PptizoEO2Fh9-_BXZhG-UzV6YK\u0026fid=0x0:0xb2d4584a9ad4bef2"],"When":"2022-12-5"},{"Name":"Alex Martinez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKfW0vVWER1vwpKRRaxkfJqUTUqBoTkhNpTUXO3nnkvR2ZkPg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Singlehandedly solving the student food crisis at UBC. Great place for an affordable, tasty and healthy lunch. Lots of seating. Cheap coffee too.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kathryn W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTP7mQy2zbUfI3ccRKhyMSWMJHDY9D5LlOeHxCPxUdPzwHfmmQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everyone 'working' here is a volunteer. Everyone is kind. Any mistakes made are honest are they are all learning. But the food is REAL and freshly cooked. The prices are very, very good. And the marginal 'profit' all goes towards benefiting students and addressing food scarcity. If it's even remotely near me, this is my go to campus cafe. Just double check the hours as these volunteers gotta go to class too, so hours can be limited.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Polly Tsao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHjs6JuXkTNSpcG8ZdpNO8nji0dnfwnfgMFiUQ3MFOilMZkg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I used to be a volunteer 10 years ago! Great to see Agora Cafe still operates by an amazing team of volunteers. Love the food here - especially the granola bars \u003c3","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joti Tronson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLofHR3UL4QtQ_l7BUZVQPiwRHtrS7TbNIC4wVv2qBoljC_5w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Incredibly pleasantly surprised!!\nWe never had such a Cafe at the good old HR Macmillan Building at the turn of the century, when I was there.   I an looking forward to Thursday.  Much Love to me Agsci peeps.  üíôüçÑüçíüçÖüçúüçØüçùüíô","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_Rd83W_mG4tCSHwLVekfeOHmun3MwMZqA0BDUETRlky_WsaThjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best kept secrets on campus. Their vegan pumpkin coconut loaf is my new favourite snack when they make it(they change their baked goods everyday, and it's only a dollar). The cafe is not for profit so all the prices are really affordable. While their soups can be hit or miss, definitely try their frittatas for lunch. Most, if not all their food is vegan and organic. Also, it's only a dollar for tea, coffee, or hot chocolate if you have your own cup.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Feast
about: [{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Takeout","enabled":true},{"name":"Dine-in","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Coffee","enabled":true}]},{"id":"dining_options","name":"Dining options","options":[{"name":"Breakfast","enabled":true},{"name":"Lunch","enabled":true},{"name":"Dessert","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true}]}]
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Rowan Tetrault","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfO97gMjqDhcxLto7LhpXIwpHTc_aV_Za2PD-ik6ShIa9lAwtk0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is one of the three conventional first year dining halls on UBC campus, and it is solidly alright.

They always offer a very wide selection of food at their various different stations including different types of pizza, burgers, pasta, and spins on traditional Mexican, homestyle, and Asian cuisine. They have all of this along with quite the yogurt/salad bar assortment + desserts and drinks.

Unlimited food with so many options is definitely a benefit, but some choices can be subpar at best and I noticed readily accessible protein options (primarily meat) are not always available.

My go to "clean" options (download nutrislice to be sure, but don't expect to see nutritional facts posted publicly ANYWHERE) that also taste pretty good include the sesame chicken salad with a hard boiled egg, any of their salmon meals, or a simple yogurt bowl.

It may be difficult to eat here everyday, but sometimes there are hidden gems and the staff never disappoint. This is why they deserve an absolute minimum of 4 stars :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOp1PYN4xQ9rgNxumgQsKC0nK56EXU44ehjOiVv&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Robin Zhuo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4YJfTGesCXz1xbhn6UpYAqxjtSHa4hbLPPN34KDkRy9WuDw0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Best 1st yr dorm dining hall for sure, but the quality are not stable :‚Äô( , staffs are absolutely helpful and amazing. If u r not in meal plan pay this dining hall for 12-20$ are insane.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOg61NRqlYqOY2-UH5B9vI8ZVC7VD4Ykn4YspXU&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Alexander Hunt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKntg94WsHup3cVgJBk3yO0jaRf4K-ndL2T0xGy94s_gBQtie8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The Feast is Totem Park Residence's dinning hall. With 4-5 separate kitchens serving unique styles of food, students and guests eating here will enjoy the food.

The atmosphere here is wonderful. There are celling-to-floor windows, allowing much natural sunlight into the dinning hall. The seating can sit 200-250 people. Sitting varies from cafe tables, to Howarts style long tables or high-chair tables found in coffee shops. The food-serving area of the dinning hall is immediately at the place where you pay so you can line up to get your food. To avoid the line at the main entrance of the dinning hall, you can go to the back to pay as well.

The food here is okay. This is not a high-end restaurant. The food may not be for everyone. Also, there's a self serve ice cream machine, yogurt and salad bar. There are coffee machines and juice dispensers. There are plently of fruits, snacks and bread. At night, the pizza kitchen opens. Food is served in small to medium portion which is perfect for those who do not eat as much or want to try multple things. Chefs are polite and kind and will be willing to give you a bit of extra food if you ask.

There is no washroom in the dinning hall. You will have to leave the dinning hall and lose your ability to come back to use the washroom.

If you come here during regular meal times, expect there to be lots of students. If you come during 8:30am, 9:30 am or any time when class is in session, there are not as many people. Menu of the dinning hall can be found at both front and rear entrance. Menu can be found online as well through Nutrislice app.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWzm1_3n7h1l2H9rwoh2H89TZ0Fq1NXU3odOco&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2023-9-15"},{"Name":"Jarod Walsh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvAxeA4y5ekP9kJ4EmyOw8TsE05_KmQ9ASGN1BZSNnDc39dHRw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This buffet-style restaurant is amazing. You pay $16 and can enjoy unlimited servings of various foods, drinks, and desserts. While the food itself is just okay, it‚Äôs truly incredible considering the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4uPJeAZ6lVIORSxF5yULsp8ZpenwbVQF3Fcqh&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2023-12-7"},{"Name":"Brendan Mitchell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3Qlg33iKZu8wkzLBmt9R9RBp_9-J_M_xbmFoyCBbc0eyazMCC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is awesome!  Very reasonable price and if you like to eat alot the variety is awesome.   I can't believe a place like this exists for the price.   It is not fine dining but it is deffinatly a few steps above what you would expect for eating lunch anywhere at a university campus.  Came here with my 9 year old daughter who is a healthy eater and we both had 3 breakfasts.  She loved being able to get up and go get whatever she wanted.   Good selection of different drinks avalible Aswell.   Highly recommend. For the price, nothing beats it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMN7yTSIDM_65m4bBL6QwgHr2tRxv3ruxm0pDbJ&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2024-2-3"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place is quite amazing and the food is very healthy, you can taste the health! For only a flat rate of $15.00 for lunch, it's an all you can eat buffet which includes roasted veggies, curry, rice, Bahn Mi, tacos, fries, burgers, smoothies, juices, milk, soft drinks, coffee, tea, salads, fruits, and desserts, including frozen yogurt! Where else are you gonna find a lunch buffet for $15.00 these days and such quality healthy ingredients!!! Highly recommend it! The only reason it lost a star is that the taste of the food is just average but for the price, it's awesome.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMefaQLhCYBXkPvbE6zYnfa2QtOKPoJTciFo0p1&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2022-10-5"},{"Name":"Ahnaf Muqset Haque","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9JdQZtXBMvD618JDWqRmaMkXk-I2NhqdPuW2NLQFP33Qn87KikQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Feast is one of the first year resident dining places at the University of British Columbia. They have a bunch of variety of cuisines and have all sorts of options(vegan, vegetarian, halal, etc.) to meet your needs. The food is not so great in terms of taste and is quite expensive. Ambience is great though!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYAuVTb8ktuztAQgPbE2inlqJ4Yo-UDnubXkp8&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2019-3-28"},{"Name":"Ethem Can","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGyCt7ndLGEeKEaL2-gks_s7s8Q37Wov3ouVX3P4o--96Axg9t=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Foods are delicious and perfectly designed. Only downside is there is always crowded and you need to wait some time to get your food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYUnLzVImnmGR01tQ3elsZg4CjFNKf14pGd5Sm&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2023-9-5"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Stephen Mac","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUoPC8lYoGwhrnfIc_f4se0z42VgmocbQORloZc6SPdkmVh6n0z=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"A great spot to visit during Happy Hour, conveniently located near the UBC Bookstore. They have outdoor picnic tables, perfect for enjoying sunny days. While their morning coffee and pastries are tasty, the lunch menu and beer selection are somewhat limited. Additionally, the food options are on the pricier side, with smaller portion sizes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbT3drdK9xEv2ja7-_sP67frGGeqnQHNZyU6RE&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Chloe Rachel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgExGuK1W-XgQc1tPnrQlqQkWxCTaNhdz977uVTTY3zjpsAzs-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Subpar experience at Loafe for brunch on a Friday. The location is quite popular for students, with many tables filled by students with their laptops/books! We couldn't find an available table, so had to settle for sofas outside the caf√© (inside the alumni centre). I could barely taste the oat milk in my decaf Americano, and the blend was not very strong itself. The hot chocolate was fine. The Mushroom Ricotta Rice Bowl ($13.95) had a nice marinade on the mushrooms, and a decent amount of ricotta (on a bed of rice and arugula). The rice is very plain, and perhaps a little mushy/overcooked.

I was disappointed with their Midnight in Havana Rice Bowl ($15), having asked for no arugula, and it coming with the bowl anyways. The place was packed so I didn't feel like asking them to remove it. The pork shoulder was not tender (it was more like dry pulled pork). They were able to use a balsamic dressing instead of their garlic aioli at my request, which was nice of them to accommodate. There are some inconsistencies with their in-store menu and what's online on their Square site, as the Square site says the bowl comes with caramelized onions, but in-store it's pickled onions. On top of the pickled jalapenos, I thought it was too much acidity toppings wise and would have benefited from the caramelized type. Self-service after you receive your order. Would be interested in trying their baked goods (which are unlabelled in their display case), but would skip the bowls.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiE8GLojK31GVv4M8k9y-jJfyWRKUikLidQ0ZW&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Roman Kozak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXaei_E5eRgQInxhzdn1QSNV_at7npoBUF_sdv7jvDoiE-7SM2Uw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"High quality food and pastries. Excellent coffee. Lots of indoor and outdoor seating but gets busy so hard to find seating.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEq_0tU5sB0MEcKHfk2ujiVdIA1tltgD1iAZz-&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Soefae Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWO7ZNgUf5Dwk1W_QTwOUDH5IE-lT_O8VF-ftw5oM5hbRZ-8oOz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried this place after two separate friends recommended it to me. It was quite crowded and busy, but the wait for food wasn‚Äôt too bad. I loved the toast ‚Äî creamy and crunchy ‚Äî and the portion was great too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4E03kf6fYhGFCf_COAC14gCZPFHbjW4gjYUbj&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2024-2-16"},{"Name":"Sartaj Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1doLfhIpPIdYO53EoD_63mHYE3jrQc1kxM-CAvFcju93a6Z1xPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pretty great spot to grab a coffee or a bite! Great place to study too if you‚Äôre a student. Can work out to be a bit pricey for certain items but the quality is great! Service is good too but not as friendly as most places on campus. Pictured is a chocolate croissant and the Havana ‚Äúsandwich‚Äù which is really a pulled pork burger but is not advertised as such (tasted great was just surprised by what I was served compared to the order).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPlziy98Efwm1emaGHuaminWA-fhktmoVLuvY71&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2021-2-20"},{"Name":"Bahar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUU5aKs1eICwt862xHyk6eML8Nhxgoc_vXAN8CVDAAXDoHVGQ78=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I recently visited Loafe Cafe and had a mixed experience. The Huli Huli chicken sandwich was disappointing‚Äîcompletely tasteless and definitely overpriced for what it was. On the bright side, the Earl Grey tea latte was excellent‚Äîperfectly made and one of the best I‚Äôve had in a while.

However, what really stood out was the service. Despite ordering food, we were politely asked to leave to free up some seats for other customers. While I appreciate the politeness, it was frustrating considering we were paying customers.

Overall, Loafe Cafe has potential, but they need to improve on the food quality and customer experience to justify the prices.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chels","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIEG8ImuHXjQ-hpfgYhplAhH9cls8PSmkmT9KPxEmPx9DwGMw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered smashed avo toast for breakfast but it was so cold as a toast. It costs almost 12 dollars.

I feel so unhappy and it is pricey as such a toast. I won‚Äôt come here again for any sandwiches.

The server said the kitchen staff didn‚Äôt work this morning.

The food is so bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxOhRzHWMZG6JrD4sH-xnGaPJ51NdAA0A_CanW&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2023-9-17"},{"Name":"Josh Adams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSvEV1wbWNmITPLILC0Yrj8KqIzEYTYtwHybPjIq7PlceuYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I used to be a regular customer at the Sauder location, however once I found out my favourite Barista ‚ÄúTom‚Äù had left I was quite upset (still great staff at Sauder, just different ya kno).
However I was walking past the Alumni Center Location and saw a familiar face smiling behind the counter, lo and behold, it was Tom! He is now the manager at the Alumni Center location and I have never been happier.
Hearing his kind voice say ‚Äúhow‚Äôs it going Josh? You want the usual?‚Äù was music to my ears. He even recommended his personal favourite ‚Äúchicken avocado rice bowl‚Äù and it was amazing. I‚Äôll definitely be returning to this Loafe cafe and am excited to see what changes Tom brings to the cafe.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyG6LpRVr068PHL6LI0b4McMll6dKr_xChK8fl&fid=0x0:0x6d561b0ad6a3f6f7"],"When":"2024-6-14"}]

[{"Name":"Rowan Tetrault","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfO97gMjqDhcxLto7LhpXIwpHTc_aV_Za2PD-ik6ShIa9lAwtk0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Unless you live in Place Vanier, it may seem inconvenient to come all the way to Gather for food, but when their best options are available it is 100% worth it.

One thing I noticed about the 3 UBC dining halls is that they try their best to be high quality, so when it took 5 minutes for my ordered poke bowl to be made I knew that it would be good. The fish tasted fresh and the bowl was stuffed with kimchi, edamame, and other goodies that I did not expect them to include.

Just because of this experience and the other high quality options Gather frequently has (including their solid shawarma and gyro wraps and vegan brownies) I seriously believe this could be the best first year dining hall on campus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPMwUMSywIfBT8IVruFiiEXEKlWcFg9eiskGds&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Hugh Gao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFlJmYlj82sx6sLKOje56IkZUG693ZnITvHtJUekoopvQlVKt9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"There‚Äôs a station here at Gather called ‚ÄúSimply Local‚Äù that makes some outstanding dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9pJkT3-BNBojmCwdrk9PX3Gn5zU2s_WhpLb6-&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Alexander Hunt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKntg94WsHup3cVgJBk3yO0jaRf4K-ndL2T0xGy94s_gBQtie8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Place Vanier's Gathering Student Residence Dinning Hall is one of the three dining halls available on the UBC campus. It is the farthest dining hall compared to the other two.

After entering the building, you will have to take a flight of stairs to get to the dining hall. The food available at Place Vanier comes from a variety of different cultures. Everyone will find something good to eat the dining hall. The dining hall can sit 200-300 people. It is a buffet style dining hall and you can get as much food you can eat.

There is a salad bar and custom sandwich making station. There is a  burgers, tacos, pork bun and pork belly ramen station. Food changes from time to time. It is best to check Nutrislice, the online menu app, to see what food the dining hall is serving before paying. The dining hall building has big windows overlooking the court yard of Place Vanier. You also have different kinds of seats like the Caf√© style seats and also the long dining hall tables.

During regular hours like mornings from 8-9am, lunch from 12-1pm, and dinner from 7-9pm, you will find lots of people there. You can avoid the traffic by avoiding these common times or arriving earlier to skip the potential line-up for food.

The presentation of the dish is average. The portions are small. Food is placed on the counter which may get cold and unclean. Food quality tastes ok, but the servers are more concerned about getting as much food out to as many students and people as possible. During peak hours, the place becomes hectic.  Food also is warm, not hot after peak times. Staff there are friendly and kind.

Washrooms are downstairs, separate from the dining hall.

Parking is very close to the dining hall about a 5 minute walk. Near this dining hall, there are lots of nice trees to look at.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkJTXAZhQtPzHpRvjlF4cdHyFgKSktppk9ET2t&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2024-2-23"},{"Name":"Ra√∫l de Le√≥n","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXR1w_Ji0Yz-Xp82r5o46luBx2_3UdjKeiMHOkVr4mcBNjLxloC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I don't know why people give bad reviews, this place is amazing. Food is tasty, service is good, great choice of dishes, and for the quantity of food you can eat it's worth. I come here very often.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSUe-AzPEDj9K7keJtauLlc84KoBtXeRrR1lB2&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2023-9-30"},{"Name":"Michelle Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrZc4FOCz7AcGuorZE4SGdMyBNzLpAyMERBSqnXndHoxWZ5T_e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I really like the food here except for being repetitive.
I love Fresh Fare the most but they don‚Äôt change menu as often. I Iove the overnight oats, avocado toast and fajita bowl. A really good vegetarian station. Smoothie is my go to! Love the one with yoghurt, blueberries, chia seed, etc. Soup is pretty good too! They rotate all the time but I like their chicken soup, vegetables and legume curry, whatever bean soup, etc.

Gather has too much hate haha. It‚Äôs actually one of the healthiest and cheapest residence food among all the three.

I wish they have more cooked green vegetables. They always have potatoes and squash but they don‚Äôt have enough broccoli, spinach, green beans, etc.

Grill station is pretty good and they change menu around 2-4 weeks. Salmon burger is decent. I wish their chicken burger is cheaper.

Latino is also my favourite. The Havana bowl is pretty good but sometimes they don‚Äôt season the chicken or tofu enough.

Home cooking is also one of my favourite because they rotate the food daily. They have similar food every week. The vegetable lasagna with garlic bread is so good! Not a lot of cheese and love the sauce. Butter chicken is not really good imo.

Sandwich station is alright except they don‚Äôt have the press!!! Please we def need the press for sandwich especially for those who order with cheese.

Simply local is a lot of people‚Äôs favourite. Not too expensive unless you get a main with two sides (around 12-14?). They serve beef brisket, pork chop, chicken breast, salmon and a vegetarian day every week.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMSCT6VsYqtYkDRF-j31F88f1xfA6I9Q7h3tsB&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2021-10-16"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"They offer a great variety of food, including Latino, vegan, burgers, sushi-inspired, world (rotates often), baked goods, salads, and soups. Everything is fresh and there are some interesting things to try. Portions are usually pretty filling for me. As with other UBC dining halls/markets, prices run a little high. Also it's hard to find a time that every station is open - stations will often close unexpectedly for the day or even for a few hours during the day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMqfjc_HqIif1hZmIstsralupMRNW7XFrdevVyw&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2018-12-4"},{"Name":"Luke Kuro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYgP_ll8ede6rokqjyo-gOuHJnPxjys9UFzHU35KFVwvMyuKs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Buffet, lunch for $16 per person
Best dine-in place in UBC with fair price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHAKj0GGdoJ6QYLEWd48pKfqiCkWAB268qMjiK&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2024-3-12"},{"Name":"Neil Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLwJoC3pQnZZnUx7vr-pCC8C_c6dpXLIiL2qDjojVFRSBIWWg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Only carbohydrates and fats, not much protein consistency. Desserts are good if you like sweets. Pic of cheese bagel attached!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTgtbx3C5QnopesabURqL1khnsdnXVg1nJAG3d&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2023-11-1"}]

[{"Name":"Alex Zhang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhM8_i0FgjcMWn1pe2iCTPCulYiJ6ZdM-BxEPPrbNCZswmBhAC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We got the 12.99 specials that come with the free strawberry tea. Food was good but portion sizes were amazing - way more than what we would expect for the price point. Would come back again, please don't come when I'm here though because I don't want to wait in like to get in.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwGUffMCid9mYoOZnoUamdNb5OEGSphWqcE3J4&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Grace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpyR6lW9JHiyXGuG73lo5A19PTb1WXFzVLCnrO84Gv3hfeDE5c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A new restaurant on campus serving Japanese and Chinese cuisine! I got the corn croquette set for $12.99, with a small bowl of udon added on for $3.50. The set came with a melon smoothie. The corn croquette was delicious, crispy on the outside and creamy on the inside. It came with curry sauce and katsu sauce. It also came with a big portion of rice (the rice was well-made, which was a relief since I‚Äôve had mushy rice at other restaurants before). The miso soup was salty, but paired perfectly with the rice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP24-dj3EKzX1h2q3vosOg1MLmiGK8BW9sRxAVJ&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Madeline Kam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpk6Vux-KZ276SHSgtsoa9YbbByLpXdFWBO-biQ8KXP9MZVJYZxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The staff and atmosphere were great, but the food was a bit bland. I ordered the combo which included miso soup and drink of the day and I believe it was 10.99 which is a pretty good price. However, the food did not have much flavor and included scarce amounts of protein (in this case chicken). The drink was a winter melon slushy which was a bit icy and crunchy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0eJ6zfyWxK9NGBkvDlyPP7AyjsetQVWVPollW&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Anouk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX030nN0Ds_sauo0gxWlayfH_7n_wMK-lQfODkscyR8xTr0EynOFg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Place is bright and clean. We both ordered the Shanghai thick noodles and the dishes took 25 min to arrive. Taste was unbelievably mediocre and the soup was too sour - neither of us finished. The opening deals on the menu are affordable though, especially for UBC, and maybe they taste better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWiirhGWCywKk_4pWuAI7dmTssCBUA1V0fb4Cd&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-7-9"},{"Name":"Isabelle lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKeqOC4yQmaYwP6NpsFegJJEZXL9yVwbsvUjxB7-j-CAgqz2g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service - all the servers were super attentive and even the store manager was helping with clearing, wiping down tables and serving food.

Food is decent, generous portions and very reasonable price. You won‚Äôt find anything cheaper than this these days.

I got the 3 fried prawns, 2 fried scallops,  2 pieces of fried yam + bowl of rice and miso soup for $14 only.

Highly recommend this place. Give it a try (:","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNz-ZmsmRszrSY1eFYJM1K72lNbvdcZnF6Ubyzo&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"Sophia H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJj7J89gHLVylfj7eNtEAHc3P50FouTDBLmVYxgTpUzNqmzNA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came here today for lunch with one of my friends and were pleasantly surprised by Beyond BBQ!! We both got the pork loin katsu ($17) and they had a special on where if you get any katsu you also get a free drink, so I got a supreme mango tea and my friend got the passion fruit tea. Everything was so delicious, and they gave us a TON of food for the price!!! The pork had an amazingly crispy breading and was flavourful without being dry, the miso soup came out hot (which I was very impressed by), and there was the perfect amount of rice. The sauces were good also and added a delicious pop of flavour!! Not to mention that the fruit tea was so flavourful and fresh!! The staff and servers were also lovely and did an incredible job, especially with giving recommendations. I would definitely come back!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4_goCkK_8lX1VMTr-7haXCj-Lb_pjZnBWZzOc&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Justina He","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJX5XpjJlDr-QcyrWD78qxzdGiJ3dWfMQkYELeI3EDDwTRmpES=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is an affordable new restaurant on campus that people should NOT go to. They serve horrible versions of Asian cuisine that not only are insults to the original recipes but are disgusting. Ordered a class mung bean noodle dish that took half an hour to be served despite being a COLD dish but what is supposed to be salty and spicy noodles in a sesame paste was grossly sweet and soggy with random vegetables. Friends got the croquette and udon dishes that had undercooked rice and just a pile of raw cabbage as a "salad", stale kimchi and noodles with no flavour.
TLDR: DO NOT be fooled by the cheap deals because they are too good to be true and you can get much better food for a similar price. Service was mid at best, with food taking too long to be served but the food itself was disgusting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzVrAc1rEc5JYNxc7W5m9l-YXkA8S25-YuqHcQ&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Big portion size, pretty tasty and great customer service! The food came pretty fast given that this is deep fried food. I liked the unlimited salad and rice servings! I wish the sauce was bigger in portion size too to dip the katsu in. Overall, the price seems reasonable for the portion size and taste that you receive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOz5ZRWgqek5cZ591Gbo4WglK7khxYCB4szBSK&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-5-22"}]

[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of the better cafes at UBC for quality. Service can be a little slow and people camp here to study, so it‚Äôs pretty difficult to get a table inside during late morning-mid afternoon on weekdays (the patio is easier and quieter when weather permits). On the weekends, though, it‚Äôs very quiet.
Food and drink are generally good, especially sandwiches. The kimchi grilled cheese and avocado toast are my favourites. They have lots of vegan and gluten free baked goods, though these are sometimes dry or underbaked. The matcha latte is a little weak.
I would definitely recommend this Loafe over the chains or UBC-owned cafes. It‚Äôs comparable in overall quality to other independent shops on campus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAprulsuk_dAkmTTBr7HCi3HBB1DpdgdWrlVgw&fid=0x0:0x94d026007847cea1"],"When":"2023-2-27"},{"Name":"Naheed G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKCMr_R2sPkvHyPnPR1A8YtFfOj7NFXUnGWqEdJIzLrWna4ufVnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Avocado toast was the 3rd option I chose - the 1st two items weren't available. For $12, i got one piece of bread. Not impressed when I leave a place hungry hungrier than when I arrived.  Feed.Your.Students.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEoDcmfLpSqp56JQ-zl-JnExBA2Ze8EsfC13Hm&fid=0x0:0x94d026007847cea1"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Ben Wells","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-91uU5BSvZ5NPIXZC1dHenwZQufEwUCi4pg29RVkdAJ-ALjIM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I don't understand why this place has a 4+ star rating. Every time I stop here for something I'm disappointed by some aspect of the experience. Consider:
**Value**
- For a $6 oat milk flat white, they use the cheap 2L earth's own oat milk, not delicious Barista oat milk as at most premium cafes (eg Great Dane coffee), resulting in a watery, bad tasting flat white or latte.
- On an $11 breakfast sandwich, there is only 1/2 an egg!!! Or the $11 avocado toast has like 3 tbsp of avocado on it and a teaspoon of feta. Their aggressive control of ingredient portions makes the prices totally unreasonable.
- The $5 treats like brownies, lemon bars etc are made en masse and frozen, and kept too many days in a row: they taste like fridge and have poor texture. Absolutely not worth it. (the spinach and feta croissant is a bit more reliable)
**Service**
- Every single time I find myself wondering how the service is so slow. They don't train the team to be attentive to orders or to move with pace. On my last order, the kitchen person was picking mint leaves off of stems very slowly and chatting to the barista. They ignored or did not notice when the food order came out of the printer right by their face, and took a full 5 mins to start making the order. Once they did, they became distracted: I could hear the oven beeping after toasting the bun for a full min after it was finished before someone else picked up the task. Note, the cafe was NOT busy at this time. Just inefficient. Slowness is a theme every time I order from there.
**Atmosphere**
This part is fine! Nice that they have the patio space.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A great place for a quick bite during classes! They have really good sandwiches, though I am not too huge on their drinks. But they do have a decent price for their portions and taste. I highly recommend their bacon and cheese sandwich :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZFVf-F0nOX9IKuvrT3YxrP0bXoHXvfLP0xWvC&fid=0x0:0x94d026007847cea1"],"When":"2023-10-4"},{"Name":"M D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgYfqGJ25uGc8cn5Foi08q73KwDbqZaEL9gTHw5c043KXpcnID=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The drinks are quite terrible. Bad enough to write a review so that should say something. The atmosphere is the only thing that really saves it. Overall just go somewhere else to spend $8 on a latte","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Allison Chao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI1_VXjvqeFRnOuPZPqR4all6wEIKzVuAp-eQ-1290s2ubS2w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I ordered a matcha latte with oat milk, however, they made it with regular milk instead. Matcha flavour wasn‚Äôt really strong either so kinda disappointing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marvin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIOUB9fqPRyAnJAGsLqhyOV_Bp81x_bJC8wIyyATYNP2vGJzmc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Busy and wasn‚Äôt able to get a seat, got the garlic chicken sandwich and it was pretty good, however more on the expensive side for the portion. Would try some of the other items on the menu. Overall alright.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Josh Adams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSvEV1wbWNmITPLILC0Yrj8KqIzEYTYtwHybPjIq7PlceuYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went to this Loafe cafe instead of my usual Tim Hortons, and oh boy, I‚Äôm never going to Timmie‚Äôs again. The Turkey Club sandwich was SOOO good, the coffee was tasty and the guy who served me (Tom I think) was a ray of sunshine on a cloudy morning. His smile felt genuine and warm, not like the faked smile I usually get at Timmie‚Äôs. 10/10 service, 10/10 sandwich and I‚Äôll definitely be going back.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It‚Äôs a convenient place if you are near IKB. I‚Äôve found that the early morning staff is super sweet but the attitude of the afternoon staff is a toss-up. The convenience is the main draw. They have Upmeals entrees and UBC-issue bake goods. The Upmeals stuff is healthy and easy on the palate but interesting. In the past I‚Äôve found that even some of the fresh baked goods somehow came out tasting stale, but this year‚Äôs iteration of UBC baking seems better. They‚Äôve also instituted a Pearl Fever ‚Äúpop-up‚Äù where you can get a limited selection bubble tea here (which is good, although I‚Äôve only tried the jelly, which is harder to mess up than pearls) and also ice cream with taiyaki (the waffle is good, the soft serve is just okay - little icy - but it‚Äôs an accessible way to experience a fun dessert that‚Äôs a little hard to find).
My experience with the espresso drinks is - and I only drink decaf, so this may or may not be representative - it‚Äôs not awful, but it does taste a little over-roasted. Sometimes adding milk can mellow out bitter coffee but this one basically tastes the same in americano or latte form. The chai is not offensive but is made from a concentrate that‚Äôs very sweet and the London fog is also very sweet. Be careful because the hot drinks come out intensely hot. If you just need a coffee or tea, this will do the job, but definitely go somewhere else if you‚Äôre a coffee snob.
At peak studying hours, it‚Äôs crowded, but at off hours, the clean, quiet environment is very relaxing.
Good place for students/UBC-people if you want a break from heavy food or fast food, not the place I‚Äôd necessarily recommend to campus visitors.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCIoyH-0sdLvK7eGkdXRaADKQuUnvNnYAN71NY&fid=0x0:0x38c96d30bcb01b2f"],"When":"2023-8-29"},{"Name":"Oakley Nance","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwVuB38LSpIWv_yGP7nRej-Jw5m59HC-jukdf9PfQxIccZsQIsjA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was the only person in line, i ordered and had to clarify my friends drink order, the bubble was literally typing as I was ordering and the lady asked if the drink was iced or hot. I was like "One sec she's just clarifying through the text," and she audibly sighed and walked away. All throughout this order I said numerous times that I needed oat milk in the drink and she never verbally responded so I repeated "yes with oat milk" every time she went over the order and she rolled her eyes at me so I figured she heard and was annoyed I was repeating myself. As I see her make it she uses regular milk so I interjected and said " Oh shoot that was supposed to have oat milk," and she was upset with me and said she didn't hear me. I was just shocked by how rude she was.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Clara Sui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDpfMVOFlSfYJkiY3GBxSPXynTXF_RcCUHA_sqSaVyj6n4b46n=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Love the baked goods but would love to see the hot pasta entrees back! Also the soups! - I‚Äôve noticed a huge drop in quality since 2019. Every order is mostly just spices, salt, water, and starch. There are very little toppings and the texture is incredibly runny, especially for the split pea and ham soup. Would never recommend them. Sandwiches and salads are okay but on the bland side.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jenny Tao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXl7qwNZdMK5UNeVm4Ss-BcTIDEv1k4P2sX-wHjGHKDHLJN9-0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Compared with the other cafes (not residence cafeterias) on campus, Ike's has a better selection of hot entrees and overall food. I love their pasta feature and now they have this huge chicken leg/breast for $8. Hot entrees always comes with side salads too. Not a huge fan of their drinks though. Service is speedy. My favorite cafe on campus :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lucy T.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKgUI8Y67OZjnaU2GTvCShItivsl_UV40o2V1eXoQZn3MU36Iw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Sometimes I would come by this cafe if I hadn't decided where to have a light lunch. I tried their beef wrap, mac& cheese, salads, and a few drinks. They're all at an average level. During summer season when there were few students, their soup seemed to be reheated for many times, not fresh at all. Once I wanted to get hot water from their dispenser, the staff member gave me an unfriendly look and behaved rudely. If you study in the IKB, and don't want to go far for food, it's a convenient spot. But do not have high expectation; it's just an ordinary cafe with standard campus food and it-depends-on-who-serves-you service quality.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nicole","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDjZJdREKI7_BD8K9KUQFoFVw5xhXpFyRgJEI-_J1YSIYrGDdt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Most of the staff here are friendly and I like the baked goods and salads. I've been picking up my morning coffee here as of late because the line usually moves quickly, but this morning I was charged $7.30 for a medium coffee. I went back to talk to a server (a different one from the one that charged me) and while they expressed concern by asking who had served me, the woman that served me didn't so much as apologize. I used to be a barista and I know that early morning shifts can throw you off sometimes, but I think that was quite rude. I wasn't offered a refund, but the other server told me that I can take some baked goods to even out the cost.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Z.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQPWk1igWiScMJLvbEfOGbn_E-SvYzWdnJ-_3R9XXD4Q9XGO0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Not gonna lie, a not-so-big, leftover, expires-in-a-day breakfast wrap and a small dessert for $10 doesn't sound very good. I wouldn't say anything special about taste either. I was too lazy to buy food elsewhere while I was at IKB, and so this was the best I got. I'll spare this review from the one star because I think I picked the wrong foods. After all, this is a coffee place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Meghan K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUfBN1bKKzFYujQ7qqMJ4sRqtV75B4nnaJOolJ96kg6M8dnXzkfdQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The worst. Please go somewhere else. Coffee tastes like cardboard, REALLY overpriced mediocre food, chicken is all fat and gristle, pasta tastes like hard crunchy paper. Your money is worth way more than what they are charging you- yes it's convenient, but it's so bad. Staff are also RUDE.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tried their cinnamon bun and it was surprisingly delicious in taste and texture. Reheated it at home and it was extra tasty. Lots of cinnamon flavour but also not too dense and heavy. It‚Äôs an above average cinnamon bun.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcTrXmy2mk7KggpQXy6Kc5QBBMvTE6uOJYeztz&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2024-9-15"},{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I‚Äôm told Blue Chip is known for its cookies: their chunky chocolate chip cookie is quite decadent and unhealthy (as all good cookies are).

The egg sandwich makes it clear why they‚Äôre not known for their sandwiches. To be fair, the multigrain bread is pretty great, and you really better like bread if you order their sandwiches because it‚Äôs pretty much all bread: there‚Äôs a thin layer of filling inside as if just to flavour the bread. Sandwich places are not so often pitiful: the egg salad itself, I do a way better one at home; I swear this had to be store bought in bulk.  $7++. No wonder people pack lunches here.

Service is certainly fine: you line up and place your order like any other quick-service caf√©, and they did toast it nicely (on one side) for me.

Overall, as a student organization operated outfit, you'd think they would try to offer better value for revenue-less students.

Note that Blue Chip has moved from their small location (in the same building, by the side) to the airy south end of the Nest. Lots of seating everywhere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzLTMm7Za2T10ggJ62fHI4Rw32gE5i5Q3UFuVI&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2024-7-26"},{"Name":"Lancelot Xu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUU7AtUL5RSbEqhx7nxJ8l31yO7iHUO4yb3ZiKg_LXM4h2NF1s=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Blue Chip Cafe is a gem! The food is always fresh, delicious, and beautifully presented. Their menu has a great variety, and every dish I‚Äôve tried has been flavorful and satisfying. The atmosphere is cozy, and the staff are friendly and welcoming. Highly recommend for a quality meal and coffee!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0SGKwzYKBmMXlDRjkyIbr59KLBWS4m0ujDRsP&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2024-11-14"},{"Name":"Alex Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpCadF-dmx5XTlgh_E5TB__7n649M3gDsKp0UgTsGtzt1oywZE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Solid bagels and pastries, matcha is decent too. Great atmosphere with plenty of seating overlooking the ground floor. A little pricey for food after factoring the single use containers fees.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4xZLMQjg1UFWQF2VZHZx0apLyoKKoM6O1eEWF&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2024-7-5"},{"Name":"Kayla Mizuki","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcEGcj5JPeyIAIQJw3qGO8j1u7XbI927-7frVyMbwPWPc2pbjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a UBC student, I can‚Äôt emphasize enough how I enjoy this bagel every single day for school. These bagels are unbelievably soft and undoubtedly the most delicious treats I‚Äôve ever tasted, almost like savory bagel cakes. My top recommendation is the rosemary bagel with butter; it‚Äôs under $3 and easily my favorite bagel in the city. It‚Äôs bittersweet to be done with school for the year, knowing I won‚Äôt get to savor this daily delight anymore.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOekSWPTjiTB-hlKTDXA7-GvWCVwJVJMEKLM6hx&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2024-5-1"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Known for their freshly baked cookies, it‚Äôs also a pretty good all-around cafe, although quality is a mixed bag ranging from okay to great depending on what you order. The great: most cookies, bagels and bagel sandwiches, date square, butter mochi, muffins and loaves. The okay: pre-made sandwiches and wraps, sugar cookies and vegan cookie, dessert bars besides the date square, and tiramisu. The coffee is more variable but generally pretty good, and I think the matcha latte is actually one of the best on campus (or at least the smoothest). Do not order an iced London fog/turmeric fog though - they tell you they can make it, but you will get a cold tea bag in watery milk, not a properly steeped iced tea latte.
The students who work there are usually pretty friendly and the speed of service is reasonable even though the line gets long at lunchtime when school is in session. Like other AMS-owned outlets, you can not only bring your own drink cup but also bring your own food containers and save $.25 per item.
They recently moved across the Nest to a bigger space with more seating. With the move, they now offer for-here mugs for hot drinks, but you have to be kind of aggressive if you want one - you have to say you want your drink for here, in a mug, and probably repeat yourself, otherwise they will probably ignore you, I guess because they‚Äôre not expecting it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqKjJmYV6mZmMyuj4wO5b6DaK9WwoWHXvk-COc&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2023-7-24"},{"Name":"Bekah French","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJiYLh-7emQ9AthzE2N_CGxwmtRUdZguPeMRuVIWmhyOtllxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Visited new location on Saturday (on opposite side of building to where they were before). Ordered Turkey and Brie, without the Brie. Very yummy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmZNOxehejwf2wBMhNJWaXcSR-jtZKucO-MKCI&fid=0x0:0x5acb5f931df758b7"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Rhofa Mae Realista","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLDRtU7fV1AfY8do5JUFssXSrDFilnJOloJt5l_LixJpPuW-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This cafe makes one of the best iced matcha lattes! The place is REALLY busy (I usually go here during lunch so ofc it‚Äôll be busy), but the line moves quite quickly. The staff are full of smiles despite working nonstop to accommodate customers. Took around 10 minutes for me to receive my drink, but it‚Äôs all good since it‚Äôs busy. They also have tables in front and around so you can study or chill after.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Beatrice Sebastian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUUwek93RSRQI7WTfEuNcqVL7HGmZluvzKeumWSk0H6j-wxN_r7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So many options and all of them good! I had the spicy veggie and avocado frittata, while my partner had the one with sausages in it! Packed with lots of flavour, and spicy enough where it‚Äôs not overpowering, but there is still a kick. We also had the chai latte and the Thai milk tea, the latter being my choice. The prices are very reasonable as well, and I left with extra","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMrV7r33OaiAb880nhUGDColmaJCXMDk_5rTOI&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Felipe Nardini Semedo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURszN0SB5gfUgG15JRA2VZnMKg9saOc8VB56_o8u8YD-YjWkyM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The place is very nice that is for sure, and the food was pretty good. The employees were kind and friendly. Though, it is quite expensive. Paid 15 dollars for this:","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUve_LEC5JMNxUojeXyKD3s4aLHWVChffsvrbP&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Rebecca Crean","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJffXx9jAHNGss4kYu6c34jLTh2TEgTCsOy2Ri5WTEPdAkIcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can not recommend this restaurant enough. Staff are always so welcoming and friendly. My personal favorite from the menu is the spicy egg ciabatta with bacon and avocado, with hasbrowns. It has to be the best lunch spot in UBC for sure!! Also, I have tried many of their Indian dishes, and they are so tasty and authentic. Butter chicken is amazing!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMR-lz9EE8USNUNZ7pDTmoKSZKRdbDkLAxGw5xW&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Ethaniel Chou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfW0x1CC0hsJlAWDv_pkaw3wzcOBSIvaLMpmRqZz5EHutkyWNl=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went in a few minutes AFTER closing without realizing that they were closed. They were so kind and offered to make eggs Benedict for me anyways, even though it was after closing time! The food was delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjgRxG3YdMn_U7cN7A3ThxuqiOpgxyGanjrio1&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We ordered two sandwiches. The turkey melt was nicely filled with turkey hams, cheese, and tomatoes, and it wasn't skimpy at all. For the pesto chicken and cheese sandwich, we chose the spicy version, but it was too spicy for our tastes, and not in a pleasant way. They serve frozen fries, which were unremarkable, so I might skip those next time. The portions were good for the price. Overall, we enjoyed our meal and plan to try other items in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjuWCCjG3bKAaRvShSvmkeAFyJhhm5ItRN4pFj&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Suha Khan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocINzwRxo4T3JStfrT3enCk3zn4WB4wfUp-_mi52cxtbb_WFgNA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really enjoy this small cafe along my campus quite a bit! The food is so authentic and quite flavourful. I‚Äôm from Mumbai so the Indian menu here definitely reminds me of home and the environment itself is absolutely friendly! The owner, Mr. Arwan is such a nice person, and he always greets me and asks me about my day and if the food was to my liking. If you‚Äôre looking for a unique, yet quiet place, this is definitely it! The food comes under 5 minutes to your table, and the amount is impressive. Worth every penny!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Zaayer Nasib","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkh0fpj6mvCROx8j1Ux0TdNtszR1GgFfGTRvlt6JMDCheOJwvK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Ratings Scale 0 - 10
Variety: 8
Service or Product: 7
Customer Service: 6
Environment: 6
Cleaning: 6
Washroom: 6
Cost: 4

While the food itself was decent, 2 factors made me give this page a 2 star rating:

Price: its too expensive! For a simple 2 person breakfast with tea, it cost us $42!!

Service: The service from the waitress and counter person were fine but another rude guy ruined the experience. I simply wanted to know ingredients of the cheese they use for my dietary restrictions. Instead of listening to me properly and guiding me he said he doesn't know. I asked if I could see the packaging and he said he threw the packaging out and then proceeded to leave without listening further. Pathetic. Will never visit again even though the food was decent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMq2SIcp5YKM2nN8KcchNCIq7FwbYOyHNtJ3iQV&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2019-3-12"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Five years living at UBC and I have been sleeping on this place. Finally stopped in to try their Indian food for lunch and was very pleasantly surprised. I had the Kadhi Onion Pakora Chawal and it was so good. Nothing too fancy, but just excellent Indian comfort food. I‚Äôm not in a place to say whether Indian food is ‚Äúauthentic‚Äù or not, but this was not the relatively bland take on Indian food that you might expect from this unassuming brunch place, it was pleasantly rich. And the paratha was so soft and flaky! The portion was also very filling, so good value for your money. I like that the Indian section of the menu has so many (vegetarian) breakfast dishes that most Indian lunch/dinner restaurants don‚Äôt serve. I‚Äôm kind of curious about the Western brunch menu too, but will definitely be back to try more of the Indian food if nothing else.
I had a Pi√±a Colada smoothie too. It wasn‚Äôt bad, but it didn‚Äôt really do anything for me. They called this a ‚Äúfruit smoothie‚Äù but it was so sweet and tasted closer to a flavoured slush to me. I'd skip the smoothie next time since the main meal was enough.
The atmosphere is totally bare-bones, it‚Äôs not sketchy or anything, there‚Äôs just absolutely no ambiance to speak of. The staff was nice enough though, especially the person taking orders at the front. It‚Äôs not a hip brunch place at all, but a great place for some no-fuss good eats. Although I can‚Äôt speak for the Western brunch stuff, I can definitely recommend you check them out for the Indian dishes if you live around UBC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOGkL616_ijo3iJGYtqCaMmv43q99ohyD-11woA&fid=0x0:0x235021b24bb8028f"],"When":"2022-9-11"}]

The coffee is the same price as you‚Äôll pay at any of the independent shops on campus but not quite as good, but definitely acceptable. The staff is usually nice. Basically impossible to find a seat inside around lunch time since people in the Buchanan just treat the caf√© area like any other study spot and camp there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDdLJPzUn7n24eMJB87t5qtL3U-BSyWyk6XbMK\u0026fid=0x0:0x4584be10efa073b2"],"When":"2022-7-2"},{"Name":"Navdeep Kundi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLR37nz--ycJy074sdUBv3DZUyxW4jzWvoXQP2HkN2_OCdDWA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good cafe in ubc with ample seating space .  food is good include some vegan options too","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Will Messcu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ0HMR67KoEZTEUofCAlE7qBksri5vMDUXCzBZdKkJUPkIUKw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I got ignored by the cashier while she chatted with her coworkers then recieved the worst breakfast wrap I've ever eaten, cold straight through and very small.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexandra Gil","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGHVoZ6S-gccTuFX7t9yx29wH4TozOwS4lSatKljgktDTQENM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food is overpriced (just like any establishment in UBC), the quality doesn't justify the cost, small portions, nothing too special about it since you can find the same baked good in literally every cafe run by UBC. I have been served cold food there. I've been served cold food from there and that's the lease of my complaints regarding the place. The problems are not unique to this cafe, its a standard set across every UBC establishment.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eleanor Hawkins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItAOkchaJ4fzYoHBipQXki6SVib53In7HwmfCCCtVg8XWMJQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Food is good, but they reuse the same milk and re steam it for lattes. The London fog was undrinkable. Milk can only sit for 40 seconds before it should be dumped, and it should never be resteamed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bill Zhang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwbDKu19kVa0ubt7UJxezndgCB9k4mXuDX2262XNQEkLnwqt89=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good paninis at this place, I always ask for extra toasted cause it makes it really nice and crunchy. Ok price too so good place to get a quick bite before your next class.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Isobel Dawson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUusWJxAoDuIDLD2Rend5oOxhk_7NCFJvrYsxitwY3VG_9nDp5ylg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"pretty decent, nothing too exciting. one worker keeps berating her coworkers over things she doesn‚Äôt want to do, sad to see as she gets mad at them for no reason.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amy G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUyB9_jQgQDNOeSjqO6Hb6noFRRtRls_6tm8ZhkHxw7wcptajgO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"More expensive than Starbucks :/ lemon loaf tastes like a lot of vegetable shortening went into it. 8$ for a sandwich is too much...","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Rina Tedja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCUXpJzYjJvgoEpkOVkc0pbrgG_5eFoaZqgY-XQUp-9x6VbVQf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Made a reservation to celebrate my friends graduation, glad that they have a big table to accommodate all of us. Food were good, and we didn't have to wait too long. Price was students friendly, not too expensive. And the waitress was willing to separate the bills. Thank you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOECwl2kQckPquUlCvPef_3x4Heu87O09BQYUEo&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Olive Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWaNKzMiC0kwUfahhPHKJzI23aKwHnkWquzcNkJSLJCjhuJoC_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Restaurant's price with food court level of food and presentation.
$20 bento with only a little bit of rice, the avocado in California roll went half black, the egg tasted disgusting, the miso soup was served in a plastic bowl and the green tea from the water bottle was cold. The fried chicken was the only good thing....but definitely not come back again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kit Kat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3dZjoko9sqyxGJIpo6Vuc0LAP-G_ufVv3gqG1OzG8hLIiI4o=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dined in for the first time two months ago and the food was absolutely delicious! I've tried all of the bento boxes as they are my favourite to get a little bit of everything and they never disappoint. I've since returned many more times to enjoy the food here, and the staff are all so friendly. I would absolutely recommend coming here for a bite to eat 10/10","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Luke Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-nw_Hipvgt6UpenAw0abcDlQMvwpFIko8ke_8Sy_24ohAlwTK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"New food location here at UBC and of course I had to try it out. The restaurant was very clean and had very good COVID 19 precautions set up with electronic little hand sanitizing bottles set up at the entrance and payment counter. The server was nice and very direct. The overall environment while in the environment was very comfortable.

They had quite the variety of food on their menu and at affordable prices considering campus food prices. The menu was large, not overcrowded with menu items, and easy to follow. I ordered Bento Box A with beef (roughly $14) to go. I went at around 3pm on a Sunday, there were a few tables inside and I waited for just over 10 minutes for my food, which was a little longer than I had expected.  The packaging for takeout was pretty meticulous with everything being packed nicely in a large brown paper bag. The food was the typical bento box style food but everything was quite tasty. The beef to rice ratio was a bit lacking but the beef had adequate flavor and the added tamago (sweet eg) was a nice bonus. The California rolls were pretty good and the assorted tempura was light and did not leave an oily taste layer in my mouth.

Overall, a pretty good first experience here at this new establishment on campus. I will be back to try one of their curries.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzR7fkKpZwe8yvCpZLjeSxdz3pIlm7XjwH-llL&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2020-9-15"},{"Name":"Daniel Slick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_rZhDYtX3p8Slyn1b3td54gJ7P5nOU91uTlm-nX3vMAWbK9f5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was very fresh and nicely prepared. Service was very warm and friendly but a little slow.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMV_MEbs8rViQqFqmGdJS2OXO_u5BMXbXZn7vqj&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Tina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAKiC5J1ql1LsLTTfBwgvAj6sVGUusHXghumDKVG9ZTQ8QjcD_1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Quick food and good price! I love their Bento box A (for around $14) with a good variety of thing: tempura, sushi, salad, tamago. It‚Äôs just enough to sample all and the chicken rice is very filling.
Also the service is great and they got my order ready really fast. Recommend for students!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeaPUY7Q--PH_Rutk0VgFbhkRyMSLT8gkqANqC&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2023-6-15"},{"Name":"Sepehr Mirzaei","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZMkP1FM4xSnxxmsChX6t7nGX4XBELdM4VoX6LyFTiA8owPtU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Relatively good food at good prices for UBC. Love the gyu don, the beef Curry, and the fried bento boxes are quite nice too! I wish the tea was a little bit hotter though, but it's free so I can't complain. Sometimes the "wait to be seated" sign makes it hard to enter due to obstruction of the path though which can be a little frustrating","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPiSfDXfg5R1CM-ASn3rWTpnHdczFlq5NuBF7av&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2024-2-23"},{"Name":"w","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVECjtzjKwGGU2yagM5sH2sMNpUPFv0VdGQBZqvehtzvpFlyVDi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"good prices, quick with the food. place is small and cute. waitresses checked up on us regularly.

update: has gotten even better! niku udon tastes authentic and looks amazing","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhtgbisEJ4_pTdVmEGp0QaIsyHLa7DR3Xe8sDg&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2022-8-16"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Adil OKUMU≈û","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWILc9czCClsi1y9wPizaOjmclU9tapIH8_ES7EWExaSXRNOBnE2g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The udon noodles lack firmness and that chewy texture you‚Äôd expect from it. The noodles here taste more like thick cut pasta boiled in water as the base has no taste to it as well. Though California rolls were tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgpY5DR5Gc-JXB-ZTL7HY7s60-DKODDDDNCMen\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can't say enough, but Nori bento is one of the most affordable and high-quality restaurants on campus if you're interested in Japanese food. From the bento options, I like the beef and katsu. For me, the bento is enough for two portions, but I usually eat less than a normal person, I think. The spicy udon noodles with spicy laska broth was nice, and my friend had a good experience. The spicy level for me was 8/10, but it was a nice kind of spiciness, so I definitely recommend it if you like spicy food. The sushi is also nice, but you need to visit the store in person as they're not available for delivery. We usually include one sushi roll, and they're always fresh and good. Also, they have nice staff, and they're pretty quick as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZrb_SeHHHdWxIoRXfkxukBgJQdtKYocmxBAFA\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2024-5-7"},{"Name":"Wei x","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_gqktxpcwm5-Ae9lvoeXAyfIgSzBgJfFmiGs2nilpJU5Zx6z7jw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Perfect place for a quick and inexpensive meal at a nice location. The place is  self serve. Order and pick up at the counter. Clean after done. Service is fast. The food has a good portion and is reasonably good for the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMyeadNAJAius8I8O1Mq2mHcpkypIT90B9ehVhh\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Hashan Peiris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQS5tXYmTSP8F6gc8CzViRW9uUkD3rHwc2GCIQJ7tX0r6Ne1oo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They have a good variety of food. Portion size and the temperature of food is good. Prices are reasonable and one of the best place in the area to taste Asian cuisines. I bought a bento box which came with a miso soup and some crab katsu. All of those were good in taste, portion size and temperature. I would love to try their other dishes and will keep you updated about them.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuATPhm51u0grXUAdBBxtTK-Z6qFsSoqfOzEJl\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2023-7-4"},{"Name":"Lil Crisis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUf-SqiEXi0v2ZRyt3xQxN2DW5nEhVrpSV4y3-tDyj00BCugBTa=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The noodles were pretty soft as if they were over cooked and the Kimchi Mentaiko Udon had very little kimchi in it, no green onion like the photo, and was warm rather than hot like you might expect it to be. I never waste good but had to throw out about half because I couldn‚Äôt bring myself to eat the rest of it","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Adrian Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJRz_uEV8AM70-EugybmCMjVZLIi0OfMP3My2LKS1PidWwGuA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Deep fried teriyaki chicken. The chicken was crispy and crunchy and the portion was large. The tempura was also deep fried really crispy as well, in fact a bit too much in my opinion. Unique take on the normal Bento box. Salad was nice, California roll a bit lacking avocado. Overall really good value and probably the best Japanese on campus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMIeZ7EeRQsBlOSo1rGaRmqodc4UTnNmPZOLFnE\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2021-6-25"},{"Name":"w","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVECjtzjKwGGU2yagM5sH2sMNpUPFv0VdGQBZqvehtzvpFlyVDi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely bussin. Portion sizes are huge for the banging price. Food was ready 90 seconds after we ordered. Recommend the tonkotsu ramen.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNte3JWgReq0dfvd3nnvI63ELOzijrfb4q1Cjw_\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2022-12-20"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"It gets the job done if you have a craving for bento or sushi, but not the greatest. Portion size is okay, but everything is a little lacking in flavour and the rice and croquettes are pretty greasy. On some occasions the food has been better than others - I've never had a terrible experience here, but the quality floats around just alright to underwhelming. Service is also slower than I would expect for fast food, although the staff is nice. Again, though, it's good for satisfying a craving for Japanese comfort food if you don't have the time to go somewhere nicer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN9ZNX2nVv53JUypILVN9dAbQQqy4GsB19SiOfB\u0026fid=0x0:0xd5fcdfc69a733d2d"],"When":"2021-2-3"}]
