user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jeff Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVeVKpdfNOdTnoZ-ITkSuOW-c2zXalTP1RiXc0xiQ5ZEZBSpWaGw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I‚Äôm a huge fan of Xi‚Äôan cuisine so I got the Cumin Lamb Noodles. This was dressed in a fragrant chilli oil sauce, and was decently spicy/numbing. (The kind that makes you sweat and blow your nose mid-meal). Generous portion of thicker hand-pulled noodles and sliced lamb, and only a handful of gratuitous veggies at the bottom. This is a heavier option for a meal so be warned. Decent value for $15+tax. Only wish it was tad less greasy and included more veggies. Service was super friendly!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsGHmIHxKdxVTdO5K1hvrNzisuObOdV8gOpEDr&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Josh J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXe42PdxuYHUOJL_X8RN0pr9xXBVzrdppHzz1uqjoxioU06wUY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered a Beef Fried Rice Noodle. The entire bowl had only a handful of beef (around 3-5 pieces). The rest is bean sprouts. Literally around 500g of bean sprouted on my bowl. And doused in so much oil I can't taste anything but the oil.

I get that there's cost cutting measures but this is just inexcusable for the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNShl1CT87CReQzrVfSvBSP_m74OWBFYD5Au1Tf&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2024-8-7"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered two dishes, one with two toppings and one with three toppings. The base was fried rice with vegetables, which was tasty. Our favorite topping was the sweet and sour chicken, followed by the spicy fried shrimp. I'm not a fan of beef brisket, so I didn't enjoy it as much, but it wasn't bad at all. The tofu and fried chicken were also good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYn5ivfW57olI8tk1-SStvN0ONJf03iQ8hIsij&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2024-3-23"},{"Name":"Serena Jiang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdrdumUkGSxjbtk1_LQZc0knhS2eGprfXet3quGlQUesHypA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food was lukewarm and you could see oil coagulating in the trays. I understand it‚Äôs made earlier in the day but shouldn‚Äôt fast food at least be served hot considering people are eating it right away? Also I‚Äôm clearly getting tiny portions of the items compared to the photos here and from the reviews saying ‚Äúgenerous portions/ good portion for the price‚Äù. To be fair I could imagine the braised beef tasting really good for tray food if it‚Äôs hot, hence one more star than this experience deserves.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNl6gVMVsuDEnQrnqEc4lczMnKqKGZ-0QpTvEE9&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2024-5-5"},{"Name":"Thanh To","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVd1WYJP1UmnIbSg76XorhMDMrCl48AkAncBIVkE7p0lcIIllbB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Not sure why all the hate but Sesame probably gives the most bang for your bucks on campus. The food is consistent and the portions are huge. Sure, the Chinese food in the international basement is cheaper but at least here you can see how clean the kitchen is. That said, prices have increased within the last few months. [{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The new Popeyes restaurant in the UBC area is finally open! The staff are nice and kind‚ÄîI asked for additional sauce, and they happily gave it to me, so I'm giving them a 10/10 üòõ. The quality of the food is the same as at all other Popeyes locations: it's nice and tasty, perfect if you enjoy fast food. I definitely recommend their hot wings and butterfly shrimp; both were really nice and tasty. Try all the different sauces‚Äîpersonally, I prefer the buttermilk ranch, but I also like the Cajun cocktail sauce, which is pretty unique to me.

I'll definitely try more and update my review if anything changes. üç§ üçó üçü

I am very impressed that the vegan and GF muffins are large, have good texture, and lots of flavours to choose from üëç Also, even my cat seems to like the scones.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbx7PB-wr1q7IhJ04-Yt0yTK7qPtHQNSMcLR9W&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love their sandwiches! The atmosphere is great, they have a mini bonfire outdoor sitting which I love. It does get packed during school term tho. The drinks are ok.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOS_Zq_evUK07fQpAswcFGj_GtmlHZX4AUnVmz_&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Jamie Glennon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLOjs5-jqgyQWUX_yOuzgUG9TpUgCo3VZBWVH5vnxr8HdflLs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great spot close to Chan Centre and Gage Towers for a high quality coffee and baked good in the morning.

Much better than the chain coffee shops!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWllLnH-9j6g8HteXdulm-5IuO4DeupNnsxwGs&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"Justbeing Sam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWM9hiJK-AfVP-qSHlK2ogC-KKU9aHv9jB-f8Zpy8fNkox9PG5e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nestled in a cozy corner, this cafe is a warm embrace of delicious coffee and friendly vibes in UBC . Baristas greet you with smiles, crafting your perfect cup with care. Vintage decor and irresistible pastries add to the charm, making it the perfect spot to unwind and connect.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIzHKWJ5uIM5OYLtmxcD6VblvJoIt7iesMyagS&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2024-3-22"},{"Name":"Eden","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgHIQ66Jm9chZEYySFVv8p0ryPQbWvKkG3vS_9dnDINf-CKCV_ZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This beautiful cafe is highly suggested if you ever decide to staycation or study at UBC.

It is a pet-friendly cafe and offers quality products of fresh sandwiches, espressos, delicious homemade pastries [ with options of gluten-free], and spacious atmosphere with an outdoor fireplace! The staff were so welcoming, friendly, and excellent counter-costumer service.

Their business hours may not meet your needs nor expectations but they'll be opening early and close late once school starts in September.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyppoj0m0i95g6EEpfFj7iN4tIukn51d2QckpU&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2021-8-8"},{"Name":"Jessica Lu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTqZgPj0eXg_JYgAnVgUcTOilpA24BvBnkompjw1nEkEUn2g3_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Only been here once and ordered a matcha latte. It sucks. Tastes like milk and the matcha flavour is absent. My mistake for ordering drinks when this place is known for their sandwiches. The latte art was cute.

Staff are very kind and efficient especially because this place gets super busy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tario Sultan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVs5egw4ytTDIua69pxGET59kVTaWgbfGJaRgqyQl37e1dCXZiC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Dane Coffee shop located towards the north side of UBC campus.

The staff is super friendly and helpful. Pretty good quality coffee, the price is definitely reasonable.

Highly recommended!

Keep it up guys.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYAsbfa3t9q9Juj68FHljEPh0OO5hRwXWah_gi&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2022-12-14"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Iconic coffee shop at UBC. The staff is really chill and friendly so the vibe is great, and the food/drink is good all around. In particular they have some of my favourite scones around. Their veggie sandwich is very very good (as long as you're prepared for your hands to smell like focaccia for the rest of the day). Except for during the summer, they have a daily soup which is always very tasty. The regular dessert pastries (brownie, cookies, dessert bars) are all good but not stand-out good, but they sometimes have fancier cakes which are amazing.
For their drinks, it is also really hard to go wrong. The masala chai latte is amazing - it's sweet but also richly flavoured with spices. The London fog is also very good. Both of these tea lattes use stone ground tea instead of brewed tea which I think contributes to the intensity. They do a great job with the matcha latte too - it's never clumpy at all. I used to be not the biggest fan of their coffee, but it's grown on me a lot. It's a bit on the acidic side, but if you don't mind that, then the flavour is pretty nice. I really like their mocha too (especially the peppermint mocha available in winter) - this is actually the only place where I really get mochas!
They have pizza nights now (7-10 Wed-Fri) where you can get a flatbread pizza big enough to feed two for less than $15. Only the very basic flavours available (margherita, bianca, or pepperoni), but super tasty (and cheesy).
The seating inside is limited and the space is so narrow that I find it very hard to be comfortable inside unless you go during a rare quiet hour, but I love the patio, which is huge and mostly covered. They sometimes turn the fireplace on during the cold season.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWhxuY6zE3pvpsEAp5I-7RS-wKJgHl_8B7qvR0&fid=0x0:0x58f47ab4d39c9e95"],"When":"2020-10-24"}]

Waste of money, will not be returning","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott Gong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVU6Nrm_sRXxa4lpEjkIrZxamz6LceMGV7mYsCaPEW4FMeyz2s=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Most over-priced burger and fries I have ever had in my life. I paid $20+ for those two low quality items, and I spent 20 mins waiting for my order. Unbelievable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN631R1cPS3wdtE7V2X44E-JEd_XK6KnfeYAx-X&fid=0x0:0xfba7b2899b4f414c"],"When":"2022-8-25"},{"Name":"Hoori Barkh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVsmGMB0Ma8Q_QX1b7LIeHjfj2OE3c7JiglHyQcJ3rqf9KbgA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Skip Vera‚Äôs!
Ordered online and paid, when we got to the store apparently they never received our order so we ordered again and paid (1 week later I‚Äôm still waiting for my online order refund).
Took a while to get the food ready (that‚Äôs fine, made fresh-ok) but the quality of the burgers was just mediocre. Nothing to complain about but nothing to rave about either.
Restaurant was completely empty on a Friday night. Surprised they are still in business to be honest.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eric Grant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhVR02aPzwVvQvqn63QlXyk0bgYy0E-LewKb9qSI5x_FX_h9ejyg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"There are many great mysteries in life. How were the Pyramids built? What is Love? And most mysterious of all, how is this place still in business? It is always empty. Never go to an empty restaurant.
Only thing I tried was the chocolate milkshake. Was disappointed with the size, price, and texture and the time it took to make it. Why does it take 15 minutes to make a milkshake when I am the only one there? If you are going to get one make sure to ask for it well blended or get a spoon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Esmed P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPaVfVvhS7UlShhw7n3W_Eju3p15-TBYDAUGYnwKIb2zgwxN8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went during my lunch hour & ordered. I wait, & after 25 minutes pass watching the person who took my order have a conversation with another staff in the kitchen, I get up & start to hover at the counter. I guess they noticed, because I saw only then, did they start cooking my order. There's no ketchup available, so I asked for some. The lady seemed confused, then insited they keep it behind the counter. Finally after waiting another 20 minutes, I'm given my burger with smallest amount of ketchup possible, after this lady had sassed me about literally, 3 drips of water which fell from my fountain drink after pouring myself water. I didn't bother to try to ask for more kerchup I wanted. Bottom line, do not go here, unless you want horrendously slow & rude service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brian Taylor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVS9FnL1Xm2VSimjexdVbc5QM_VHkzVtM3eQen6wRNt-IyDFLYSYA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I'm not sure how this place stays in business. I used the Vera's app to order a burger and got confirmation of my order at 6:12 pm, but the burger wouldn't be ready until 6:45 pm (not that the restaurant was the slightest bit busy). I showed up at the restaurant at 6:35 and the staff weren't aware of my order and asked what app I used. Really? Once the order was located they proceeded to make the burger and it was ready by 6:50. I had ordered a Vera burger ($10.50) with a few free toppings, cheese ($2 extra) and bacon ($2.50 extra). When I sat down to eat the burger I thought they'd forgotten the bacon so I brought it up to the counter. It was pointed out to me that there was a piece of bacon on the burger, but at most it was one square inch! For $2.50? The burger tasted fine and I've enjoyed Vera burgers for a long time, but if there were a Five Guys anywhere on the West Side I would never go back to Veras.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tano Pham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLZTH6gNWlc-cb4ja-Rt0oeskyJW7A4uEUVtm6QYAF2hoCk8A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely terrible service on a non-school day at the UBC campus location by this employee. Had ordered my burger 35 minutes ahead on the app and she did not accept the order until I physically got there.
What is the point of skip the line function of the app if takes your money and not process your order","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuESOGkrJ4ca-F7MGAy2wyT8MDyLvBk6Wdks6G&fid=0x0:0xfba7b2899b4f414c"],"When":"2019-2-23"}]

[{"Name":"Ali","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVc2yFZO2stJjMAA_yC-haWWL7s20-2uvdCcNdcZmJ0nShSIEgN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Lemongrass Chicken with spring rolls was extremely tasty and definitely worth the $19. While some comments suggest this place might not be the destination for authentic food, our experience was fantastic! The chicken was juicy, the salad was well-dressed, and the vermicelli was cooked to perfection. The portion sizes were so generous that we ended up taking most of our food home for later. I would definitely come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAr1GhD8M7eOKgDtd4ILOfEhn0gSPEBWV4dytn&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"Arroyo Spero","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxtGzSht4hUue94OJChsO0T0v5gn-kGbLMxKrdo9nYj-1wKfpi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The rare beef pho was the best I‚Äôve had in Vancouver,  if not the world.  I also had a great chat with my server who was knowledgeable,  kind and extremely efficient.  I will always recommend this restaurant as the go to for Pho in Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPh0pmw8fVpITDOGmScrITwuse1QuIG3sFBEY7x&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"Tony Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPKcy0N8L_e03kCanD-kbqBYJvghgec1_Wu16Qs-S8YjI-PLg2nw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"For a pho place at UBC, it's pretty good but it lacks authenticity. I mean, the broth is great but you don't get a plate of bean sprouts and basil leaves like you do at other pho restaurants. I thought maybe at first, they forgot but my second time eating in, they forgot again. No one got it so that seems to be the norm. Service is prompt. Food is good. Also for big eaters, try to do an add-on. I added a lemongrass chicken to my pho and ended up bringing home 2 large pieces of grilled chicken for dinner. The servings are plentiful. Meat balls can be a little more plump, quail eggs in a seafood soup?? Music is a bit rad for this place too but catered to students, it's understandable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjOQVegjA6Q1U07IN_MZnnr7auHBN2VOCLhu2c&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2024-4-30"},{"Name":"ITwins (iTwins)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUUfk9fQ2wnUPyx22p2MtHChD4th8SauoOfDx9kxsrTGIv_31wePQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went to UBC for the Food Truck Festival. Instead, we ended up having lunch here. We should have eaten at the festival.

This is an imitation Ph·ªü restaurant or a Ph·ªü-wannabe restaurant. Their ph·ªü soup tasted nothing like authentic ones. It also has no Vietnamese ph·ªü names, like B√∫n B√≤ Hu·∫ø, Ph·ªü t√°i Nam, or Ph·ªü b√≤ vi√™n, for example.

My $18.50 "Spicy Beef Noodle Soup" tastes somewhat similar to Bun Bo Hue but lacks all the major ingredients found in real BBH. It only comes with meatballs and beef slices typically used in Hot Pots or Shabu Shabu. üòÖ The taste is also very mild in comparison and lacks any herb flavor.

The $19 "Special Noodle Soup" is laughable, not even close to any beef pho we have ever tasted. But nothing is worse than what I am about to say....

In both the noodles, the beef slices were HOLY SH*T!! - SO MUCH FAT! ü´£üòÆ‚Äçüí®üòµ There were less than half edible meat portions in each slice. Don't know if we should ROFL or go postal. Either way, one of the worst beef ph·ªü we have ever eaten in the world (only two other ph·ªü restaurants in the world are worse than Ph·ªü With Us', and we have eaten many ph·ªü in many, many countries in our world travels!)

Three hours later, my stomach was growling and I had to eat a full meal. Therefore, Pho With Us' pho is considered a snack. $19 FOR A SNACK. Sheesh!!!

.

Picture 1: $18.50 "S1 Spicy Beef Noodle Soup." Doesn't look greasy initially. Wait till the end....

Picture 2: $19 "P1 Special Noodles Soup"

Picture 3: Every beef slice is filled with fats. Not for human consumption!

Picture 4: A thick layer of grease formed on the surface at the end of the meal

.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvVQMHXUy43_OHH3GX22WtlqJezpi7tgHp1wiY&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2024-4-6"},{"Name":"Harry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-RtcD0-6ye1J2JBnA5bvdHPLsbB6QNrfMYYEBmsFbjc_dS_Co=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best bowls of pho I've ever had! The soup is really really good and there were plenty of beef and beef balls in the soup. The shrimp salad rolls are also really good but I couldn't finish it because of the large portion size of the pho. The only thing I would change about the special pho is adding some beef tripes to the pho, but it's not a popular ingredient outside of Asia so that is understandable. The staff is super nice too! The ambiance is also super nice with speakers playing pop music that I actually recognize. Honestly a super wonderful experience! The restaurant deserves a higher rating than the current average rating since I was unsure about the quality from reading the rating and the low rating is a little misleading.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNomg64hwrqeNIsRWfQmdhF93tXomr06ajxhY-o&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2024-3-20"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I didn‚Äôt know where to set my expectations for Pho  with Us, but I was pretty impressed with the food here! I had the Tofu & Veggie Rolls with Dry Noodles and a Tofu Pudding w/ Ginger Syrup. The noodle dish (vermicelli) was totally delicious, especially the veggie spring rolls! Even though the tofu and spring rolls were deep-fried, the dish didn‚Äôt have an oily taste. I saved one of the spring rolls for later and was still very full - I could have gotten two light but complete meals out of this if I hadn‚Äôt gotten excited and eaten so fast to start out with. The tofu pudding was okay, kind of bland. I haven‚Äôt had a dessert like this from a Vietnamese restaurant before so I don‚Äôt know how it usually should be. I appreciated that the ginger syrup wasn‚Äôt too sweet but I would have liked the ginger to be stronger. This was also a large portion so I took half home.
Like other restaurants in University Marketplace, the environment is rather cafeteria-like, meaning not much ambiance to speak of, but the people who run it are nice and hard-working. Considering it‚Äôs campus eats, it checks all the boxes: tasty, great value, and quick. And it‚Äôs great to have a Vietnamese restaurant at UBC now.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNpGIHMY6CyqkBkK4uTFVZVKAfFxEqyve7u59Px&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2023-5-28"},{"Name":"This food","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUaxcCslaGrcC0u202g67ni7XJGWWGyPYtSKkUjWo5gpcXXO0Yv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I‚Äôm so glad they opened a pho place at UBC! This is perfect for those cold days on campus.

The portions are big and it‚Äôs a fair price given the inflation. My sandwich was a little over $7 and had plenty of filling. The spring rolls were larger than expected and I was still able to take one roll home.

No issues with seating when we arrived on a weekday at around 12:15pm. Really enjoyed it here and will return to try pho. They take card. Paid parking at the front or free parking along the road after 6pm. Overall, I recommend coming here if you‚Äôre craving some pho or hang-over food when your in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNE4Pg5kLkE6ABWevnDyEibjpcF6lM-hSY-dlDf&fid=0x0:0xfbcb5a17df449c00"],"When":"2023-3-29"},{"Name":"Florios Demosten","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKV_Z2MRxAoQMQk052NPA0eDIO0u7XtdAaudscAalqOrOtXLw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered Uber eats from here, I got the lemongrass chicken.

I don‚Äôt usually leave Google reviews so let that stand out for how bad this chicken was. It tasted like it was 2 days old and microwaved.","Images":null,"When":""}]

The staff is usually friendly and quick at making drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKaY80NvBrp9MejmRXGXmZFkt4EuAqiv-HNs4Q\u0026fid=0x0:0x1d82acab1faef3e3"],"When":"2022-11-26"},{"Name":"Manu Goyal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZ9bGCnzhlvZbFUtYdBmuIDxw5aGDmnpBiY-LPoM3HSUmqDce-uA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Tried latte and tiramisu here. I asked for extra hot latte but it was cold when I got it. And tiramisu was good taste wise but it was very watery from the bottom and looked like it was made a few days ago. Would for sure be difficult if you use a mobility aid.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Harran Shi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVposYwd6J2dlDeYCSGnh3ME_dZtFZ9u3SjpUExJkrlqu62h0dh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I like their cheesecake and matcha teramisu but they are always out of something in the fridge, especially ice cream. They sometimes have Mochi here and sometimes don‚Äôt. Their frozen cheesecakes are also always missing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hash Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLExeuh0C9VNkYa2zON0uFAstj3F0xPIKlp5QJJJRUEiJHWQA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst service ever. One female server of an Indonesian ethnicity gave me a bad attitude as she IGNORED me, because I was wearing a cheap hoodie that day. It is certainly concerning how such a snobbish woman can get a job here, and it is appalling to see such disingenuous behavior toward the customers. I am cynical toward the way this place is managed, cynical to the snobs that work there, and downright appalled by the discrimination that occurs here on a day to day basis.\n\nA comment to the owner's response: Yes I do remember when this happened, approximately a year ago. I remember it so vividly because of my disbelief in such an appalling service attitude. [{"Name":"Ivy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2btWvwldxPAFdVC30WRTnDiJDb4PhrEfk_b3M_t3CbTqvHC0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The ramen taste burn and the matcha ice cream had a weird tasteü§Æü§Æü§Æü§¢ü§¢ü§¢such low quality food with such expensive price would not recommend ü§¢ü§¢ü§¢ü§Æü§Æü§Æü§Æü§ÆÂ£ÅÂòû","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdRK5BM3beGQhxrAC3I49SGPyZrU6PGt0ZqMA6&fid=0x0:0x50d70a428840f326"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"YVR Duke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbrjJ5U6gKw7Gn1zE_GlxhUndims9WHlh7sVaHLXVrjOFlYd_B=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"**Rating: 3/5**

The ramen broth here has potential but needs less water to enhance its flavor. The pork was well-prepared, albeit too small a piece. The thick noodles I chose were an absolute disaster ‚Äì the worst noodle texture I've ever experienced, both in North America and Asia.

The gyoza were deep-fried, which isn't typical in Asia but is common in North America due to the preference for fried foods and the ease of preparation. Thankfully, their frying technique was spot on, with the right temperature making the skin crunchy and not greasy.

Overall, this ramen shop is one step away from being good, but that one step is significant. I'm puzzled by its high rating; perhaps it's because it's being compared to other campus food options?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEZscgOvkrJVwnAhJ_ijxCSFxfSYjODwksU3PC&fid=0x0:0x50d70a428840f326"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Alexander Hunt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKntg94WsHup3cVgJBk3yO0jaRf4K-ndL2T0xGy94s_gBQtie8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My friend and I had the opportunity to visit the Kinton Ramen UBC. At 6 pm on the weekday for dinner, there was a lot of space available. There are options for indoor and outdoor seating. This will be great for friends, couples or groups of friends. Indoor seating can sit around 15 people. Outdoor seating can sit around 20 people. The chairs inside are small, and the space feels somewhat cramped.

The prices for the food are on the upside as per usual for restaurants near the university campus. Both my friend and I ordered the Pork Original with thick noodles. The portions were small (somewhat little noodles, two pieces of pork), but the thick noodles and broth tasted great. Service was fast, but servers are friendly and attentive.

Our final bill came around to around $40 dollars which can be quite expensive for students or those living on campus in student housing. If the portions were more and the prices were cheaper, I will be returning here for more food. I would recommend people to try out this restaurant if they have not before, but not to rely here for a full stomach.

The washrooms are clean. The restaurant is wheelchair accessible, but the space is cramped and washroom are also small. There is underground parking quite close.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1m_bO2WcI2xuf2eO5LkkMFM0jEGbqyphVHSSq&fid=0x0:0x50d70a428840f326"],"When":"2024-4-10"},{"Name":"Keith Ver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVdqxLCf1LEt0AU82myo-eUqDcb2LcbdnfhupJTEW0sPAQ-qQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely loved the Beef Original ramen! First time to visit UBC and glad we found a ramen place! We also ordered their Pork Shoyu ramen, Chicken Karaage, and for desert, we had matcha and black sesame cheesecake. Service was fast and staff were friendly too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPO-3TfmeZZtj6P98VvroDVI_hKZpPM5w2f4y24&fid=0x0:0x50d70a428840f326"],"When":"2024-5-8"},{"Name":"Paul Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXn3m0AZWl28VYBOwUKfmGVllVddsvt-pe4tcU6-ebIHORKGYiIPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The food itself is somewhat decent but literally 4 out of 5 water cups have remaining food scraps in it. [{"Name":"Hiep Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMRHHZ7t798igHqhwEObqqiXXBYRe7_vTRRS3-gXG7fOgZlXSH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here tonight with some friends for an event so decided to have dinner here beforehand. It's my first time here, but my 3 friends have been here before. The atmosphere and energy in the place was fun and upbeat. When I told the cashier it's my first time,  please explain to me the level of spicy that comes with the chicken....he yelled "we got a first timer here!", and everyone in the back kitchen started shouting and cheering. That was different and created a fun atmosphere.  Let's get down to the chicken review üòã.  I ordered 2 piece with fries for $16.90, since I already had a drink in hand from somewhere else. I got it medium spicy. The chicken came with a slice of white bread underneath!? I was too carbed out to eat the bread. The seasoning and spice on the chicken was very tasty. It wasn't spicy at all, I liked the aroma. The fries were over fried, cause I don't taste the potato in it. Fortunately the seasoning made it easier to eat, so because of that I gave 5 stars for food since there's no 4.5 stars.  My friends all got the chicken sandwich or the waffle burger.....they loved it. Guess next time I will try a burger.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNR0vIuazIqKD1CR4YW4wDEWJcCBDsJelIUWijn&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-9-25"},{"Name":"Kanwar SEKHON","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX6CQMCc3TK9DOgcaVwnWRnMj24w6Pf6GP7z7TXjOEVhEyXN7Sx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Downlow Chicken Shack at UBC is a hidden gem! The food is absolutely immaculate‚Äîcrispy, flavorful fries and a juicy, perfectly cooked chicken sandwich that hits all the right notes. The sauces were on point, adding just the right kick to the meal.

The only downside is the overpriced soda‚Äî$3.50 feels a bit steep‚Äîbut other than that, everything else was spot on. The ambiance of the restaurant is fun and casual, making it a great spot for a quick bite. Highly recommend if you‚Äôre craving top-notch fried chicken near campus! Parking does become an issue while there‚Äôs just limited spots at front","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOh1_86RgN87YR6du_1Nn77FF8N5IgnKapjPj7Q&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-12-24"},{"Name":"Karen Mitchell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcKSF5TnT2tFwehIpLls1j_5b_VIihK99BbPy203xWx-oz-Aqc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was our first time and the service was exceptional.  We really enjoyed ourselves and felt welcomed off the jump.
The food was exploding with flavour and freshness, we ordered the mac n cheese, creamy and flavourful, the OG, OG hot, and the stinger and stinger hot‚Ä¶ all of our sandos were well balanced spice and sweet, crunchy and juicy.  The crinkle cut fries were hot and crisp with soft potato inside, they were well dusted with truffle spice‚Ä¶ I‚Äôd like to try plain fries too next time. We also tried the in house original drinks which complemented our eats perfectly.
Loved this elevated fast food, delicious. We‚Äôll be back absolutely.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMf26xJfgETJH4lBjHqTLZIVii_ZzZRykCBzdMj&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Bradley Jones","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQSjOdt_NCThfrgQQSPCAI9c1m2q4Cia70lWTZMyAGLNwKu8R3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Chicken is all the rage.  We‚Äôve done the wraps the smoothies the frozen yogurts it‚Äôs now the fried chicken.  Is it good yes is it pricey yes.  I actually have probably aged out here as I had to have one of my 16 year old‚Äôs order for me.  It seems to be the same chicken with different temperatures.  For those into the chicken crazy it‚Äôs a must as the chicken is moist and the battery is excellent.  So join the craze and go loco. Lemonade is a must.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0yUOD3jwNom_AFqWw3hkYZTDxPzF7kou6k6jA&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"AJ R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLo4tIvUrcwNXdNPm8MhPpZgzsQXb-_lGpW8MEceFXJ5buZ1dI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my favourite fried chicken joint in the city! I‚Äôve been going to the commercial spot for years and it never disappoints, and I‚Äôm glad they opened a spot closer to where I live! Lemon pepper chicken was my favourite, but it‚Äôs not on the menu now so I switched to Jerk as my go to. I‚Äôd recommend trying any new/special flavours that come in because they‚Äôre always great. The chicken is so juicy and perfectly seasoned. Great sides as well!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuLHSwiIug5WM9aa9EYGCga2X_ilVbOoqBSqZw&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Flo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQ1akzv9WR_KmITyG3KFOeHflaL3qvQNBp7BgDlj35f6xKGqcT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I got chicken thighs and fries! Food was decent enough and it has large portions that I couldn‚Äôt even finish. Cashier was nice. One suggestion is to maybe have a sign or let customers know they can wait anywhere outside or inside for order. I didn‚Äôt know so was standing by tablet with orders and felt I was in the way and was accidentally bumped into. And I tried to ask where I should be for order and then they let me know after I asked. I wish I knew earlier, so I‚Äôd wouldn‚Äôt have been in the way. Also I think they thought I might be in rush to get order. But I was not in a rush at all. I just didn‚Äôt know protocol for where to wait at Downlow since it‚Äôs my first time. Cafes usually make you wait at the end of counter to get drinks with your names on it. So I assumed it‚Äôs the same. A sign letting customers know would make a difference in the whole experience for everyone. Just a suggestion! Thanks :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvfSmmgJwve3XFFkCmrkmLNL8pofRE9hZA2yQc&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Oba Onabanjo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXW_LaEsiqKs72-cl7kUfU4hZlVuhuF321Bgnqi7uTxAz-piEFt=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Having a good chicken place on campus is such a blessing. The atmostphere is great , the staff are  really nice and personable and the music is a vibe . If you are a UBC The student special is a great deal, with respectable portions, which is a rarity on campus.  Would definitely recommend stopping by , especially if you like spicy food","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8oDj7cvSDXAc2LBgQ1NlTNO72Rm12157sNc-P&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Michelle Siaril","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvNHVR_L-5eCK2usU0kQoT055SV9vB2qDNPyrA7CmG9QXO2IM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Finally tried this fried chicken on campus. I‚Äôve heard mixed reviews from friends so been always hesitant to try. We all got the tender (extra hot and medium) and fries ($18.25/each) since we aren‚Äôt into dark meat. Honestly tasted average, pretty decent if a bit bland. Even the extra hot didn‚Äôt taste spicy but rather just peppery, whereas the medium had a more pronounced herby flavour. Batter was way too flakey and fell apart really easily, which led me to believe it was either too thin or not fried long enough. Sauces were pretty good in terms of variety though, the honey mustard and sweet&sour were pretty good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYfT4rTK4QjwO-zwmj9uQVqHI99ixDrq2hQ6Q&fid=0x0:0xe24f0c30803538b5"],"When":"2024-4-28"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Dakota Spence-Zurek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJzVq4oxp5JPUW0eYm0YjE08yOW8sHTAKTq1g0LpJ51fXxEh8E=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food provided at our wedding was varied yet classic and delicious. The staff members were incredibly helpful and were fantastic to our guests. Our guests complimented us on how nice the staff was and how easy they were to work with, as well as complimentary of the food. Would recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mitchell JBP","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKBPFpRZTYpJOUmV29GqM5EplgDqU4Y50vRchHmtgT0b5_VC4Q9g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Avoid This Venue for Major Life Events Like Weddings

If you‚Äôre considering booking this venue for a significant event, such as a wedding, I highly recommend looking elsewhere.

Last month, my friend hosted his wedding here, spending tens of thousands of dollars to make it a memorable day. While the venue itself is stunning, with breathtaking ocean and mountain views that provided a beautiful backdrop for the wedding party photos, the experience was marred by the poor attitude of the staff.

The bartender, who appeared to be the manager that evening, was particularly unpleasant. Throughout the event, she repeatedly told us what we couldn‚Äôt do and restricted our alcohol consumption, even though we had purchased the bar in full. Her demeanor was rude and condescending, which was shocking considering the high standard one would expect from such an establishment.

To make matters worse, despite the bar being fully paid for, she cut off alcohol service early, claiming we had been drinking too much. Some guests brought their own beer, and as a result, my friend (the groom) was charged an additional $500. On top of that, he was asked to RETURN THE NEXT DAY TO ASSIST WITH CLEANUP, which is completely unacceptable given the substantial amount spent on the event.

While we understand that venues have their own policies, the complete lack of warmth and professionalism from the staff was inexcusable. It‚Äôs not unreasonable to expect friendly, respectful service, especially when you're hosting such an important event at a venue of this caliber.

I‚Äôm writing this review to caution others‚Äîif you‚Äôre looking for a venue that will treat you and your guests with the respect and hospitality your event deserves, I suggest you look elsewhere.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"For you Beauty co","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJCKWjQ0aSunYiHn0gMD1zU8gnUGU5Hn0kRT7EMy3ElrRO57w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I attended a wedding here recently, and while the venue itself was charming, there were quite a few rules that took away from the experience. The open bar was paused due to what they called ‚Äúover-consumption‚Äù within just an hour, which felt quite restrictive. On top of that, even when the bar was open, we had to have our partners present just to get a drink‚Äîeven though we‚Äôd been at the venue the entire time!

Initially, we were allowed to have drinks at the dining tables, but partway through the event, they suddenly changed the rules. We were required to stay in the bar area, which felt limiting and confusing for a wedding celebration.

To top it off, the staff were unwilling to help with cleaning up the dance floor or removing decor, leaving the BRIDE AND GROOM to come back the next day to CLEAN it themselves. For such a special event, I‚Äôd expect more assistance from the venue, especially considering how much was spent. The location is beautiful, but the restrictive rules and lack of support from staff left much to be desired.

To add to that, a staff member was oddly strict about which cups we used and although the glasses were displayed on the counter. When we reached for the glass they took it away while giving us dirty looks the entire time. It made the experience feel unnecessarily tense.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Sweeney","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJsmz9GI8ExaCB0lCj7Ss9NSiRqh7rZA3AqqW0yMW3UfLFHqw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As we booked Cecil Green Park House for our wedding, we had Sage catering the event. We do not currently live in Vancouver and therefore were not able to try any of the food in advance, thankfully we were not disappointed! Every request was considered and all allergies were easily accommodated. Many of our guests raved about the food and we thoroughly enjoyed our meals as the bride and groom. Some favorites specifically mentioned were the mushroom soup, beef tenderloin and cheesecake.

Starters: Kale Caesar Salad and Mushroom Soup
Pre-Selected Entree Options: Salmon, Mushroom Risotto and AAA Beef Tenderloin
Dessert: Berry Cheesecake","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bangshoong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXAtBnMaPt0KMr34CwkrunZKxINlmvKEisDOhBY_AJY9gL4IFT1CQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have never had a bad experience using sage catering! in all honestly, I have nothing but positive things to say about this company. They have not only the best food, but incredible staff! Food quality and presentation are ALWAYS delicious and on point. ‚ÄúIncredible‚Äù is also an understatement for sage staff. This team is accommodating, responsive, extremely nice and always a pleasure to work with - in conclusion, I highly recommend sage for catering. If you‚Äôre looking for the best customer service, and amazing food, then sage should become your go-to for catering.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMcTdDcjMkCD3_2aH1Z2iuMJo6akNWGMLOhH4Ie&fid=0x0:0x4272b6b37e601a30"],"When":"2023-4-8"},{"Name":"Jag Barpagga","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhHtcktTdCipjF7fIthdF00_U6VZRlz-wmx5acU8hqwxBMB1k=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My daughter got married at Cecil Green Park house. The only option for catering is to get Sage Catering. It's the worst catering service ever. They didn't have enough food for breakfast or lunch eventhough our guest count was less than the number we provided to Sage. Also, DON'T be fooled by the price menu provided by Cecil Green House or Sage; that's just the tip of the iceberg. For example, we paid around $6000 for the food and about $6000 for the service and staff. What you see on the menu is just the cost of the food. It doesn't include delivery, staff, cook's time, etc. I wish I could give them MINUS 5 stars, but that's not the option. The staff supervisor was arrogant and non co-operative. Their excuse for insufficient food was, "They don't police how much each person is taking". I have emails to prove it. Please don't be embarrassed by blindly signing the contract; PUT A Clause saying something like "If any food items are not enough, you will get 20% discount for each item. My only motive is to save you embarrassment in front of your guests.
Thanks for reading!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cherlyn Manderson-Cortes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrHv0Pxs6QRuT5JsYRzN6IdzpnA2-AhKwxzZVktuO4BuEyHTh4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"‚ÄúI‚ÄôM TELLING YOU THAT FOOD WAS SO GOOD!‚Äù These were the words of one of my good friends, whose husband is a chef and owns a restaurant on South Granville. Other quotes from my wedding guests include, ‚Äúthat steak was so incredibly tender‚Äù and, ‚ÄúSablefish is my favourite, but it never tasted so good before!‚Äù. My vegan friend came up to me during dinner, fork in hand   and said, ‚Äúyou have to try this. It‚Äôs the best mushroom I‚Äôve ever had‚Äù. In fact, every time I ran into a friend after our wedding, the memory of the food would come back to them, and mid-sentence, their eyes would widen and they‚Äôd say, ‚Äúoh my god! The food!‚Äù It was so rewarding to hear how the people I loved felt nourished and beyond satisfied with their meal at our wedding. The catering and bartending staff were also phenomenal! They were so friendly and helpful ‚Äì I remember one staff who held my plate for me at the buffet while I held the train of my dress up. And I can‚Äôt thank Levi enough, who was our food and beverage manager. He always answered my emails in a timely way, and he managed to snag the last few rental patio warmers in the city before our October wedding. Because we were married during pandemic restrictions, dancing wasn‚Äôt permitted indoors, but with the patio warmers and a covered patio, our guests sang karaoke and danced their hearts out!

(photos @georgiajohnstonphotography, decor & turquoise linens @ellssirentals, florals @jorbelinaflowers, venue @cecilgreenparkhouse)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNX6w6-STZFJEgOg20ObTkWhlOkE_rxWjHakZh7&fid=0x0:0x4272b6b37e601a30"],"When":"2022-10-22"},{"Name":"Gaby Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0W4PKqBoZ3q8I6ORn5jCGNJo_EbPYdO9COMfQu6soCVZZMFx-XQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We visited many places around the UBC area that day and by the end of our visit at Sage we were almost certain that it would be our venue. Nicky was an excellent events coordinator/manager. He provided us with a great tour of the facility. After the menu tasting we decided it was the place for our wedding.

The venue:
Great view to the mountains and the Ocean! It is next to the rose garden and many other great venues for the wedding portraits. We needed a few family rooms, and they offered us all the rooms we needed (three) two of them facing the fountain/pond. One then was so beautiful we took our family portraits there.

The food:
We had the Fit for Chef menu. All of the courses were excellent! I loved the lobster gnocchi and the steak was superbly done. The fish was a tad on the dry side, but with a big group maybe it is a challenge to get that perfect. The lava cake was amazing too!

The service:
The staff at Sage was really accommodating to our needs, and they are flexible. We were able to drop things the night before, which was great! Nicky was always attentive to my questions and tried his best to make things happen. We had request to bring food from outside (pig roast - Chinese tradition) and they were super accommodating.

We also had a surprise band. We were able to arrange it too, as they had a space and curtains to hide them :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjL01e-ulqONTL1i3XC27qvJE5FCinXLD5QxbZ&fid=0x0:0x4272b6b37e601a30"],"When":"2018-8-28"}]

[{"Name":"Vincent Fong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUN4-jXCeHAeXVdr-sAbSQDzzVZ4qQ0z758FyNnNxpTxeA-aEqu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everything was packed neatly and they are very generous with the portions. The food was great and especially for the price. It's probably the most affordable sushi place on campus. I ordered #1 to go which was $12.95 before tax if I remember correctly (as of Oct. 8, 2024).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOank77KH0ZN3OqtoLCsXe-0VzK27LLBdl7gHEZ&fid=0x0:0x48535312e395315d"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Amity Chiang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJYIqhcYzNuOhGHtmQQKnKIbfu2MFgw-Oud25eme8BQJzg47A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is an OG and a hidden gem located in UBC Village‚Äôs International Food Court (downstairs).

I greatly appreciate the owners approach to their pricing to be accessible to students. There are a lot of food options on campus now but we always come back to Miyamae.

We love their Bento Box 1 (Chicken Teriyaki + California roll) & Box 2 (Beef Teriyaki + spicy tuna roll), each comes with miso soup, rice, salad and 3-piece tempura. Their food is consistently fresh and the rolls are made to order.

Box 1 is $12.95

[{"Name":"Ayla Panini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiwtVIpBtKGTSIlPRlXWoQjHmNImwpsGr8ajO3tXx2uHueUqE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"W deal, W service, W food. I came to use my $5 off birthday voucher and I got a mini byob for just under $10! Service was excellent and very fast, and the portion was perfect and filling. The poke scoop recommended by the guy serving me, spicy tuna, was as delicious as he said! Would definitely go again :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5edVch4DjYxWTXzuzRzQtc_Tmid0kZNIxkrLH&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Selina Zhou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdh_K07G_35WE1XQolPePKtbRPCS7etPd4GO37eQJrOR8PInDd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The place is packed during lunches, but everyone is still quite attentive if you ordered pick-up. The portions are quite generous, and even the mini bowl is enough to make sure you‚Äôre not hungry.

The salmon is my go-to pick, the shoyu is a must hahaha.

There is not much seating near the place itself, so definitely just sit on some bench if it‚Äôs not raining.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUL3NqhZUds1uCJFHjqiEfzEWo0vnCvKMwPjhe&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Nicole Villalon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvX-NXEAvIz9hfeDmCLJbpqDwAUM7ozgrgH4vZTSomKf59ULGv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"STEVE‚ÄôS POKE DOES IT AGAIN!!!
I‚Äôve eaten here 4 times so far and every single time the service has been phenomenal. Today‚Äôs experience, however, absolutely takes the cake.

I ordered a mini BYOB with one scoop of poke online, coming up to ~$15 after tax and tips. The people at checkout were very attentive and made sure to check in and let me know my order was being prepared, and would be ready in a couple minutes. And then, the girl preparing my poke misread my order‚Ä¶ and accidentally made me a large instead of a mini BYOB!!! She apologized multiple times, but how could I complain? More poke! And when I let it slip my birthday had been a week ago, the staff offered to throw in an iced tea, free of charge!

The poke was delicious, the service was stellar, and staff‚Äôs kindness absolutely made my day. I‚Äôll be happy to visit Steve‚Äôs Poke again very soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmSF-4CMT-TmWd3-H-5XYvs2169hWwMLVwRpNj&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Tresa Horney","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlCxWd5ESmqb9bOtTVn1nxYHpHQadHnSQ3MsNKRjtwrjVvD0jPDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Easy to order, friendly service, and a great meal. Pleased to have a vegetarian option. I‚Äôll return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPy2Vjy3vWoV_UVTxuZk8COaNosX0DfibJOIhOD&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"$20 for this poke bowl, comes with 4 different choices of fish/poke, and any number of free ‚Äútoppings‚Äù. The rice is ‚Äúregular‚Äù white rice, not really flavored with mirin or anything. The fish come with sauce, but I should have asked for extra sauce on it because it had either dried up a bit or soaked into the rice. Considering the other choices around UBC, this is probably pretty good value for money.

I ordered takeout, but they have a few seats inside and outside if you prefer. The street currently has a bunch of (summer) construction, though.

They frequently have promo discounts on their site, but if you order on their online platform, there‚Äôs a mandatory $0.25 bag fee.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMG5oLw7BBFbNinAOxoTystwMC33r4z7vTCasRg&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Hari haran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIiG04_8rXv0XFEGQSVtxLwFR51JdEUoQ099gTHIIYGUB0FAw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Edit: just picked up a poke bowl and it seems the folks at the store have overdone it with soy sauce (???) this is not good. See picture attached

People are less responsive for pickup orders. Not sure why.

But mostly, Some of the best poke you can eat in Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5Fa39-wPyW-gxFrFm-dQJx5a5nADo4V_MO6ES&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"Vitalie Veclici","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVn8kycEuyvgu8wcx5Mpwijp97INeeCs7xxytZNIaEQ_HzZHS2yeg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Steve‚Äôs Poke Bar delivers delicious, fresh poke bowls with a variety of high-quality ingredients and customizable options. The staff is friendly and attentive, ensuring a pleasant experience from start to finish. While the food is top-notch, the interior could benefit from some updates to enhance the overall dining atmosphere. With a bit more attention to the ambiance, Steve‚Äôs has the potential to become one of the top poke spots in Vancouver. Still, a fantastic choice for poke enthusiasts looking for great service and tasty bowls.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Erika W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXk-zmliLlm5bIplSxpmOCgffchZEiqu1WLJ9rhI9Bc-N96TAwesQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food quality is fantastic and the portions are extremely satisfying. The staff were super friendly and patient as I chose my ingredients for my bowl. Not from Vancouver but when I do come back, I‚Äôm going to be sure to revisit this place because it is a stand out even among the fancy dine in places I went to. Thank you so much and until next time all the best.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"An okay place to get a healthy and filling meal in this part of campus. Generally fresh ingredients, tasty bowls, and options for customization whether you go with one of the set bowls or build your own. Prices are fair for the portion size. Depending on who you get, service can be cheerful and reasonably quick or extremely sluggish. I've never had any serious problem with the food quality here, but some ingredients seem to not be as fresh or as high-quality as I've come to expect from poke (again, never had anything that was bad, but it's just missing that pristine touch). I also find that some of the flavour combinations are kind of odd, like the pesto-marinated tofu and pineapple or very guac-like avocado scoops. But I still generally find their bowls satisfying if you know how to pick your ingredients. The Main and the Cali are my favourite standard bowls. Although I like the personalization of just building a bowl, I wish you could get more than 3 toppings on a regular size. Service is iffy sometimes. Mostly nice people, but there are a few staff members that don‚Äôt seem to know what‚Äôs going on.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvNc8KhypRHAPOkrXn7ZvHo4XlMGwiMt5snuGO&fid=0x0:0xe8a0dead744320d8"],"When":"2022-3-27"},{"Name":"Max C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJv1TrjuIfxkeVrA_UPRCLq7NLIMbGYJSP-J-XbBeeEof06=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Just go to Steve‚Äôs. Always order them whenever I go and am greeted by welcoming staff members.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOm84TuBZ6_Hanftej6Q9Qh1oBHQJWYDM1JM6Vk&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2024-6-9"},{"Name":"No MSG No Garlic Foodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-PVOn6GcWxsKb-qqVJDTqvJ5rfua5QVuFocwcMF-ZRwuEIPLm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The points for this review is purely for the pleasure of sitting outside on a 2nd floor patio overlooking expansive area of green lawn, gardens and forest. I am also grateful for the non-metal chairs!
It was 27¬∞. We've just been cooling in the forests of the beautiful UBC Botanical Garden and not quite ready to drive back to the city. Westward Ho at the UBC Golf Course came up on my Google search for brunch. Their patio picture was the deciding factor. Since it was nearly Happy Hour, the pub wasn't crowded and we were able to get a table in the impressively big patio. Not sure if it would be equally impressive had it been a really sunny day. We'd have to check that out another time. On this cloud day, the patio was very bright ‚Äì almost to the point where I have to put on my sun glasses.
As for the food, we had a hard time choosing: fresh fish and chips, fish sandwich, Beyond Beef burger, all day breakfast, etc. I ordered a Club House with multigrain yam fries, my companion ordered fresh Cod and Chips. The bread in my Club House was dried out, the sandwich did not look as scrumptious as the one with sour dough presented to the table next to us. My sandwich was too 'orderly', the chicken did not spill out of the sandwich like the one I saw earlier. I enjoyed the cod fish though ‚Äì very fresh and not over battered. So, I guess I ordered the wrong thing! I liked the choice of using vinegar on coleslaw instead of mayo. A decent size coleslaw for a more balanced meal. MSG? For a few hours afterwards, I was very thirsty, but did not get the usual sickly feeling from eating MSG. So, not sure what was in the food that caused my tongue to feel so dry.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjr8zNCvHQWWPDvIvCsF-m8vfK6OTg8xyORYzH&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2021-8-2"},{"Name":"Azi Jahan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVoCqSGFWxXVxJxNnyUrYmJjWJKEtREeG-G0RXpmBRv8kbELxEL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"For gulf lovers for sure, it's a well-known place.

Beautiful location and viewü§åüèª
Delicious brunch
So kind and supportive staff

It's a peaceful weekend brunch location if you are looking for a calm weekend's brunchü§©","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4NKPC_4N4_VYCzznfOGLy34Q4VWIecJtPF0BY&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2022-7-29"},{"Name":"Paul Rogers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-2DEuMMhV7vJRExrjz5OPFG99Ya8EpWqhlLnkXnZqRJpDqw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My family went here with a few other people for dinner.  Nice staff (hence the 2 stars) but the food was very disappointing.  Out of the 3 in my family, none of us enjoyed our meals.  I had the fish tacos which were bland and mushy. [{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sandwich is a good size and lots of thin layers of meat: I got the medium Hat Trick on wheat, and it‚Äôs more than enough for lunch.

Cookie is pretty tiny, though.

If you order online, be sure to customize the sandwich to add veggies in.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOJUjYVedl9wR8yjoTYL8wKGYJPJhKyi0x8r4N&fid=0x0:0xbc372dfd791dd8c4"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Okay, here we go. Firehouse Subs. Wow!! They‚Äôre so good. First of all, the best staff ever at the UBC branch‚Äîthanks for all the hard work there. We ordered for the first time and got two subs: one Montreal smoked meat and one NewYork Steamer, and we loved them. We loved them so much that we ordered again the next day‚Äîone Steak & Cheese and one Pepperoni Pizza Meatball‚Äîand again, we loved those. We‚Äôre probably going to keep ordering until we find our favorite. So far, we like these four in this order: Montreal Smoked Meat, Steak & Cheese, New York Steamer, and then Pepperoni Pizza Meatball. All of them are 7.5/10 or higher, so they‚Äôre really close. The pepperoni one is at the bottom of the list because the marinara sauce was a bit overwhelming, making it hard to really get to the pepperoni and meatball.

We also ordered the chili bowl and garlic bread. The garlic bread is nice‚Äînormal garlic bread. You could get creative and make it a bit more interesting, but I kind of liked it with their special sauce. But the chili bowl is on another level‚Äîso good.

As you can guess, I‚Äôm definitely going to keep trying them again and again. Hope they keep up the good quality. ü•ñ üöí üî•

[Update, 2024, Aug 15]
Ordered two new subs:
1. Hat Trick Sub: A bit too much barbeque sauce, if you like bbq sauce a lot go for it. Enjoyed it. 7/10
2. Smokehouse Beef & Cheddar Brisket: again a bit too smoky for me. I enjoyed the beef and cheddar combination a lot tho. 7/10
Still everything is great and they're 5/5. üî•","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNthhpGT-IdxtuSBJ3GBYDhSBF10nfABiTaR73v&fid=0x0:0xbc372dfd791dd8c4"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Alexandra Rousseau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCc1VRoWPX9lI6oLLlSyZp1wtcpy95ye2Jq395pgPsfvG22Z41=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Quick service and delicious sub. Lots of sandwich options, and large portions. I got the size medium, and I would say that there‚Äôs almost triple the meat of a Subway sub, would recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMoSQpMVsainpAjodr6k3jnXld5Pk-Px0cMCsHi&fid=0x0:0xbc372dfd791dd8c4"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKf1RSg3_-AU0iu6cewVgjwGYoJmZNxdRNJCv62pXrCH7QK-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The presentation on this sandwich is amazing, it's restaurant quality. The flavor is, all I can say about this the best way to describe it, is this is a sexy sandwich! The staff were wonderful, talking to them I believe that they are treated very well by the owners. Which shows, cuz if you treat your staff father treat the customers well and they did, and they were good at their job as well. They all noticed when I walked in and when I left. The only thing I should mention, is I ordered a tuna (now I'm not sure why it wasn't on the board, but unfortunately there are some adjustments that could be made to the recipe. It might be, because when I enjoyed the sandwich, it was very wet, which tells me that when it was taken out of the can the fluid wasn't drained. So the Mayo is that was added was diluted a lot, Celeste liquid more mayo, as well the sandwich does need mustard for a tuna, and some black pepper would be ideal and a little bit of salt to bring out the flavor. )which was not on the board and I nearly walked out, except for the fact that I decided to ask just in case. So I think that listing that on the board would be great, cuz now I actually wonder what other hidden sandwiches you might have that are not listed. I will definitely be going back, and I don't even live in the city! A massive portion well worth the money, and I don't even know what it cost because I didn't care I was excited to find a place that my look and smell was really fresh.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHOmq62IGYnTZA43FR0ZLo308gMqm-CpD6eL9z&fid=0x0:0xbc372dfd791dd8c4"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Javidd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxIKHySek0FG53i0J4L70VrPkQxUMcSPGhMR3Qfp-EChdJEQU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Horrible sandwiches. [{"Name":"Seonjae Im","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIt1GgA1qP_NjMCQxVFgkQjulbXGtYGtfVP5U0gEJ-yvUVuQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Super cheap compared to rising economy.
It helped me survive most of my sophomore year.
Food here are okay but it is reasonably cheap.
Tables are not cleaned often so you have to bear with it or get takeout.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHdTccy2Q7cHtwZI9Xc9nGh1oxqRiOgFGxFSJt&fid=0x0:0x690511f5e60f3a95"],"When":"2023-3-7"},{"Name":"H W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKiEtu-Pfzzd7vMmnC1lRzmwYGQeuaGu_8hpE004heAd4NBbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Great location for some cheap and diverse eats. The place looks somewhat run down but has some pretty good deals for international cuisine (Chinese food, sushi, pho, falafel, etc.).

Their hours are a lifesaver, helps for late night meals. Staff are generally friendly and helpful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFAhHhNAAdpg0bYtqVDcCQqpyEHK7e1kohBHaK&fid=0x0:0x690511f5e60f3a95"],"When":"2019-10-12"},{"Name":"Max Hsu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLu1jhFG8wW5p1LMrMk4Cj7Gyqq2DzrOgApiEw96NN7dKOuDw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is little cheaper than in campus. And the amount of food is pretty large, if you are hungry, you can have a hearty meal there!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlHGpUAimV7S52WSxtJgq9a3eyz6vGGta6rKYo&fid=0x0:0x690511f5e60f3a95"],"When":"2019-7-15"},{"Name":"Daniel Z.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQPWk1igWiScMJLvbEfOGbn_E-SvYzWdnJ-_3R9XXD4Q9XGO0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cheapest, most worth it food on campus IMO. You MUST try Donair Town, My Home Cuisine, and Want Want Hot & Spicy House (don't customize your own pot unless you want to spend more money). My only problem with this place is that it is hella dirty and I think the janitors legit clean it once per day because there is always a time that the trash cans are full and used containers are stacked like jenga.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dean Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLvm11HIAG3Fuf8Xoq7yKAy3cehpHvdsQUqZ7KAGt3RTRQWkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is really a lifesaver. Cheap and delicious!
a quick comparison to on campus food: At Nest, you get rice+3 items for 13 dollars. In this place, you get rice/fried rice/noodle + 3 items for 9.5 dollars.

Taste is great as well, only downside is the the messiness and the lack of tables during peak hours, but still a good place place overall","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shekoofeh Azizi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWmVXX_fZYwJ9yhvcqQ9wSWDiE3BKS-9WvrgxClrWs1anQJPK1kzA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"They have good, fresh food with reasonable price for students. There are  halal options, and a  wide variety of soup, noodles and so on. However, the  area is too smelly and unclean, and kinda too old, and seriously needs a reconstruction! They don't have good air conditioning, so the moment you enter the area, you will loss your appetite.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nicola K√ºng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzwXf37j9kyhMYVC3sQVcq3Cg4-PTpSPUG28VvgRVi89mpPXOyRA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"After coming here a couple of times and being quite pleased with the food, I‚Äôve recently had a very bad experience with the Chinese ‚Äûmy home cuisine‚Äú. The pork meat has a weird and unpleasant taste to it and was of bad overall quality. This experience coincided with what some people had suggested beforehand, but which I could never really comprehend. Now I know better.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rahul Gupta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_G1LKo0ImsYGUsKsWD-P5_uazEPhMEJlxlgcUPjFkkmqE1q8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you are looking for something spicy on UBC campus I bet you this is the best place to eat some spicy Chinese food or Mediterranean. My home Cuisine is one of the best shops here which gets very busy in the afternoon time. Also there is a sushi shop which has a good variety","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Chipotle Mexican Grill
address: 6025 University Blvd C.R.U #2, Vancouver, BC V6T 1Z1
descriptions: Fast-food chain offering Mexican fare, including design-your-own burritos, tacos & bowls.
about: [{"id":"dining_options","name":"Dining options","options":[{"name":"Lunch","enabled":true},{"name":"Dinner","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true}]}]
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Jordan Bates","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfiSlogqPxTBz7X041V4ZcubJ3xk4d-ypWA52tlZknobCbzNR5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I‚Äôm from the U.S. originally so I‚Äôm no stranger to Chipotle and have been to several other locations in Vancouver, but this one is by far the worst. I‚Äôve been here a couple times now with friends and the service staff are completely indifferent/unfriendly, the place seems disorganized, and it does not feel remotely comparable to any other Chipotle location I‚Äôve been to. The portion sizes are not consistent from visit to visit and it seems as though the staff have taken some creative liberties as to how portioning and presentation should look. Every time my friends and I have visited this location, we have had to ask for more lettuce. They sprinkle it in the corner like it‚Äôs a garnish (picture attached was after asking for more). With the other toppings (corn, cheese) as well, they sprinkle minuscule portions with their fingers instead of using a standardized measuring device. I‚Äôve only been during lunch rush, but I feel they start heavily skimping so that they have to do less prep or worry about changing containers mid rush. They do not follow ‚Äúfifo‚Äù procedures (first-in, first out) and my friend and I (who both have experience in the food service industry) watched them on multiple occasions just dump new prep on top of older prepped toppings instead of switching containers. It‚Äôs about half the portion of food you‚Äôd get at any other Chipotle, which is a shame since you‚Äôre paying the same $17-$20 price tag. Seeing more experienced individuals in food service or service management at this location would be nice, in place of the youthful and evidently lacking in training/experienced staff at present. My friends and I have been here 3-4 times now but I don‚Äôt think we will continue as it stands. Hopefully changes are made so it‚Äôs more like every other Chipotle out there!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWSZEiO33TrzJ28Rpi7SrKJEuFe807cpuShEC1\u0026fid=0x0:0xa21f97d8c0582245"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"Ella Bender","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWy_6ygK4WcuTSytOxPzocdO2ji3fAN1LtRbmZJjQICX--PpR4v=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Got a bowl but it feels only half full. The service felt super rushed, even when I was the only person in the store. I had to ask for more lettuce and there's still barely any. I didn't bother asking for more rice and chicken but I definitely should have. Also did the prices get increased?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7u31reHHCAIzpoh02TTXFGSt_s4NUiGxCHLpu\u0026fid=0x0:0xa21f97d8c0582245"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Tracy S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2KIvjxx-0xSdgN7X_lDT6LFt5P_11tk9uyS8O7df2vE0ddIQt=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Please gimme lettuce bro‚Ä¶ this looks so sad. Why is the portion size always so small compared any other chipotle?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPrn-QB4qjtpmSwMtPKVES8kTtcXK0Iz9T1N_7O\u0026fid=0x0:0xa21f97d8c0582245"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Jake.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXi8ZWMWuMxlnpD5_maiEkPwNBNscsPle1pfRNmmb4_cshcMp9K=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Chipotle is known for its quickness and portion sizes and this restaurant is horrible at both. Twice in a row I have pre-ordered online only to have to wait 15 minutes beyond what was expected and all that to have shockingly small proportions. It amazes me that every other location has reasonable portion sizes and yet the one location near broke college kids skimps out? The restaurant is understaffed and proportions are absurdly small, hopefully management sees all these awful reviews and makes some change.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"gan ning","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVMjHOBXHKN8Tphl-H0LL997Q3L2sNhXFNNl90TwErPr42122A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I've been a regular at the Chipotle in my hometown for several years now. As a loyal customer, I was hoping to be able to work here as a UBC student. However, my interview got cancelled less than an hour before it was set to be held which is so disrespectful of my time and effort to commute and prepare. I was willing to overlook this location being constantly out of ingredients because of the high volume of customers but now it seems that this place is simply poorly managed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"William Cai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLowDo9VdBFQi300S4kjpXRwZghe-KspAmuoouT66ufKVCRug=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered a few items and the staff made three severe mistakes during the process, requiring them to remake the items. My order was not particularly complicated, no extras or particulars. It was simply two different items. I made an effort to speak more clearly after the first mistake but the problem persisted.\n\nOn the last error I gave up and just accepted what they did for my order. The staff are rushing and not listening to what you say or communicating with one another.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Naveen Vyas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUl5DsxUTAxLucgUkR0v5hbzzOHSqSGKEmCoXNgreAi5K8TUmg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I‚Äôd give zero if I can. Store managers are extremely rude. Food quality is terrible. Servers don‚Äôt follow any hygiene standards. I‚Äôve loved chipotle always. Not this one. Terrible store. Was excited when store opened on campus but less than a month, service went poor to horrible.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ethan Mori","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKBtAMECI5v89ED2E2A9QviFpArWVUkidkTh-g_swqyfFZmGw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Staff don't check the pickup window so you can be standing there for ages while you can see your food on the shelf. HUGE inconsistencies in portion sizes, sometimes you get half as much as the other time you ordered, and generally unfriendly staff.","Images":null,"When":""}]
