user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Lisa Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2hRhOWIQf2ren7p1R3F9BVnb3q6vzlyk-JCc_U7cm7KJ7rH11fg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"i came to this restaurant starving after my afternoon classes. the service was pretty quick, we got our order around 10 mins of ordering. however the beef noodle was very disappointing, the beef tasted stiff and flavourless, the soup just tasted like soy sauce. The vegetables seemed undercooked. The texture of the noodles was fine. Overall, 3/10, was expecting better for the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOerFh-ScT0Avl732B3GQc_JRRKBuTvCqZjOmnU&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Henry Hu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOiklZbH_t_aRkBtZKTm3pDAeGGVqs_fJp0WPZNs_8inyrTWQy9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here with my aunt and her two young kids (we are Chinese).  Having seen poor reviews, we weren't expecting much, but the dinner was surprisingly very good!

The service was slow at the beginning even though there were few people there -- even after 10 minutes or so we still hadn't been served water or tea.  It was a cold night and the restaurant was also chilly.  The server was very friendly and spoke both Chinese and English.

The appetizers were fairly good (spicy beef tendon and beef slices).  I had the beef rolls (very good) and spicy beef noodles (very good).  The dumplings were ok.  The scallion pancakes were not very good.

At the end, it was close to closing time and she gave us some free mango shaved ice which tasted amazing!  Very fluffy with a subtle sweetness.  We will return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnk7CIbwaPs_5-VtCw29sqwvLTOj_7hFEQDruC&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"Katie Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIjMysay4-FQVEPUnU2iivCs6D7x1kzSWlLVk1hwpWr3ttr5es=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went at a time when there were almost no others at the restaurant. Pretty quiet meal aside from a few shouts by the staff (to each other?), which I think were instructions. Atmosphere was fine, normal restaurant vibes. Decent decor. Nice ceiling lights.

Service was fine, although I can see why some might see it as curt. She came by and refilled my tea without being asked, which is more than I can say for many asian restaurants nearby.

I ordered A3, and found the portions quite reasonable. The noodles are expensive but I think it's partially "ubc campus tax". They did put quite a bit of beef so I don't feel like the prices are all that unreasonable given the serving size and the location.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOCR7J2-cBxj_MhFTA2O0HRjFvAoVseKHkoYN8&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2023-10-23"},{"Name":"Sartaj Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1doLfhIpPIdYO53EoD_63mHYE3jrQc1kxM-CAvFcju93a6Z1xPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Got takeaway, the brisket was really good! Really simple but satisfying meal- was slightly pricy though (menu with prices posted in the photos). Service was fine but I can see how some people may comprehend it as a bit too curt.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOm_WNO5NXyIgHBbu7z5LTIAqt8lrxTtLO88Ta3&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2021-2-10"},{"Name":"Sunny Hsieh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKn7JfczJPilvGMT4s7fYXLEV9lFRbn9veIkFCwiRyDnuZfxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We order classic Taiwanese dishes here. The food taste average, but the dining environment is quite noisy since the stuffs talk so loud and don‚Äôt care what customers think.
If you‚Äôre looking for quiet dining, I suggest you order to take out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXHF2vu1lLnJY4nrIl9jXR3Nco4mSagrnqGZF6&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2021-7-25"},{"Name":"Ryan Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJg51dkTiELfwGSC3YeGg0Cqc2FbwTcp56uR5oMbjvMxs9-kgt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Came here with high hopes after being a happy customer of their West Van location that closed down, but was extremely disappointed with the terrible service and mediocre food.
Upon arriving, the restaurant was silent except for the yelling coming from the kitchen. The lady who brought us to our table didn't say a word to us, and left immediately after pointing to our table. The way she spoke, in both Chinese and English, seemed like she was upset that we were eating there and we were doing her an inconvenience.
Despite being only one out of two tables there, it took around 15 minutes for our order to be taken. Again, the lady sounded annoyed.
The soup was disappointingly bland - I had to add lots of chili oil and soy to make the broth taste of something at all. The noodles were overcooked and mushy, and the beef shank was tough and overly salty.
It's such a shame to see what Chef Hung has become, as it was once my favourite restaurant in Vancouver.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"nataku04","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_SbO1MAS8FGX9Q1u4rgyMAxUXyAbqpEXgjPOqBTAPYYTV2-Ed=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I have no experience of the restuarant itself since I go it delivered. I'd say its not that great, apologies for the semi eaten meal before taking photos. I was just starving, first meal of the day after a 20hour fast. The noodles are a decent texture yet being so thin. The tiny beef brisket chunks were tender enough but so salty. The broth would have been good its light but tasted watered down.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5ilPwOOcgkxQZCf75Ib1kTLwfreuMBYb5gUC2&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2022-8-30"},{"Name":"Eric","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiQoGWet_oXsOFHl9IApfn5oX44S-A0_Tz_vgzgQxRW9yw_IDK=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Horrendous experience. I've always despised this place for its terrible service, inconsistent quality, and mandatory tipping on takeout.
But today crossed the line‚Äîraw chicken. To make matters worse, the server literally shoved the chicken into the box with her hands because it didn‚Äôt fit.
Absolutely unacceptable.
I'd rather starve / eat Neptune than eat here.","Images":null,"When":""}]

The lamb shank was tender and came with a ton of delicious sides. we also really enjoyed the seafood skillet. The atmosphere was so lovely here and I will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiJHdLuTbprlD8c6BxSDXT1aGnAK05UBhTekN0&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-12-12"},{"Name":"Hessam Dehqani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9_xTs6k7X3RgR-GYtpDaVcRhHZYvAkCWBCnak0FYwr9rofA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was a symphony of delight and pleasure dancing on my taste buds. Extravagant amounts of seafood in the seafood fettuccine. Sauce was perfect. The Chocolate Lava Cake was the perfect amount of fluffiness and chewy-ness all at once. The cake was the slightest bit warm and the giant scoop of ice cream served on the side was not too cold, making it the perfect combo. The friendly staff will make you feel at home.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJ5stowouGaXpUeYE6xdnYk5tTw2UAhlZkDP0B&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Sarah H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW92qwsfx_pIiwt2DlNeJL21vsXcUQcWFFO0CrTDqGo7aSuEtvR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We loved this Greek spot in Kits! We chose to share a range of appetizers- all were delicious, including the four olives with focaccia, the mezzo trio with the best pita, calamari, and spanakopita. We also had the yam fries- so perfectly hot and crispy. Everything came out quite quickly and fresh. The service was friendly and delicious. Definitely recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOboR7reOpDZb_p0TsC_cSRvUDH0o3Bk4IppOyh&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Lister Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWbNvO55wOzkDRxCcJ-fMoCcdWyut5hlx-H_zUreRnwso9_V0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyed lunch special with beet argula salad, lamb souvlaki, and ice cream. Everything made carefully and plated beautifully. Yummy salad and tender flavourful lamb. Lovely server and ample seating","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvil2aWBw9xvb1WEocpbSTu5qJKwNogPEJmVBG&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Isaac Trenton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcuG3EvRc-AAeKCn9g2ZfMQnNodo8xx3TwArbSevKXywtb2BIA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A wonderful experience with family. Would recommend for both friendly outings and special occasions. Great food, personal service, clean ambiance. Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMO--eXeeKqPcjAD_zKFBygtnPBJ296t7XWlMGx&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"andy a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ7Y7rwHyjfulEA1YHdfgv-xt7-eGezTRedst5phEBEmPsbXg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful experience, tried the four olives with the deep fried olives. If you enjoy olives I highly recommend them, you won't be disappointed.

The lamb shoulder was fork tender, and the Navajo bread was crispy fluffy and soft all at once.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPL8yvDzQrWpheoXTb2m_LsnPGF3AcaCpmykrT&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Yourstruly T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdAW_3mT95dnmWSH1jV5DzTjAp8VnRyKu5igqgCkvt_l-2XR77=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of dining at this delightful Mediterranean gem, and the experience was nothing short of extraordinary. The ambiance exuded jazzy vibes, creating a perfect backdrop for a cozy and homely atmosphere.

The moment I stepped in, the inviting warmth enveloped me, making it feel like I was enjoying a meal in the comfort of someone elses' home. The restaurant's decor and lighting contributed to the overall cozy vibes, setting the stage for a memorable dining experience.

The main course portions were generously sized. Each bite was a burst of deliciousness. Appies were so flavourful. For the dine-out menu, I really liked the Mushroom Arancini and the Garlic Prawns. Ugh!! So warm/flavourful..

A special shoutout to the owner or manager, Amar, whose friendly and attentive demeanor added a personal touch to the entire evening. His passion for the cuisine and commitment to customer satisfaction were evident in every aspect of the dining experience.

The potatoes, a standout side dish, were a delightful surprise with their sourly delicious taste. I couldn't get enough of them. The chicken skewers were another highlight ‚Äì juicy, flavorful, and a true testament to the culinary expertise of the kitchen.

In conclusion, this Mediterranean restaurant is a must-visit for anyone seeking a jazzy, cozy, and homey dining experience. With mouthwatering dishes and a warm welcome from Amar, it's a culinary haven that I can't wait to revisit during patio season as well!!

xoxo,
@yourstrulyfoodie","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8hxYl3J7Guv437YZS_Uj8FCdYhvd9RqmOTMS1&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-1-16"},{"Name":"Daniel Silver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJawI80c4qwvuA-pWmht_nhIypwFKNS8vUDHnZIepoqs0gJvft7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I enjoyed everything we ordered. Portions were decent but not overly so. Definitely worth trying if you like Mediterranean food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODYFoK7X1vlNRzms1wWtQdlB7xQK729D7csvia&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-1-3"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jeffrey Cheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuvw0DoMq0pOe2JGvzQ4U1FjBGerEQ4O70pk3YVGChUNSu7g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Update: I sent an email 2 months ago after the owner's review and have NOT received a reply at all. They have not done anything nor kept their promise. Totally soured by the customer service and have adjusted that to 1 star. Absolutely frustrated to see that happening and will never go back to the restaurant again.

The pasta was okay, nothing special and the pizza was awful, so watery","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAiQ5ZLOeaIrS5F737cTKWhpPO1WHu_H6eZ73O&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Wii Games","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1LF1yLZYvfPxybsCpHOF5AtzGVIeAoFgQLne7csT7MMJt7gY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Considering their pizzas are priced at a premium (average of 25 dollars,) you would expect their pizzas to be of higher quality. The toppings taste fresh, but the pizzas are extremely runny and the dough is very chewy even for Neapolitan style pizza. The crust lacks the air and lightness of other places. I also noticed that they don't use any wood in their oven, which just doesn't achieve the same flavor profile.

In terms of the service, i have come to this place a few times and seen the waiters talking and not noticing myself or other guests that come in at times.

The atmosphere overall is not bad, but personally i feel as though the place has an industrial feeling and is not the most welcoming .","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brad Snelling","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEo3ECglbJcC95bDjcm377gDXh3jMd9KEP9ANqJRBVc9D4SrM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Thank you Maddie for the great service and the birthday cake‚Ä¶and thanks to chefs Shaq and Yuriko for the tasty food (the Il Bastardo and Salami e Funghi pizzas and the pasta cream pasta were amazing!).  I will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNB5_ERDFOPMNUkHdMilCQ_UHzkC088WqZp8ggb&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Eve C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3TRd28YHMD0xZgG9Qff6WuaVQUBD8KHHFSJUDtDhJtE0o6w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was really excited to hear that Nicli has reopened in Wesbrook. I used to go to the gastown location all the time and was sad when they closed. I heard they are under new ownership, so we were weren‚Äôt sure what to expect. Luckily, it was still just as delicious as I remember üòã

We came for lunch and ordered four pizzas to share amongst 6 people. It was the perfect amount of food and we left very satisfied. They also have a lunch menu with slightly smaller pizzas and pasta options. The pizzas were full of quality ingredients and incredibly delicious. Our server was so friendly and made sure we were well taken care of. Will be coming back more often ü©∑","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alysia Duemler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOP2WaoVuXuPDA2rQrEDkqLAVmEa-LLcH53nj472C_ni_q4VtISQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Such a charming neighbourhood Italian restaurant with many gluten-free and vegetarian options, thankfully. It was the best pizza I‚Äôve had in Vancouver, the cocktails were refreshing, the server was friendly, funny and attentive, and the atmosphere was pleasant. Had a nice little date there and would recommend. It‚Äôs nice to be able to sit outside, too. The prices are also fair.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcjHM66qrYK1NntlYCYUZ5aePNW-D9gzlCt-Gq&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2023-8-25"},{"Name":"Michael Moriarity","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNhkYaB9zjlkkl74OBPcplO2QslT6bqh419yvto-fc4bLKxsqAKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This local pizza location in UBC Westbrook Mall invites the pizza and Italian food scene customer for a fine tasting menu..we chose the Salimi & Fungi pizza and the Bolognese pasta‚Ä¶there was a warm welcome and we appreciated the many items on the menu‚Ä¶there was plenty of parking in the area..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNx9nIE0qOANzuFm6Ak0SYk8JNr2vubnJicmWxq&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2024-2-27"},{"Name":"Ray Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3wj8Ne3ngI4eg9ouEU6zPmvERlQuudbckz4ma4Vg6pfYrsWM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The service was excellent. There was only one server and one chef but the two were very efficient. We really enjoyed the Napoli style pizza, and the fresh pasta had an interesting fusion sauce with a mixture of miso and carbonara. The guanciale in the carbonara sauce was rich and and full of flavour. The pasta was perfectly al dente and picked up the sauce nicely.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_SKvNF7awsi_PmQuHT87A8CDKGDP9aZlr2pKR&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"Ishita Malik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWV5NuG1NBDfsD_WLq2-zLuV8LgB51UWdsUfOaqy47D5rsrTXb5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went there 3-4 times for some authentic Italian food.
Was so glad to see they had so many vegan options, gluten free, dairy free. And even said they can substitute any of the ingredients for vegan.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFFFm767jOmR1P2iGRESAiZf8Zoovic4TFcWxj&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2023-8-30"}]

[{"Name":"Miyuki Food","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIefbmBJIFd8vluRG1CtvO_cHUxsRdwtm3bVobO6E-icLpG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food comes very fast, portion size seems smaller than before. And there‚Äôs only 1 type of baked pasta a day (it was fine though). Garlic toast was fine, the salad dressing was great!! Pasta and garlic toast for 11 dollars is alright. UBC cinnamon bun was tasty but hard, maybe it was from the day before. I want to try the roast chicken leg next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTB5iX6q9Xe2yx-tVSbqgor_6fP9oxY5cREcs&fid=0x0:0x1edd3bffb80ccd29"],"When":"2024-3-25"},{"Name":"April Kang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpjudrVHdeiNcmDBFdIqiSbVKaOOs-ms-BSD_TFGabSaEbLhkK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The server was busy cleaning and didn‚Äôt take my order right away. So I was waiting for her to finish her cleaning until she can finally take my order. It was a little bit awkward, but no big deal. Then I ordered a cup of earl grey latte. It came super hot with no lid or sleeve cup holder. I only had one free hand to hold the drink. While holding the drink and walking to a table, I spilled and burned myself. I don‚Äôt want to complain, but I think the server really needs some safety training regarding hot drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMvMzTQlQO5LNRU9akNZ9JACjxxTMjIqf6AQtZ&fid=0x0:0x1edd3bffb80ccd29"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I seem to remember the pasta here being better‚Ä¶ I had the Alla Norma today for the first time in a long while and was disappointed to get a stereotypical university cafeteria meal. The pasta sauce was fine and there were lots of veggies, so the dish likely would have been decent if it was cooked properly, but the pasta and vegetables were over-cooked and mushy, presumably from sitting in a hot-holding unit for who knows how long. The garlic bread was soaked and then some in butter. There was enough pooled in the nooks of the bread that I could just tip the bread over and pour it off. It‚Äôs not like the food was phenomenal before, but I thought it was good enough for a quick-service cafe, but this was just lazy.
The baked goods are still the same as you get at other UBC cafes, which I‚Äôm mostly a fan of. I find that the decaf espresso in drinks has kind of a burnt taste; it‚Äôs alright in lattes, but I had it as an americano today and it wasn‚Äôt really worth it for me.
On the upside, the value is decent. The pastas and flatbreads are heartier fare than you‚Äôll find at most of the coffee shops (UBC-owned or not) around campus, and my pasta and (big) cookie today came out to about $14 total. The service is usually friendly enough and the space is nice. They have dine-in plates and mugs but you need to specifically request them - they will not ask you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9ttobxFHARwLEw1f2WIn8975E7NUIg_MlZcrK&fid=0x0:0x1edd3bffb80ccd29"],"When":"2023-1-29"},{"Name":"Mahish Rajdev","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTK_NiWhybybG5OSaEBGMB4IPAR1DXKbumCjO5eTpafLGTEMHWRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Pure and absolute garbage! Service was diminishing and incredible rude, to then have a disgusting, cold pastry with a coffee  that was made with an old shot she had laying around! Didn't even cared to be sneaky.
Even tim's is better than this waste.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very good cafe to have a quick bite or takeout on campus! The prices are reasonable, and they have plenty of study space around as well. I highly recommend their barbecue chicken flatbread :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbNWTbTPrSs7CWgWXbrxFwMFw1NvcN3g4MK4Fm&fid=0x0:0x1edd3bffb80ccd29"],"When":"2023-10-25"},{"Name":"Fei B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUCSPR4b-Aju_3xzgvNmgK79_SKNPWkqhiQHmMJksqE4GdZMXE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"pretty decent food prices and they take UBC card here (at least when I last tried!)
I like the soups here as a filling and warming snack between my classes here. The pastas are pretty decent, but nothing special here. When I lived on campus, this was my favourite alternative to eating residence food!
The cashiers/servers here are honestly pretty unfriendly. Recently went and ordered soup and the lady didn't even look at me or say anything to me the entire time...not sure why.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ashley Xinyue C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIYz5MDYrhb1L2Ntf7XrdjiB5xemPws8aSeONm3ZAcvtG13jw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Really nice and juicy chicken but drip coffee is always cold","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Graham Douglas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIhuQ7JFTpvGa5zi_15HH4FFQnLd20ANHeexPlC6QR2fUoaZ3XVA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It‚Äôs a fine little cafe. This is now in the range of overpriced food and can no longer recommend eating at this place anymore","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Don K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUeMe3Z2Dwdjz2ebe9Hu9zPz3XZzwiZvAUP2ovxUEYWB0bHcVvHYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":""Unique" Japanese Dining Experience: Bones and Bad Attitudes

Just had the most "memorable" visit to a supposedly authentic Japanese restaurant in town, and let me tell you, it was quite an experience! üç£üôÑ

If you're a fan of eel, I suggest you bring your own toolkit for removing bones because this place apparently believes in quantity over quality. üêüüò£ I've never encountered so many bone spurs in a single dish before, talk about a challenge!

The icing on the cake was the lovely attitude of the staff, especially the charming individual I suspect to be the owner. üôÑüëé If you're looking for that authentic Japanese politeness and hospitality, well, you won't find it here. They seemed more interested in asserting their authority than making guests feel welcome.

So, if you're in the mood for a unique dining experience that defies traditional Japanese standards, this is the spot for you! Otherwise, I'd suggest looking elsewhere if you want genuine quality and respectful service. Save yourself the disappointment and bone-picking frustration. üö´üçΩÔ∏è","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNk3gNOOJ4m47LMTvIRz_vf85Wr33som8XgJzch&fid=0x0:0x21697c2ced69071"],"When":"2023-10-8"},{"Name":"Lizzie Hammond","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLl0YNeVEnImfaQfmG0d1UhPs7gS14GBRTsKOd1-_XmOq8j_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I work in the area and this is my go to place! Worth trying if you're on campus.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alan Small","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKzLTrQnMjgBTtPZOLeWQyRNTv1apzwevnTMT_sb6y76t2nQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Waygu bowl with garlic chili or Chipotle sauce are DELICIOUS!! It‚Äôs 95% rice with a scattering of veggies on top","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcVudMpDOhY9B2y_C_sgViVrukWpF7qWiWrEWM&fid=0x0:0x5e70cd9bc564b542"],"When":"2022-11-23"},{"Name":"Winslow S.E.M.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2HCkP_vVp2Ah2D073WW_0Q4z9QlqqiZnhsuCp9Y3NbhCMfRg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Literally the worst Japanese food on campus, food does not match their price.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Athena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvcHYZ9C3U9WsCVWuvPpPPrR6DNL7Ywhr5D3WdUVxhk1FF9arkwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Usually udon is a safe choice but not here. It was the saltiest udon and the beef was even saltier. I didn't even drink the soup and it was this salty. Not worth the $13. Would not come back again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Z.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQPWk1igWiScMJLvbEfOGbn_E-SvYzWdnJ-_3R9XXD4Q9XGO0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Saw someone review "overpriced with really small portions": pretty much yeah. Got me through my afternoon but I was still hungry AF. The teriyaki beef has the texture of chewed-up beef jerky. The flavour overall is on the most generic end of the donburi awesomeness scale.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jakob Schmidt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgeN-BI2FD7doKOsV7ge4lNAIG3A31zObtODjG6FxxvBa-92Hb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The best part of the meal was the miso soup.

I got the chicken donburi once and the dynamite rolls when I went back. The chicken was pretty much like subway processed chicken breast; pre frozen tasteless protein block. The sauce flavours were what ketchup packets are to a good tomato soup.

The sushi is kind of congealed. You could say it tastes like ‚Äúfridge‚Äù. Even the wasabi is bad. It‚Äôs fake fake wasabi.

The worst part is they charged me 10 bucks for it. To be honest I have a sushi place that‚Äôs probably a five minute walk from my house that charges 5 dollars for dynamite rolls. That‚Äôs half as much and fresh and absolutely delicious. I‚Äôm sorry but this place is a scam taking advantage of rushed students.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Max Hnatiuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBtN6HhvYUHvBHQU_xtNRl0s1V_J_Y2evW9fOX6UkEaHvn1REM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The Sushi is okay, but the rice is pretty low quality. The food is as expensive as eating at a restaurant but it's all served from a counter.  All the sushi is in togo boxes in a refrigerated area at the front; great for lunch on the go or in a rush. I personally did not enjoy the Ramen, I found it sweet and fairly small. I have yet to try the udon or poke but they appear to be popular options!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Very quick. Sushi and donburi are a bit expensive given the size. On occasion the rice in the sushi has been a little dry, but quality is usually okay. It seems you get a better value for your money with the udon.","Images":null,"When":""}]

It is almost as if she wanted my decision to be final, even though I wanted to test how expensive was the food I got. She didn't even show me how much it weighed, so I was really frustrated. I probably could've put the ingredients back, since I didn't tamper with it at all.

My final pricing was $18 dollars or so, which isn't that bad if the quality of the food is good. Thing is, the food wasn't anything special. [{"Name":"Chris Helgren","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMAlSlQnmQbIkMlcbNUhzxzkQe_i_pBwvNmCrJ1Wm7NdB_9U0R=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I hope this doesn't turn out to be a eulogy in the end, but I walked in for brunch and was told that this was the final day in this location at Jericho Beach. Apparently the landlord didn't want to extend the lease. I hope they find a new space in Vancouver. That said, the service was fantastic and deserving of a good tip. I loved the eggs Benedict with hashbrowns and pork belly, I forget what they called it but the food was memorable. And it's in a perfect location near the marina at Jericho so a great place for a walk to burn off the calories","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO44BS-QhzVwExBGdBt60sVJ7rQI5WrhEEj06X1&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Laurel Windover","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnEhLdsjZ16qCFrqZXUCMvuEzXtbI46OBVg6YSX7imdPsfZHYlwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I love the casual patio and the menu is priced right. I asked for the salmon burger as a salad instead of a burger and it was delicious!
The service was a bit slow the day I was there though. It didn‚Äôt appear to be too busy but we waited 40 minutes for our food and nobody came to do a quality check after we were served. In fact we didn‚Äôt see the server again until quite awhile after we were finished eating. That said, it‚Äôs a cute, casual spot in a great location and I would definitely go back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOg4RgddnYKK-Gjr0FDLECUohwzN85d-LhzmZqd&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-7-8"},{"Name":"Tina Fischer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_PBoE3UhL3iJ077dZx_qOA7mXIKHJuwtODDKop9ishOSiUuMS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Classic breakfast was awesome! Wonderful servers! Very fast and yummy! Even gave me a green onion when I asked for it!! Thanks for making my travel experience a good one. üòÉüëè‚úàÔ∏è","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoOAvh2tRDsfrjuEP1ANoDHO4Ncr2jLxqAl9Ga&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Ben Jefferson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBEOMkGOoEkxaChUtJDYIbi9DXvbFJ44f1Vjs7ERmTv1vlDzvJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super friendly staff. We had the salmon burger and vegan burger. Both were delicious - the salmon in particular. A low key local vibe. When we visited there were young kids, students, and old timers like us all enjoying the food. Good amount of seating outdoors and inside.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Silver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJawI80c4qwvuA-pWmht_nhIypwFKNS8vUDHnZIepoqs0gJvft7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I really wanted to like this place but unfortunately we didn't. Affordable prices but the food just let us down. I'm fine with basic but found the DICED burger lacking and the nachos were ruined by the corn chips. The fries, which were pretty good, and the biscuit were the only items I liked.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2IuCEopmqKeJmI6RJiYC1Jx0nJYLnmSgbhl5z&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-3-16"},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stumbling upon this establishment was like uncovering Vancouver's best-kept secret. Critics of its operations might miss the bigger picture: this place is not just a restaurant but a cornerstone of the DICED Culinary School, which champions affordable and sponsored culinary training programs. With very reasonable prices, especially for its locale, the ever-changing menu keeps the dining experience fresh and exciting. The patio and the events hosted there add another layer of charm. More than just a meal, dining here supports a noble cause, making it all the more worthwhile to explore and endorse.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNY6bN7P2eB7zct_4A0kOI6o7FgWoR-H3d3oeSf&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-2-25"},{"Name":"Adam Myhre","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLlloGTdin2BEFn5bg_e4KC9zJLJE3T-tVTT7t76H3j3mWQRw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"DICED Discovery Cafe, tucked away near Jericho Beach, surpasses its seaside competitors remarkably. This establishment prides itself on prompt service and observant staff, showcasing an unwavering dedication to guest contentment. In fact, there were staff hovering near the entrance the entire time looking for tables to clear or anyone needing anything.  As a dog lover, the inclusive pet-friendly policy significantly enhanced our dining experience, contributing to the overall laid-back vibe of the place.

The outdoor seating area presented a slight hiccup, as only half the tables benefit from the shade, either natural or via umbrellas. However, after a short wait, we managed to nab a shaded spot for our meal.

A point worth noting is the slightly elusive location of the restrooms, hidden within the upstairs hostel. This required a minor search, but the overall experience outweighed this minor inconvenience.

The charm of DICED lies within its simple but well done menu. The irresistible Cuddle burger has managed to capture the hearts of many, including mine. The unbeatable combination of delectable flavor and affordable pricing make it a standout choice!

A crucial aspect not to be forgotten is the cafe's commendable work within the community. Functioning as a social enterprise, DICED invests in shaping the future of young adults in the culinary field. Every delicious meal served is a testament to their commitment towards empowerment and opportunity.

To top it off, we found free street parking just one block away, saving us the usual parking hassle. DICED Discovery Cafe is a great combination of delicious, wallet-friendly food, comfortable ambience, and admirable community engagement.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSPfi0AwhrYBYvn8ORU8C3XN4mxY8m-1H40jSJ&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2023-7-26"},{"Name":"Joshua Brodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLFib9zhnbuMwdZJxwP44egP7q34gwvfJ-Pyd_QVmgeuHQq0g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place and the concept. Unfortunately 2024 wasn‚Äôt as kind to Dice as 3023. Perhaps losing the liquor license for the patio?

However still a great place. And just wonderful people. Great prices.  What more could I want?","Images":null,"When":""}]

The quantity is so small, I am so confused that each of them cost $14.99? How could it be?! Only a server there who was nice and friendly. The worst experiences we have never met.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMYtSdqJj03V3B94ILPOk5SfskXY5XzW29Nq33\u0026fid=0x0:0x4f0ca7813ea9fd69"],"When":"2023-6-4"},{"Name":"Sophia To","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfemfoLMDopq79u8NOfhH5E0jeaAtKfixSXUfKCXkmzZFxRoTV=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super friendly service. I think they are under new management. Had the bibimbap, a fried chicken combo, and cheese balls. Bibimbap is a staple, and was good. The cheese balls are wrapped in mochi and deep fried. Just a hint of sweetness and very satisfying. The chicken is less crunchy than some other places, which I appreciate (sometimes the crunchy stuff ends up taking a layer of skin off the roof of my mouth), and it did not feel greasy. The ordering system is a bit glitchy, but it didn't affect us because we went when it wasn't busy, so they were able to clarify what we wanted.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Forrester","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKclUfheJ5Bxu-Y63dr7FmLPgRgWHLqFZJYBG3AoUFZJiW0tA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We went in for family dinner. Regular chicken was delicious and crispy, and yangnyeom chicken was just right for us. (not too spicy)  Each table were equipped with ordering tablet which were self explanatory.  Definitely will visit again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Maggie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdRAltSXABaU9WZtDiDFGAwgNoF-T5Zl3pbuS7IiXA5Fsl5bFw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Only leaving 5 stars beacuse 10 stars isn't an option. Everything on the menu looked amazing and we are so excited to go back and try more!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPRJ_Squw7YgeJoXdgOp-5lGtNC1QcYeieuJw0\u0026fid=0x0:0x4f0ca7813ea9fd69"],"When":"2023-8-30"}]

[{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bought a 20oz cold brew this afternoon for under $5, takeout.
The donuts looked pretty fancy, and I‚Äôll have to come back for one next time.
Service was good, quick, no problems.

They have bar seating downstairs with enough room to work on a laptop. Upstairs seating and more isolated into individual pairs or quads of seats, some very dark (almost pitch black like coders‚Äô cubicles). Could be alright to work in, if you needed, but most of the table heights aren‚Äôt particularly suited to laptop work.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNI4qmEtB4N21oAzMs9tywfzjWAbycBO8paChkg&fid=0x0:0xf0b2db8921115ce5"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"S. Em","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvU9E4vn1Q9Po0cgEsgrGFBEAIwH-1YuABimdecViWHQsIkbflqg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"JJ bean is great for students needing a coffee and affordable snack.  But they really need to learn to up their pars on the most popular items. It's a campus with  construction crew everywhere and I often find they are out of the best muffins for example. Any other cafe would make more and set it up for times they are busy (lunch hour/4:00) but not this place. Often sold out of the best buy 11:15. Please consider this and upping your pars- esp on the jalapeno cheddar muffin!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rohini Mettu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFejkZ-30wz8Qnk6MZsgaXoKAmWI61rSnOugKhzDrxDe076MC43A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Im not local to Vancouver, but this coffeeshop feels like home away from home (Seattle)!! Wonderful atmosphere, I love the upstairs seating area for coffee chats and study time. They have a great selection of pastries as well - as a scone fan I would recommend trying the cheddar and chive scone 10/10. I got a London fog and my friend got a latte here - the coffee bean itself is not my favorite but I loved the tea!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNUYTZB1LOgf332fOOJr259GPFIis9sTbcIoDG&fid=0x0:0xf0b2db8921115ce5"],"When":"2023-8-21"},{"Name":"Bay Color","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJI1k4Sgd0aWDCqtosK7do8Vp3VfqEkz0STA2XewyBkbsa6hw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I ordered one butter croissant and a medium cup of  cappuccinom. The taste is not badÔºåbut the staff provided a smaller croissant than one that showed in the display cabinet. Because I hurried up to go other place, I forgot to take a picture.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"JJ Bean has a nice selection of food ranging from snacks to full meals, and always delivers on flavour. Delicious jumbo muffins. They have a full range of espresso drinks and their coffee/espresso is nice and smooth. They also do a dreamy London fog. The one drink I wouldn't recommend is the matcha latte - the quality isn't super consistent. Usually it's passable with only a bit of clumping but I've also gotten just frothed almond milk with green clumps floating around. You can get a better matcha latte at any UBC coffee shop and the other drinks here are all worth your money so I would skip the matcha.
Staff is always nice and smiley. The cafe is very clean and there‚Äôs two levels with lots of seating inside and out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsyO6sCRzWquS6GzgViOyhgOixxNiSPBtapTmn&fid=0x0:0xf0b2db8921115ce5"],"When":"2020-10-15"},{"Name":"Komal _","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVe79YhMUnOs_CFq3VFFDZdsazH62kTyKFLVqsc0aMpMFY3ysgM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food and service is good; I'd come for that often. But, the seating, however, is very uncomfortable. Upstairs: all chairs, sofas and other sitting surfaces are hard and very right angled at the back -- which is not particularly comfortable to sit and work from. None of the tables are at a good height respective of the seat. The shop should throw in some cushions on the seats to make the space actually cozy and comfortable.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexandra Rousseau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCc1VRoWPX9lI6oLLlSyZp1wtcpy95ye2Jq395pgPsfvG22Z41=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"JJ Bean serves the BEST chocolate chunk cookies you can find in Vancouver. They‚Äôre actually magical - most of the time, they‚Äôre so fresh that the chocolate is still melty!

The vibes in the cafe are cozy, and I love finding a comfy study space on the second floor. I‚Äôm also a big fan of the gender neutral washrooms: it‚Äôs a welcoming space for everyone :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFjlPNj2axjHSTKksdL9AqkhEsCZXg_I5LH-ga&fid=0x0:0xf0b2db8921115ce5"],"When":"2023-3-15"},{"Name":"Michelle Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrZc4FOCz7AcGuorZE4SGdMyBNzLpAyMERBSqnXndHoxWZ5T_e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"JJ bean has a lot of stores around BC.  Itusually has a long line with people buying coffee and baked gooods.

What did I get?
‚≠êÔ∏èCold brew
‚≠êÔ∏èChocolate zucchini muffin
‚≠êÔ∏èChocolate croissant

Everything is very fresh. The muffin is gigantic (swipe to see). It‚Äôs even larger than my hand!! And it tastes absolutely delicious. The zucchini crunch adds texture and blends really well with the chocolate ( you don‚Äôt taste the zucchini). No wonder it‚Äôs one of the poplar muffins in the shop.
Chocolate croissant is very fresh and crunchy. It has a decent chocolate filling that we adore.
Cold brew is decent. I like the flavour. I‚Äôm down to try other coffee there. I also love that I can use reusable cup there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIsurmTJeHjqxBofZQgY141lMiAS23FkE4SsPk&fid=0x0:0xf0b2db8921115ce5"],"When":"2021-12-28"}]

Tip: they will charge you a bit less if you bring your own container.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPU0hn5Mg4l0zHpKMkGJIxxHqeplCD1bDAmH6oB&fid=0x0:0xcd0ee9e06776c19d"],"When":"2024-3-13"},{"Name":"Grace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpyR6lW9JHiyXGuG73lo5A19PTb1WXFzVLCnrO84Gv3hfeDE5c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It‚Äôs in a convenient location in the Nest, so I‚Äôve eaten here very often throughout undergrad. My go-to are the salmon maki or takoyaki if I want a snack, or a bento or donburi if I‚Äôm more hungry. The crispy chicken is very good. I also like adding on a miso soup for $0.99.

One time, I decided to get some chicken karaage for the first time here, and it was TERRIBLE. It had gone bad and was super stale, it felt like I was chewing plastic.

According to some other reviewers, they‚Äôve also had bad experiences here. I‚Äôd say that Honor Roll‚Äôs food is generally okay and consistent - but once in a while you might get unlucky and get something really bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdCG-1pati8qnNiy0_MICxOyMcRU20pemZxOiB&fid=0x0:0xcd0ee9e06776c19d"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Marc L. When passing the order the vendor did not flinch nor talk to me.
The vendor through a number at me without telling me what it was for.
When the food was ready the vendor did not say anything, I had to check myself.
So she lost her tips - obviously.
Like most students, the vendor doesn't need the income for which she works but it's not a reason to be despicably unprofessional.
It is pathetic to realize how low AMS is ready to go to hire aid.
Not everyone is meant to work, especially the privileged kids who despise labor work because they know it is not something they'll have to do.
The people in charge of hiring SHOULD REALLY start questioning themselves","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"elaine !","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXeWGmQ6CCD8spyKKy_hRGpa5E8CPoGuFlTOZITz-n1J3qegRp-=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"i shouldve listened to the reviews, the sushi rice was as hard as a rock and tasted like it was many days old. the sashimi shrimp tasted like sand and was also hard. avoid the take out food if possible","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Decent selection of grab-and-go items which is of just okay quality compared to sushi in general but a lot better than the average premade sushi. They also have some donburi and poke. I haven't tried the poke but do not recommend the veggie donburi since it's just steamed carrots and broccoli over rice. [{"Name":"Mehmud Iqbal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzdKzd7CEtSWik7PUDkAL2bm7hm1Q3Nn4JMf0vY7aaPod9GjZfWg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Highly recommend this place for authentic Italian cuisine. The pasta was amazing and the servers were very cordial and our utmost attention to the customer needs. The ambience is amazing and suitable for every purposes whether that‚Äôs family or group of friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkd2evFh0o1-Gl_313Imi0RHeNvqA4YGu1M5EC&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Alex Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKIbHt8qTJa2xwClrVQAh4osofzP09STVVcRuaZPnZixApKqA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently dined at Milano Casa with a group of friends. Food was excellent as well as the service. My favourite dish here is Veal Chops. The manager wasn't not only friendly but also knowledgeable about wine. When we ask for recommendations, he guided us through the menu and suggesting wine pairing for our dishes. Overall, great service, great food. It's a place where you can unwind and enjoy delicious food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOlLYVOTxipt4ZBeT91W7ivPgIqmehkuo82DGTh&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2024-2-16"},{"Name":"Ben M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLY7-DFsqx-InW5CnlXpJd6DWvP1u6nfShJnLWMiHPMX_9EZw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The bread is great - both the complimentary bread and the sandwich. The roasted chicken sandwich bread is crunchy outside and soft inside. The pappardelle taste very good.

We sent there for lunch on a weekday and there was only one waitress. She was friendly but was a bit slow, which is understandable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjYZ_ySR3AuaaNaLiBCvxh6fPxBHUUyWzZNIDY&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2024-6-14"},{"Name":"Fern√°n Oviedo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLMNyrTTiHR4Zfs_4KOSf072KTEBXxk2tD4rnh3ffoznWOycg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good food at its price point. We sat on some big chairs that were super comfortable. They were kind enough to split a plate of pasta in two for us to share.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCYtPCqEgECcqRWEUMECcyzfvU8llidqi7vFKs&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2024-6-22"},{"Name":"Ruohan Zhang (Morio)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLyrsA6Ajzj4MMiAAltl5rNoW7U9n4G_g-Ui2_Ju7FBqWwreA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would highly recommend this restaurant. It‚Äôs a quite random visit because I just pass by. And it surprises me by the cozy atmosphere and the amazing flavors of the dessertü•∞","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjJKkn39MAjVfySo-JL1HVJihoQk-97B-eJBol&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Daniel Silver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJawI80c4qwvuA-pWmht_nhIypwFKNS8vUDHnZIepoqs0gJvft7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good food with enjoyable live music on the weekend at dinner. Love the complementary bread which was excellent. Portions are definitely on the larger side.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMlZ61Taxv7LWuGa0WjqPoVlS1JuMIqQwc2fVWN&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2024-5-13"},{"Name":"Tommy Byun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQhlW94B8T2fhww-HWh0iFh-RYIvFitfF4mjJX2E5t_heAv3Lb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking for a new place for a Christmas dinner with a big group (18), and Linda was very helpful in organizing a 3-course meal for the party.

The live music on a Saturday night was amazing, the servers were very friendly, and the owner Babito as well. The atmosphere was energetic, and the entire place is renovated substantially recently, so it was quite clean.

The shocking thing with this restaurant was that the portions for all their dishes were huge, and at least half of our members couldnt finish the main dish. This is difficult to find in any restaurant due to inflation. The only downside I felt was the taste of the food was average and the desert was too sweet, though it may differ between people.

Babito treated us a round of shot for everyone just for fun :) we took some good memories last night.

I gave Linda, the manager, a thank you email, and she got back to me with thisüòä

"We always try our best to make every guest happy. Because every day is a day to remember"

I was happy. Strongly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXfQZ4uw0Izw6Y_wvGRZOFEclqpgAAgcDENT4L&fid=0x0:0x1f76b6b4b29e5148"],"When":"2022-12-12"},{"Name":"Jamie You","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWETbFekq_Et68W-djuZjThdO4JZuMkSpHcfiSGZ5B7-99a9xk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"If you like food that looks nothing like the pictures on google and are bland this is the place for you. The last main arrived 40 minutes after our first one arrived, we were a group of ~20. If you like waiting, this might also be a good choice of restaurant.","Images":null,"When":""}]

My jambalaya was cold and had to send it back. Only one piece of andouille sausage (the cold bite) was a bummer and the chicken was dry. My wife and daughter had the beef stew and butter chicken and it was average. Service was friendly and attentive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxCe4rokS2lf9BBaZE7_T91FcRuvw6tC1IlYDA&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"Allana Berger","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKWM8axIi4jm1P_J7hVKEEINnOaULvzQtvyXxpQ3RFKEW2ytXRaQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've eaten here 5 times now. Every time I'm in BC I go back! The menu changes weekly and my meals have always been delicious. My favorite was a lamb stew. They also have delicious mocktails.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhuGXRYPmzVYMJztbkxH__z7JHRuEWRdXiMbIT&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2024-4-16"},{"Name":"C.A. Walker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV6TWw2B1gYniTx9Jv9I-sjHY7yvLKIKSb2UNOXsFxJKyeXfY8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good vegan friendly healthy conscious menu. Recommend Butter Chicken and French Onion soup .. also the Brie fondue was great- if they‚Äôre on the menu when you go. We were in Vancouver for a weekend getaway. Only 1 star for service because our reservation was for 7:45p we got drinks immediately..but no food until around 9:15.. yes you‚Äôre reading that correctly. They were very apologetic and gave us a discount on the amount owed but it was still quite expensive","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOhHICAkL_sKB-ZBZ-EjwSeWQ4NZ9z0ntDCNs8&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Andrea J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK65HUpzpqY6517xF0fzpt6E222LL02oqw5uRrqd-JC0F_U3w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A family lunch today. What amazing service. So friendly, helpful and attentive. I would go back just for the service. As for food I had the French onion soup. It is very impressive looking, however the taste of the broth was bland. I'd like to try the Mac and cheese next time I go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMn6uYKQ5t4T6IGLJ25lRXeUHAo393hZ2YcA8dH&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2024-2-19"},{"Name":"Rhys G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKhDN_RhBJBaKomIPKrjzczztaQgfWjWmKvGOPFus9xAhXjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dined in and got served by Jan, so kind + welcoming + accommodating to my preferences! I ordered the lamb special and cherry cheesecake for dessert ‚Äî 10/10 need to go again!! Definitely give this place a try when you‚Äôre in the area, this location specifically","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Blue Angel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7f51VtKBeHUyxFkPNC56JU91zCBjw1D7P5VQUMNOkHX1HFd_n=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Managed to locate a place nearby for dinner. Was quite a nice rusty restaurant with some special priced meals and drinks. Ordered the stew beef and lager beer for dinner. Beef was really great with rich flavour beef chunk. Hope to come again next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM57iEqsxZjXMgh47M_yP-vqPJrVMC7AbcfxNdv&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2023-9-5"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cute comfort food eatery. Very warm atmosphere, from the design of the inside to the friendly service. Because the place is relatively small, it‚Äôs probably not a good idea to bring a large group, but it‚Äôs a nice place for a smaller hang or even to chill by yourself. I have been curious for a while and just tried it with some friends. I probably will be back.
They have a great drink menu with lots of specialty cocktails and nonalcoholic drinks. I got a nonalcoholic pineapple guava soda. I don‚Äôt like drinks that are too sweet and this was good for me, but some people might find it weak compared to commercial fruit sodas.
I got a soup and sandwich combo as my entree with the Eggplant Caprese sandwich and the Crab Bisque. I really liked this take on a caprese sandwich, and the baguette was very fresh and soft. The bisque was very good too. Rather than being a super creamy bisque, this was more tomato-based and a little tangy. Good flavour with a fair amount of crab meat. I also liked the little side of coleslaw that was included in the combo.
Wasn‚Äôt really planning on getting dessert but then I saw they had a Chocolate Banana Bread Pudding, and I will rarely pass up on bread pudding. It was delicious but, as you might expect from bread pudding made of banana bread, with ice cream, with caramel sauce, VERY rich and heavy, and I had to get some help to finish it. I think this would be ideal for splitting between two people.
For this meal, with tip, I paid $48, which surprised me. I thought it was a good meal, but not $50 good - I‚Äôd associate that kind of price with a more upscale experience than this. I can understand the soup and sandwich pricing, the dessert was a little expensive, but what really strikes me as obviously overpriced would be the $8 soda. I understand it‚Äôs made in house, but it was just a fruity soda - no fruit bits or anything fancy, and no alcohol. It was a nice refreshing drink, but for $8 I wouldn‚Äôt say it was worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMA-33yhxlhuJWzrEmE3NBivENZ-qwhvFcoFjxN&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2023-5-20"},{"Name":"Keith Ver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVdqxLCf1LEt0AU82myo-eUqDcb2LcbdnfhupJTEW0sPAQ-qQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good food and good service! Loved the ambiance of the whole place. It gives me this vibe that you know you'll be ordering comfort food. Not only will it fill your tummy, but also your soul.

I ordered beef bourguignon and it reminded me of Filipino dish called Caldereta üß° - minus the mashed potatoes that is.

The whole place is accessible as they're located along Main street. Will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOT835yv9VmYFeqt5AwiAEPtu_4O-xMZON9EBlg&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2023-6-5"}]
